Ayodhyā --the capital of Ikṣvākus. The children of Ayodhyā were cast into the Sarayū by Asamañjasa and then restored to life by his yogic power. 1) Bhā. IX. 8. 17-19. Chief buildings were prāsāda, gopura, sabhā, caitya and devagṛha; 2) Ib. IX. 11. 25-34; Br. III. 63. 21; one of the holy cities. 3) Br. IV. 40. 91. City of Rama and Sagara; 4) Br. III. 37. 33; 47. 75; 48. 1; 49. 10 and 58; 53. 5. also known as Śāketa. 5) Br. III. 54. 54. Capital of Madhyadeśa of King Divākara, famous for Rāmatīrtham; 6) M. 191. 93; 271. 5. Vi. IV. 4. 97; Vā. 99. 282. in the nose portion of the personified Veda. 7) Vā. 88. 20, 94; 104. 81: 111. 68.

