उग्रसेन
Ugrasena  (I)--A son of Āhuka of the Kukura family, father of Kamsa and other eight sons. Father of five daughters who were all married to the younger brothers of Vasudeva. 1) Bhā. IX. 24. 21, 24-5; X. 1. 30; Br. III. 71. 129-134, 212-3, 230; M. 44. 71-74; Vā. 96. 206; Vi. IV. 14. 16-21. King of Sātvatas, Vṛṣṇis, Bhojas, and Dāśārhas. 2) Bhā. III. 1. 29. Hated by his son Kamsa who desired even to kill him and who eventually threw him into prison. 3) Ib. X. 44. 33; 1. 69; 36. 34; Vi. V. 15. 18; 18. 6. Enthroned by Kṛṣṇa, after performing Kamsa's funeral rites; 4)Ib. X. 45. 12; Vi. V. 21. 9-12. got helpful service from Kṛṣṇa and welcomed him to Dvārakā. 5) Bhā. III. 2. 22; I. 11. 16; Vi. V. 24. 7. In Kṛṣṇa's opinion Ugrasena was the proper person to wear the jewel Syamantaka; did not press it lest there should be a family feud. 6) Vi. IV. 13. 27-28, 107. When Jarāsandha beseiged Mathurā, Kṛṣṇa stationed Ugrasena to defend the northern gate; was presented with spoils of war including jewels and ornaments. His part in defence against Jarāsandha's third attack on Mathurā. A member of the Yādava sabhā; was consulted by Kṛṣṇa as to failure of rains in Dvārakā. 7) Bhā. X. 50. 20[3]
and 41; [50 (V) 32-33]; [51 (V) 25]; [52 (V) 15]; 57. 30[1]. Vāyu fetched from Indra the hall Sudharmā for Ugrasena's use; 8) Vi. V. 21. 13-17, 32. attacked Pauṇḍraka and laughed at his message. Heard of Sāmba's imprisonment and urged war on the Kurus, order being communicated through Balarāma. According to the Kurus, a king only by sufferance. 9) Bhā. X. 66 [3]; 68. 13, 21 and 34; Vi. V. 35. 10. 14, 23. Ordered the musala born to Sāmba to be powdered and thrown into the sea. 10) Vi. V. 37. 11-12. Sent to Dvārakā for defence after the Rājasūya. 11) Bhā. X. 76. 7[5]. Welcomed Balarāma on his return after a pilgrimage tour. 12) Ib. X. 79. 29. Went to Syamantapañcaka for solar eclipse. 13) Ib. X. 82. 23. Honoured Nanda. 14) Ib. X. 84. 59 and 68. Heard of Vṛṣṇis killing one another and of the decease of Rāma and Kṛṣṇa and bemoaned their loss. 15) Ib. XI. 31. 15; Vi. V. 37. 57. Entered fire. 16) Vi. V. 38. 4.

