उग्रायुध
Ugrāyudha  (II)--the son of Kṛta (Kārtā the SāmagaVā. P.) of Paurava dynasty. Father of Kṣema; slew father of Pṛthuka, the Pāñcāla Nīla: Conqueror of Nīpas: was engaged in severe austerities for 18,000 years. Was served by Janamejaya, son of Bhallāṭa. They were both attacked by Nīpas who were unmoved by Ugrāyudha's appeals for peace and protection; then Ugrāyudha asked Lord of Death to destroy them. Soon he took pity and asked Yama to save them; and this led to a scuffle between Yama and the king who got salvation. M. 49. 59-78; Vā. 99. 182, 191; Vi. IV. 19. 53-55. 

