Upadānavī  (I)--a daughter of Vaiśvānara, and wife of Hiraṇyākṣa. Bhā. VI. 6. 33-4.

उपदानवी
Upadānavī  (II)--a daughter of Sadasya. (YamaVā. P.). Mother of Duṣyanta. Br. III. 6. 23. 25; Vā. 68. 23, 24.

उपदानवी
Upadānavī  (III)--a daughter of Maya; mother of four sons through the son of Ilinā. M. 6. 21; 49. 10. 

उपदेव
Upadeva  (I)--a son of Devaka. Bhā. IX. 24. 22; Br. III. 71. 130; M. 44. 72; Vi. IV. 14. 10.

उपदेव
Upadeva  (II)--a son of Akrūra and Ugrasenā. Bhā. IX. 24. 18; Br. III. 71. 113; M. 45. 31; Vi. IV. 14. 17.

उपदेव
Upadeva  (III)--a son of Manu Rudrasāvarṇi (Ṛtusāvarṇa-Vā.) (Rudraputrasāvarṇi-Vi. P.). Bhā. VIII. 13. 27; Br. IV. 1. 94; Vā. 100. 98; Vi. III. 2. 36.

उपदेवा
Upadevā --one of the seven daughters of Devaka and a queen of Vasudeva; mother of ten sons. Bhā. IX. 24. 23 and 51; Br. III. 71. 131 and 162; Vā. 96. 130, 179; Vi. IV. 14. 18.

उपदेवी
Upadevī --one of the wives of Vasudeva, and mother of four sons. M. 46. 17.

उपदेश
Upadeśa --one of the ten lakṣaṇas of the Brāhmaṇas. Vā. 59. 139.

उपधा
Upadhā(yogam) --By this Brhaspati deluded the Asuras; different tests. Br. III. 73. 40; M. 215. 79; 227. 3; Vā. 79. 65.

उपनन्द
Upananda  (I)--a son of Vasudeva and Madirā; 1) Bhā. IX. 24. 48; Br. III. 71. 171; Vā. 96. 169; Vi. IV. 15. 23. went with Vṛṣṇi's host to Bāṇa's city. 2) Bhā. X. 63. 3.

उपनन्द
Upananda  (II)--an elder gopa addressed an assembly of gopas at Bṛhadvana to leave it on account of evil portents occurring from time to time and go to Bṛṇdāvana. Bhā. X. 11. 22. 29. 

उपनयन
Upanayana --a ceremony for twice-born castes; 1) Vi. III. 9. 1. of Sagara; 2) Vi. IV. 3. 37. of Kṛṣṇa and Rāma. 3) Vi. V. 21. 19.

उपनिधि
Upanidhi --a son of Bhadrā and Vasudeva. Vi. IV. 15. 24.

उपनिषद्
Upaniṣads --essence of: in Śrutigītā. Bhā. X. 8. 45; 45. 33; 87. 43; XII. 6. 41; Br. I. 1. 170; IV. 4. 72; Vā. 1. 200; 6. 22; 20. 25; 30. 231; 97. 158.

उपप्लाव्यम्
Upaplāvyam --reached by Pāṇḍavas after defeating Kurus in cattle-war (gograha). Bhā. X. 78. [95 (V) 2].

उपबर्हण
Upabarhaṇa --the name of Nārada in a previous birth born as a Gandharva. Looking pleasant he spent all time in women's company. His wrong behaviour was discovered in the sacrifice of the gods and he was cursed to be born a śūdra. He took birth as a dāsi's son, and by proper conduct, became the son of Brahmā. Bhā. VII. 15. 69-73.

उपबर्हिण
Upabarhiṇa --a hill of Krauñcadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 21.

उपबिन्दु
Upabindu --belonging to Ārṣeya pravara (Aṅgiras). M. 196. 8.

उपबिम्ब
Upabimba --a son of Bhadrā and Vasudeva. Br. III. 71. 173; Vā. 96. 171.

उपमङ्गु
Upamaṅgu --a son of Gāndini. Vā. 96. 110. 

उपमद्गु
Upamadgu --a brother of Akrūra; father of a number of sons and a daughter Sutārā; (The Cal. Edn. & Wilson's trans. make Upamadgu, the brother of Sutārā and her brothers). Vi. IV. 14. 8-9.

उपमन्यवः
Upamanyavaḥ --the descendants of Upamanyu, son of Vasu. Vā. 70. 89.

उपमन्यु
Upamanyu --a Śrutarṣi and a madhyamādhvaryu; son of Vasu; after him came the group of Aupamanyus. Br. II. 33. 3 & 15; III. 8. 98; Vā. 70. 89.

उपमा
Upamā --the Goddess in Brahmakṣetra. Vā. 59. 130.

उपमाय
Upamāya --a son and commander of Bhaṇḍa. Br. IV. 21. 84; 26. 49.

उपय
Upayas --Śveta Parāśara group. M. 201. 36.

उपयाजि
Upayāji --certain kinds of homas in a sacrifice whose devas are Sudharmāṇaḥ. Vā. 100. 105.

उपराग
Uparāgas --Eclipses: rituals during; worship of the guardians of the different directions; gifts especially in Amarakaṇṭaka best; eligible for śrāddha. M. 17. 11; 18. 22; 67. 1-25; 82. 25; 83. 8; 188. 85 & 95; 193. 53 and 54; Vā. 78. 3-4.

उपरागा
Uparāgā --a śakti. Br. IV. 32. 13. 

उपरिचर
Uparicara  (Burnouf--Uparica)--A Vasu. Son of Kṛti. (Kṛtaka-Vi. P.). Father of Bṛhadratha and other sons. Bhā. IX. 22. 5; Vi. IV. 19. 80-81.

उपरिमण्डल
Uparimaṇḍala --a Bhārgava gotrakara. M. 195. 25.

उपस्कर
Upaskara --broomstick; pregnant Diti (woman) not to sit on. M. 7. 38.

उपलप
Upalapas --a group of sages. M. 200. 9.

उपलम्भ
Upalambha --a son of Akrūra. M. 45. 29.

उपवाह्यका
Upavāhyakā --a daughter of Bhajamāna. Br. III. 71. 3.

उपवीर
Upavīra --a class of Piśācas, generally in the burial ground; wear barks of trees. Br. III. 7. 378 & 382, 392; Vā. 69. 264 and 273.

उपश्लोक
Upaśloka --Father of Manu Brahmasāvarṇi. Bhā. VIII. 13. 21.

उपसङ्ग
Upasaṅga --Had two sons Vajra and Samkṣipta. M. 47. 22.

उपसङ्घ
Upasaṅgha --a son of Vasudeva, killed by Kaṃsa. Vā. 96. 178. 

उपसम्हार
Upasamhāra(pāda) --the fourth pāda of the Purāṇa. Br. I. 1. 38; IV. 4. 43; Vā. 4. 13; 103. 44; 104. 2.

उपसर्ग
Upasargas --accidents to yoga are the results of satva, rājasa and tāmasa guṇas. Vā. 12. 5-6.

उपसुन्द
Upasunda --a son of Nisunda. Vā. 67. 71.

उपस्थेय
Upastheya --see Ajaikapāt. Br. II. 12. 25.

उपस्थेय
Upastheyas --a number of Agnis, all sons of Samśya Agni. Br. II. 12. 26.

उपहारिणी
Upahāriṇī --a Brahmarākṣasī. Vā. 69. 134.

उपहूत
Upahūta --sons of Aṅgiras, brought up by Sādhyas; a class of Pitṛs in the Marīcigarbhaloka; Somajas and Somapas: Their mind-born daughter is Yaśodā, mother of Khatvāṅga. Br. II. 28. 18; III. 10. 89-90; Vā. 73. 39-41.

उपाकर्मेष्टि
Upākarmeṣṭi --the first ritual of the yāga, as part of the Yajña Varāha. Vā. 6. 21.

उपाख्यानम्
Upākhyānam --a feature of the Purāṇa: Legends in general. Br. II. 34. 21; Vi. III. 6. 15. 

उपाया
Upāyās --seven in number: Sāma, Bheda, Daṇḍa, Dāna, Upekṣā, Māyā and Indrajālam: Acts done with upāyās become fruitful. M. 222. 1-3; Vā. 62. 158.

उपावृद्धि
Upāvṛddhi --an Ekārṣeyā. M. 200. 5.

उपासनविधि
Upāsanavidhi --for those purified by karma. Vā. 104. 15.

उपासङ्ग
Upāsaṅga(dhara) --a son of Devarakṣitā and Vasudeva. Had two sons. Br. III. 71. 181, 258; M. 46. 16.

उपेक्षा
Upekṣā --one of the Upāyas of a king. M. 222. 2.

उपेन्द्र
Upendra --a manifestation of Hari born of Aditi and Kaśyapa. He was known as Vāmana because of his short stature. 1) Bhā. X. 3. 42: V. 24. 24; VI. 6. 39; Vā. 98. 84; Br. III. 21. 59; 73. 84. Anointed by gods as the Lord of all worlds. Helped Indra his elder brother in the administration of his kingdoms. 2) Bhā. VIII. 23. 23-25. Knew the yoga power of Hari 3) Ib. II. 7. 45; 5. 30; IV. 2. 18. and was invoked by gopas for the protection of the baby Kṛṣṇa. 4) Ib. X. 6. 22 and 23; Had a son Bṛhatśloka through Kīrti. 5) Ib. VI. 18. 8. Also known as Urukrama. A son of Diti. 6) M. 146. 20; 244. 26-8. Kṛṣṇa, crowned by Indra as the Indra of cows, urged by the speech of Gava; perhaps the cows of heaven like the Kāmadhenu; at that time the cattle delighted the earth with milk. 7) Vi. V. 12. 12-15.

उपेन्द्रदत्त
Upendradatta --surname of Śuka. Bhā. II. 7. 45. 

उपोद्घात
Upodghāta(pāda) --the third part of the Purāṇa 1) Br. I. 1. 39; III. 1. 1; IV. 4. 43; Vā. 4. 13; 65. 2; 103. 44. represents dvāpara yuga and is of 2004 ślokas. 2) Vā. 32. 62.

उभयजातक
Ubhayajātaka --a Pravara of the Bhārgavas. M. 195. 31.

उभयस्पृष्टिह्
Ubhayaspṛṣṭih --R. of Śākadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 26.

उमा
Umā  (I)--worshipped for a happy family. 1) Bhā. II. 3. 7. Her splendour. 2) Ib. VIII. 7. 33; VI. 17. 36. Also known as Ambikā; also Rudrāṇī. 3) Ib. VIII. 18. 17; III. 12. 13. In the forest of Sukumāra. 4) Ib. IX. 1. 25; XII. 10. 4. Consort of Śiva, also Gaurī; originally Dākṣāyanī, daughter of Menā and Himavān. Original name Aparṇā. Her garden: a śakti: 5) Br. II. 25. 17; 26. 44; III 9. 1; 10. 13 and 26; 41. 17 and 55; 60. 24 and 27; IV. 44 84; M. 13. 18-9; 23. 5; Vā. 71. 2-5. The world of: Adhidevatā for the planet Soma. 6) M. 84. 9; 93. 13; 132. 18. Festivities at her birth. 7) M. 154. 93-108. Going with her father to Śiva's house, they met Rati weeping on the way. She said that Śiva had burnt down her husband. On this Umā's father did not like the idea of giving his daughter to such an ill-tempered person. Umā requested permission to do penance and was allowed. Indra at this time thought of the seven sages to bring about Śiva's marriage with Umā. The sages were satisfied of her steadfast love to Śiva and had his consent for the marriage; celestial women dressed Umā, as also the god Śiva; amidst divine music, the couple went to the city of Mahāgirinagara and Brahmā officiated as priest: After the marriage they left for Mandaragiri. 8) M. 154. 276-496. Once Umā made a doll with elephant face and dropped it in the Ganges. It became a huge figure and was claimed as son by Umā and the Ganges respectively. 9) M. 154. 502-505. Then Umā  grew a tender Aśoka plant when Bṛhaspati and others told her that she would have a real son and that trees and dolls were no satisfaction; 10) M. 154. 506-510. once she heard a yell of noise and was told of the play engaged in by Gaṇas, and then her eyes attracted Vīraka. She expressed to Śiva for a son like Vīraka. Śiva asked her to have him as her child. He was sent for and nursed by Umā. 11) M. 154. 522-555. Touched by Goddess of Night, she became black in colour. Śiva found fault with her and after reproaching him with his past deeds, she left him for penance. Vīraka appealed to her when she said she would return as Gaurī. She asked Vīraka to see that no lady entered her harem. Meanwhile Āḍi, son of Andhakāsura entered Śiva's abode in the guise of Umā but was slain by Śiva. Hearing from Vāyu that a lady entered her home, she cursed Vīraka to be born on the earth; out of her rage came out a lion which Brahmā gave to the Goddess of Night, who was asked to leave Umā for the Vindhya hills. Now Umā became Gaurī and entered Śiva's abode when Vīraka stopped her, as he did not at first recognise her. Convinced of his mother's identity, he requested her to recall her curse and was assured of a place in Devagaṇa. 12) M. 154. 588; chap. 15558. While Umā was sporting with Śiva, Agni entered the harem in the form of a parrot. Noticing this Umā left the bed and Śiva made Agni drink his vīrya. Out of the scattered vīrya, there sprang up a beautiful pond where the six Pleiades bathed and took water in a lotus leaf. Blessed by them the Devī got the garbha and out of her left side came out Subrahmaṇya. 13) M. 158. 24-48; Vā. 72 (whole). Going through the Udyānam again Śiva spoke to her of the greatness of Benares. 14) M. 180. 20-79; 181. 6-8; 191. 113; 193. 46. Satī in previous birth. 15) Vā. 30. 71; 54. 20; 55. 42; Br. II. 13. 77.

उमा
Umā  (II)--the goddess enshrined at Viṅāyaka. M. 13. 41. 

उमातुङ्ग
Umātuṅga --a locality fit for performing śrāddha. Br. III. 13. 87-88; Vā. 77. 81-82.

उमापति
Umāpati --surname of Śiva (Śaṅkara); worship of; 1) Bhā. X. 52. 43; M. 185. 24; 274. 15; Vi. V. 33. 40 and 45. destroyer of Dakṣayajña. 2) Vā. 25. 2.

उमामहेश्वर
Umāmaheśvara --to be worshipped in Ādityaśayanam: Image of; worship of; either four or two hands; three eyes; clad in elephant's skin; surrounded by Jaya and Vijaya, and also Kārtikeya and Vināyaka. M. 55. 5; 60. 42; 64. 22; 260. 11-21.

उमावनम्
Umāvanam --in Kailāsa where Śaṅkara assumed Ardhanārīśvara form. 1) Vā. 41. 36. Once Umā requested her lord that whoever might enter her hermitage should be converted to womanhood and that Śiva himself must become a woman in form; hence all the creatures in the great forest became women. Once Sudyumna came on a hunting tour to the place and became a woman. 2) Vā. 85. 25-8.

उमाव्रत
Umāvrata --a rtvik at the yajña of Brahmā. Vā. 106. 39.

उंजिक
Uṃjika --a son of Yadu. Br. III. 69. 2.

उरकाम
Urakāma --the son of Aśmaka. Vā. 88. 178.

उरग
Uragas --a mythical tribe, 1) Bhā. II. 6. 43; 10. 38; Br. IV. 1. 155; 4. 2; M. 5. 1; 6. 29; 23. 39; Vā. 31. 12; 34. 55; 38. 5; 47. 47; 100. 159; 106. 59; 112. 43. brothers of Narmadā; māyās relating to. 2) Bhā. IX. 7. 2; X. 55. 23. Kingdom of; 3) M. 121. 48. see Nāgas. 4) Vi. II. 5. 12. 

उरगबन्ध
Uragabandha --see Nāgapāśa. Vi. I. 20. 4.

उरगारिकेतन
Uragāriketana --Kṛṣṇa. Vi. IV. 13. 114.

उरगेश्वर
Urageśvaras --Lords of Nāgas; (also Pannagādhipatis and Uragapatis). Vi. IV. 3. 5.

उरणक
Uraṇaka --a ram; Urvaśi loved two and brought them up when she was with Purūravas. Vi. IV. 6. 44.

उरःसंकीर्ण
Uraḥsaṃkīrṇa bhaumakas --a Janapada of the Bhadra. Vā. 43. 21.

उरु
Uru --a son of Bhautya Manu. Br. IV. 1. 114.

उरुक्रम
Urukrama --a surname of Hari. See Upendra. Bhā. IV. 12. 28; VII. 11. 1; XI. 5. 26.

उरुक्रिय
Urukriya --the son of Bṛhadraṇa and father of Vatsavṛddha. Bhā. IX. 12. 10.

उरुक्षय
Urukṣaya --the son of Bṛhadbala; a sage; no marriage alliance with Aṅgiras. M. 196. 29; 271. 4.

उरुक्षव
Urukṣava --the son of Āhārya; wife Viśālā; father of three sons. M. 49. 38-9. 

उरुक्षव
Urukṣavas --the Kṣatriya sons of Urukṣava, who became Brāhmaṇas, and the best mahaṛṣis among Kāvyas. M. 49. 40.

उरुगाय
Urugāya --a surname of Hari. Bhā. X. 6. 23; XI. 5. 26.

उरुगम्भीरबुद्धि
Urugambhīrabuddhi --a son of Indrasāvarṇi. Bhā. VIII. 13. 33.

उरुवल्क
Uruvalka --a son of Ilā and Vasudeva. Bhā. IX. 24. 49.

उरुश्रवस्
Uruśravas --the son of Satyaśravas and father of Devadatta. Bhā. IX. 2. 20.

उरुशृङ्ग
Uruśṛṅga --a boundary hill of Śākadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 26.

उर्व
Urva --the son of Ripumjaya and father of Tigma. Vi. IV. 21. 13.

उर्वरीवान्
Urvarīvān  (I)--a son of Pulaha and Kṣamā. Br. II. 11. 31.

उर्वरीवान्
Urvarīvān  (II)--a son of Sāvarṇi Manu. Vi. III. 2. 19.

उर्वश
Urvaśas --the kingdom of. M. 121. 47. 

उर्वशी
Urvaśī  (I)--an apsaras born of Nārāyaṇa; worshipped for success in love affairs. 1) Br. III. 7. 16; Bhā. II. 3. 6. While she was plucking flowers in Badari āśrama Mitra and Varuṇa saw her, when she gave birth to Agastya and Vasiṣṭha. 2) Bhā. VI. 18. 6; IX. 13. 6; M. 201. 25-29; Vi. IV. 5. 11-12. Satyadhṛti saw her, and she was mother of Śaradvata. 3) Bhā. IX. 21. 35; Vi. IV. 19. 65. Heard of the beauty of Purūravas from Nārada, when she came to the earth due to a curse of Mitra and Varuṇa, and gave enjoyment to him so long as he satisfied her two conditions--keeping her two sheep safe, and not showing himself naked before her except in sexual intercourse. When after 64 years she saw him naked one day, she left him. He looked for her and saw her at the R. Sarasvati playing with her friends. At his request she promised a day's enjoyment with him every year. On her advice he prayed to Gandharvas, and got an Agnisthāli. Mother of six sons by Purūravas. 4) Bhā. IX. 14. 16-42; 15. 1; XI. 26. 4-5 and 25; Br. III. 65. 46; 66. 4-5; Vā. 2. 16; 91. 4; Vi. IV. 6. 35-78. Returned to Heaven. 5) Bhā. XI. 4. 15; Br. IV. 33. 18. The Goddess enshrined at Badari. 6) M. 13. 49. When she danced before Indra, she forgot her abhinaya and was cursed by Bharata to become an invisible creeper for 55 years on the earth. During that time Purūravas was in the guise of Paiśāca. After the lapse of the period she bore him 8 sons. 7) Ib. 24. 12-33. In the sabhā of Hiraṇyakaśipu. 8) Ib. 161. 25. Mother of six sons by Aila. 9) Vā. 90. 45. Also Ūrvaśī (s.v.).

उर्वशी
Urvaśī  (II)--The Apsaras presiding over the month of Saha. 1) Bhā. XII. 11. 41; Br. II. 23. 18. With the sun in the Hemanta; 2) Br. I. 2. 16; Vā. 52. 18; M. 126. 19. in the sun's chariot in the Mārgaśīrṣa month; 3) Vi. II. 10. 13. a Brahmavādinī. 4) Br. II. 33. 18.

उर्वशी
Urvaśī  (III)--An Ābhīra kanyā who observed the Bhīmadvādaśī, and became Urvaśī. M. 69. 59. 

उर्वशीपुलिनम्
Urvaśīpulinam --A tīrtha sacred to Pitṛs. M. 22. 66.

उर्वशीरमण
Urvaśīramaṇa --a kṣetram in Prayāga. M. 106. 34.

उर्वी
Urvī --see Bhūmī or Pṛthvī; extent 500 million yojanas; foremost of all elements and mother of all beings; depth below the surface is 70,000 yojanas consisting of the seven regions of Pātāla. Vi. II. 4. 96-7; 5. 1-2.

उर्वीश
Urvīśa --Bhārabhūti; a varamūrti. Br. IV. 44. 49.

उलूक
Ulūka  (I)--the son of Bala, and a righteous person; Father of Vajranābha. Br. III. 63. 205.

उलूक
Ulūka  (II)--a son of Hiraṇyākṣa. M. 6. 14.

उलूक
Ulūka  (III)--a son of Sahiṣṇu of the 26th dvapara. Vā. 23. 213.

उलूक
Ulūka  (IV)--a son of Somaśarma; an avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 216.

उलूक
Ulūka  (V)--a Vidyādhara chief in the Veṇumanta hill. Vā. 39. 38.

उलूक
Ulūkas --son of Bhāsi, owls as children of Śukī; 1) Br. III. 7. 455; M. 6. 31; 237. 12; 240. 18. of Tāmrā line. 2) Vi. I. 21. 16. 

उलूकजित्
Ulūkajit --a son of Dhūminī, sister of Bhaṇḍa; served as a commander Bhaṇḍa, and killed by a Devī of Lalitā. Br. IV. 21. 84; 28. 6, 38 and 100.

उलूकिका
Ulūkikā --Life sucked out by infant Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. II. 7. 27.

उलूकी
Ulūkī --a mindborn mother. M. 179. 15.

उलूखल
Ulūkhala  (I)--the mortar; pregnant Diti not to sit on; 1) M. 7. 38. child Kṛṣṇa tied to by Yaśodā. 2) Vi. V. 6. 14 and 16.

उलूखल
Ulūkhala  (II)--a lekha on this wooden mortar and the honouring of Udapātra are details of the śrāddha connected with the Āśvalāyanins. Vā. 75. 28.

उलूखल
Ulūkhalas (Ulūkhali)  a group of Piśācas (also Ulūkhalikas)--Hidden eyes and long tongues; wearing Ulūkhala for ornaments. Br. III. 7. 378 and 393; Vā. 61. 46; 69. 274.

उलूखलक
Ulūkhalaka --a pupil of Kṛta. Br. II. 35. 52.

उलूखलिक
Ulūkhalikas --see Ulūkhalas. Br. III. 7. 382.

उलूत
Ulūta --a northern kingdom. Br. II. 16. 48.

उलूप
Ulūpas --Trayārṣeyas. M. 198. 5. 

उलूपी
Ulūpī --the queen of Arjuna and mother of Irāvān. 1) Bhā. IX. 22. 32. A Nāgakanyā. 2) Vi. IV. 20. 49.

उल्कचा
Ulkacā --a daughter of Khaśā and a Rākṣasī. Br. III. 7. 138.

उल्कामुख
Ulkāmukha --a Rākṣasa having his city in the third talam. (Vitalam-Vā. P.) Br. II. 20. 29; Vā. 50. 28.

उल्कामुखी
Ulkāmukhī --a mindborn mother. M. 179. 24.

उल्बण
Ulbaṇa --one of the seven sons of Vasiṣṭha and Ūrjā. Bhā. IV. 1. 41.

उल्बम्
Ulbam --womb of the aṇḍa; became cloud. M. 2. 33.

उल्मुका
Ulmukā  (I)--a son of Cākṣusa Manu and Naḍvalā. His queen was Puṣkariṇī. Father of six sons. Bhā. IV. 13. 16-17.

उल्मुक
Ulmuka  (II)--a friend of Jarāsandha, who was stationed at the eastern gate of Mathurā when it was beseiged. Bhā. X. 50. 11[2].

उल्मुक
