Ṛbhavas --one of the five groups of gods of Cākṣuṣa epoch. M. 9. 24.

ऋभु
Ṛbhu  (I)--a son of Brahmā; one of the first two created, the other Sanatkumāra; a siddha who knows the māyā of Hari. 1) Bhā. II. 7. 43; IV. 8. 1; VI. 15. 12; Vā. 9. 106; 24. 79. A resident of Tapoloka; 2) Br. III. 36. 6; IV. 2. 24, 35 and 214; Vā. 101. 26, 37 and 212; Vā. 25. 92. teacher of Nidāgha; imparted to him the essence of true knowledge after partaking of meals with him; once again met Nidāgha after 1000 years; initiated him into the mysteries of Advaita and disappeared. 3) Vi. II. 15. 2-34; 16 (whole).

ऋभु
Ṛbhu  (II)--heard the Viṣṇu Purāṇa from Brahmā; communicated to Priyavrata. Vi. VI. 8. 43.

ऋभु
Ṛbhus  (I)--a class of gods resident in Bhuvarloka 1) Vā. 101. 30. specially created by Bhṛgu to put down the Pramatha and other gaṇas in the sacrifice of Dakṣa. Followers of Indra; 2) Bhā. IV. 4. 33; VI. 7. 2; 10. 17. of Cākṣuṣa epoch. 3) M. 9. 24. 

ऋभु
Ṛbhus  (II)--gods of the Vaivasvata epoch, came to Dvārakā with other gods to ask Kṛṣṇa to go back to Vaikunṭḥa. Bhā. VIII. 13. 4; XI. 6. 2.

ऋषभ
Ṛṣabha  (I)--a sage about whose welfare Arjuna is asked by Yudhiṣṭhira. Bhā. I. 14. 31.

