Ṛṣabha  (III)--a son of Indra and Paulomī. Bhā. VI. 18. 7.

ऋषभ
Ṛṣabha  (IV)--a manifestation of Hari in Dakṣasāvarṇi epoch. Born of Āyuṣmat and Ambudhārā; engaged in dhyānamārga. Bhā. VIII. 13. 20; Vā. 23. 143, 146.

