Ṛṣyaśṛṅga (Kaśyapa)  (II)--married Śāntā, the adopted daughter of Romapāda. Superintended the Iṣṭi of Daśaratha to propitiate Indra and blessed Daśaratha with issue. 1) Bhā. IX. 23. 8-10. The son of a deer, became the plaything of dance, song, etc. 2) Ib. XI. 8. 18. Gave son Caturaṅga to Lompāda-Daśaratha. 3) M. 48. 96. Blessed his son with a son; 4) Vā. 99. 104. one of the seven sages. 5) Vā. 100. 11. L

