Karma  (I)--two-fold; Pravṛtti and Nivṛtti; 1) Vi. I. 1. 27; VI. 4. 41. importance of; 2) Vi. I. 18. 32. that which consists of yajña is best. 3) Vi. II. 14. 14.

कर्म
Karma  (II)--(Vedic) two-fold; Pravṛtta and Nivṛtta. 1) Bhā. VII. 15. 47-49. There is another classification of Karma: Vaidika, Tāntrika,  and Miśra (mixed). 2) Ib. XI. 27. 7. Kṛṣṇa advised Uddhava to pursue nivṛtta and abandon pravṛtta path. 3) Ib. XI. 10. 4. Karma exalted as the source of all good and evil, and appropriate to four castes: is done due to māyāmohan; 4) Ib. X. 23. 50; 24. 13-14 & 18-20. does not lead to final destruction of Karman. 5) Ib. VI. 1. 11. Seven-fold: tapas, brahmacarya, yajña, prajā, śrāddha, vidyā and dāna. Bad karmas--five-fold: killing, theft, injury, drinking and lust. 6) Br. II. 28. 75; III. 4. 5 & 24; 28. 9; IV. 5. 25; 6. 37; Vā. 56. 70.

कर्म
Karma  with Agni is kāmya, naimittika and ajasra; should be done with detachment. 7) Vā. 29. 44; 104. 86-96. Rebirth after death is dependent on. 8) Vā. 14. 2-3, 31-42; 61. 106.

