Karmabhūmi --the earth as distinguished from Heaven. 1) Br. IV. 9. 10. Bhāratavarṣa as compared with others which are bhogabhūmis. 2) Vi. II. 3. 22.

कर्मयोग
Karmayoga --Three-fold. Scriptural and not laukika. Intended for the attached and householders. Ācāra preliminary to karma. Karmakāṇḍa an ocean. Three kinds of  worship--vedic, tāntric, and mixed. Worship of image through a guru and according to established rules. 1) Bhā. XI. 3. 41-55; 20. 6-7; 21. 14-15; 27. 1 & 6-9. Preached by Janārdana to Manu; greater than jñāna yoga; as jñānam is the result of Karma; origin of Brahmā from: also Kriyā yoga; five yajñas and 30 samskāras come under this. 2) M. 52. 3-11; 258. 2. Four of Karma category--Agnihotra, silence, study and sacrifice, when not performed properly give fear. 3) M. 39. 25-7.

कर्मश्रेष्ठ
Karmaśreṣṭha --a son of Pulaha and Gatī. Bhā. IV. 1. 38.

