कश्यप
Kaśyapa  (I)--(Savituḥ Vidvān, Mārīci) son of Marīci and Kalā, and husband of Diti. 1) Bhā. III. 14. 7; IV. 1. 13; Br. II. 37. 44; III. 2. 31; 3. 55; IV. 1. 20; 2. 33. 47; M. 146. 16 & 25; 171. 30; 199. 1, 14, 19; Vā. 63. 41. Married twelve (thirteen Matsya P.) daughters of Dakṣa, who were Brahmavādinīs and Loka-mātas. Married also Pulomā and Kālakā on the advice of Brahmā. Their sons were Dānavas distinguished for warlike qualities. 60,000 of these were killed by Arjuna while in Heaven to please Indra. 2) Bhā. VI. 6. 2, 25, 34-36; M. 4. 55; 5. 13; 6. 1-2, 44; Vā. 65. 115-116, 157-158. Aditi was another wife of Kaśyapa, and was the mother of Vāmana-Hari. On an appeal from her on behalf of gods exiled from Amarāvatī, Kaśyapa taught her the payovrata to please Hari. 3) Bhā. VIII. 13. 6; 16. 2-25; 17. 22-3: X. 3. 42; Br. II. 13. 79. Pleased with the anointing of Vāmana. 4) Bhā. VIII. 23. 21; M. 244. 41; 245. 82. His tejas. 5) Bhā. III. 16. 35-36; 17. 2. Pleased with Diti's Madanadvādaśivratam but did not relish her request for a son to slay Indra but granted it under certain conditions. 6) Bhā. VI. 18. 44-54: III. chap. 14 (whole); M. 7. 30-49. A sage of the Vaivasvata epoch. His descendants. 7) Bhā. VIII. 8. 31; 13. 5; M. 9. 27. Father of Vivasvat. 8) Bhā. IX. 1. 10; M. 11. 2. Awarded Madhyadeśā by Paraśurāma. 9) Bhā. IX. 16. 22. Visited with pupils Bhīṣma on his death-bed; 10) Ib. I. 9. 8. goes round Dhruva. 11) Bhā. IV. 9. 21; M. 127. 24; See Diti, Indra. A Brahmavādin and a Prajāpati. A Devaṛṣi. His sons were Nārada and Parvata, as also Ādityas, Maruts and Rudras. 12) Br. II. 27. 104; 32. 98, 112; 35. 92-95: 38. 3; III. 1. 53; 4. 34; 8. 1 and 27; M. 145. 92; Vā. 1. 138; 3. 2: 65. 53; 84. 26 and 31. An amśa of Brahmā. 13) M. 47. 9; Br. III. 2. 105; 71. 238; Vā. 1. 138; 3. 2; 65. 114. When Dakṣa grew angry on account of his daughter Kaśyapa drank Kaśya, a kind of wine; 14) Vā. 65. 115-17. hence his name; hid yoga in a cave; 15) Br. I. 1. 117; Vā. 83. 83; Br. III. 19. 53. āśrama of; 16) Vā. 37. 22. a sage by jñāna; 17) Ib. 59. 90. place in the Viśvacakra dāna. 18) M. 285. 6. With the sun during the months Saha and Sahasya, 19) Ib. 127. 17. a sage of Cākṣuṣa epoch. 20) Vā. 62. 66. 

