Kāpeya --addressed Sūta to explain creation. Br. II. 6. 1.

काम
Kāma  (I)--God of Love (s.v.); born of Brahmā's heart. Burnt by Śiva, was reborn as Pradyumna, son of Kṛṣṇa, an aṃśa of Vāsudeva. 1) Bhā. III. 12. 26; VIII. 7. 32; X. 55. [2]; Vi. V. 27. 28. Sent by Indra to spoil Nara's penance; 2) Bhā. XI. 4. 7.  to induce Śiva to marry Umā. 3) M. 154. 209-239. For having observed Vibhūtidvādaśīvratam, Anaṅgavatī the courtesan became co-wife with Rati, and her name was Prīti. 4) M. 7. 13; 100. 329. Icon of. 5) M. 261. 53-6. Worshipped Śiva in Siddheśvaram and attained divinity again. 6) M. 191. 110. His arrow afflicted Brahmā who was made to love his own daughter, cursed by Brahmā to be burnt by Rudra; when pointed out that he only discharged his duty, he modified the curse to be born as son of Kṛṣṇa, then of Vasu in Bharata line, to get overlordship of Vidyādharas and finally attain godhood; afflicted the nine devīs. 7) M. 3. 33; 4. 12-21; 23. 23.

काम
