Klībā --a deity. Br. IV. 27. 38.

क्षण
Kṣaṇa --a measure of time. Bhā. III. 11. 7; Br. II. 24. 56; III. 72 29; IV. 1. 211; 32. 14.

क्षत्र
Kṣatra  (I)--a son of Anamītra. M. 45. 25.

क्षत्र
Kṣatra  (II) 1) Vā. 99. 268.--its dharma; 2) Ib. 99. 227. originated with the sons of Kāmyā and Priyavrata; 3) Br. II. 11. 34; Vā. 26. 35; 28. 19; 32. 46; 93. 7. powerful householders were appointed for the protection of the world and they were Kṣatriyas; duties of; to serve in an army, to be king and to take part in war; 4) Br. II. 7. 154; 161-66. to protect the people and engage in righteous wars. 5) Vi. VI. 7. 3. 

क्षत्रधर्म
Kṣatradharma  (I)--the son of Aṅenas, father of Pratipakṣa. His line ended with Kṛtadharma. Br. III. 68. 7 and 11.

क्षत्रधर्म
Kṣatradharma  (II)--a son of Samkṛti and the last of the Kṣatravṛddha line. Vi. IV. 9. 27.

क्षत्रजित्
Kṣatrajit --a son of Kālanemi. Vā. 67. 80.

क्षत्रम्
Kṣatram --the body of Brahmā, while the Brāhmaṇa is his heart. Both dependent on each other; 1) Bhā. III. 22. 3-4; Br. II. 36. 23. created with the Brāhmaṇa, and hence no obstacle to intermarriage between Kṣatriya and Brāhmaṇa; 2) M. 30. 19-20. dharma of; no sin in killing men in war. 3) M. 43. 18; 103. 21-22; 114. 12.

क्षत्रविद्ध
Kṣatraviddha --a son of Raucya Manu. Br. IV. 1. 104.

क्षत्रवृद्ध
Kṣatravṛddha --a son of Āyu, and father of Suhotra and Pratikṣatra. Bhā. IX. 17. 1-2; Br. III. 67. 2; Vi. IV. 8. 3; 9. 25.

क्षत्रि
Kṣatri --a name of Vidura. Bhā. XII. 12. 8.

क्षत्रिय
Kṣatriya  (I)--the fourth Manu. Vā. 26. 35. 

क्षत्रिय
Kṣatriya  (II)--created out of the breast of Brahmā; 1) Br. II. 5. 108; Vā. 30. 83, 232; 45. 117; 54. 111; 57. 52; 100. 246; 101. 5, 352. 104. 13; Vi. I. 6. 6. the Aindrasthānam. 2) Vi. I. 6. 34. Distinctive traits; a)Bhā. VII. 11. 14-15, 17 and 22. protection and other duties; b)X. 24. 20; Vi. III. 8. 26-29. definition of; 3) Bhā. XI. 17. 17. destroyed by Kalki. 4) Bhā. X. 40. 22. and by Mahāpadmananda. 5) Ib. XII. 1. 8. seven clans distinguished; become Brahmanas by dāna, yajña and tapas. 6) Br. II. 291. 55; III. 10. 89; 28. 56; 63. 141; 66. 77; 71. 231. Their Pitṛs are Haviṣmantas; observe pollution for 12 days for father's death; pray to Devi; 7) M. 13. 63; 15. 17; 18. 2. can take to Vaiśyakarma and not to Śūdrakarma. 8) Vi. III. 8. 39.

क्षत्रिय
Kṣatriya Puṅgavas --the Haihayas and the Tālajanghas, so called. Vā. 88. 129.

क्षत्रोपक्षत्र
Kṣatropakṣatra --a son of Upamadgu. Vi. IV. 14. 9.

क्षत्रोपेतद्विज
Kṣa(ā)tropetadvijas --Rathitaras, Viśvāmitras and others; 1) Br. III. 63. 7; 66. 86; Vā. 88. 7; Vi. IV. 2. 10. Śibis, Bharadvājas, Samkṛtyas, Kāvyas, Maudgalyas and Bhārgavas; 2) M. 49. 38 and 41; 50. 5 and 14. of Aṅgiras; Saunakas and Ārṣṭiaṣeṇas. 3) Vā. 88. 73 and 79; 92. 6. Gārgyas, Śaṃyas and Mandagolapas. 4) Vi. IV. 19. 23, 60. Viśvāmitra, Māndhātā, Samkṛti, Kapi, Purukutsa, Satya, Ānṛhavān, Ṛthu, Ārṣtiṣeṇa, Ajamīḍha, Bhāganya, Anya, Kakṣīva, Śijaya, Rathītara, Runda, Viṣṇu, Vṛddha Gārgyas; all these rājaṛṣis who have become Brāhmaṇas. 5) Vā. 91. 115-7; 99. 161 and 198.

क्षतौजस्
Kṣataujas --the son of Kṣemadharma and father of Vidhisāra. Ruled for 40 years. Br. III. 74. 130. Vi. IV. 24. 12-13.

क्षपण
Kṣapaṇa--(c)  a southern kingdom. Br. II. 16. 56. 

क्षपाविश्वकर
Kṣapāviśvakara --Ārṣeya pravara (Aṅgiras). M. 196. 10.

क्षम
Kṣama --a Sudhāmāna god. Br. II. 36. 27.

क्षमा
Kṣamā  (I)--a Brahmarākṣasī. Br. III. 7. 99.

क्षमा
Kṣamā  (II)--a Śakti. Br. IV. 44. 91.

क्षमा
Kṣamā  (III)--a daughter of Dakṣa; wife of Pulaha Prajāpati; 1) Vā. 10. 28, 31; 28. 25; Vi. I. 7. 25. mother of sons Kardama, U(A)rvarīvān, Sahiṣṇu, Kanakapīṭha and daughter Pīvari. 2) Br. II. 9. 52; 11. 30.

क्षमा
Kṣamā  (IV)--the wife of Kratu. Vi. I. 7. 7.

क्षमा
Kṣamā  (V)--a R. from the Ṛsyavat hills. M. 114. 25.

क्षय
Kṣaya --a son of Bṛhadkṣaya. Vā. 99. 281.

क्षात्रिय
Kṣātriya vidhi --not to kill a woman. See also Kṣatriya. Vā. 94. 14; 96. 224.

क्षाम
Kṣāma --the son of Saharākṣa, who burns down houses; 1) Vā. 29. 34. his son Kravyādagni. 2) Br. II. 12. 37.

क्षान्ती
Kṣāntī --the main stream of Krauñcadvīpa. Vi. II. 4. 55. 

क्षारकर्दम
Kṣārakardama --one of 28 hells. conceited men who disregard their superiors in birth, merit, learning, etc., are punished in this. Bhā. V. 26. 7 and 30.

क्षारोद
Kṣāroda --see Kṣiroda. Bhā. V. 1. 33.

क्षारोदधि
Kṣārodadhi --a lac of Yojanas in extent encircling Jambūdvīpa. Vi. II. 31. 28; 4. 1.

क्षिति
Kṣiti --a secondary divinity. Bhā. IV. 14. 26.

क्षिप्र
Kṣipra --a son of Upāsaṅga (Upānga-Vā. P.). Br. III. 71. 258; Vā. 96. 249.

क्षिप्रा
Kṣiprā  (I)--a R. from the Vindhyas, sacred to Pitṛs. Br. II. 16. 32; M. 22. 24; 114. 27.

क्षिप्रा
Kṣiprā  (II)--a R. from the Pāriyātra hills. Br. II. 16. 29.

क्षिमक
Kṣimaka  (Kṣemakas alias Nikhumbha)--a Rākṣasa who invaded the city of Kāśi during the rule of Divodāsa and brought it to ruin; 1) Vā. 92. 38. 2) Ib. 92. 24. the head of a gaṇa of Maheśvara. 3) Ib. 9. 36.

क्षीर
Kṣīra --Ārṣeya pravara (Aṅgiras). M. 196. 6.

क्षीरक
Kṣīraka --sacred to Lalitā. Br. IV. 44. 97. 

क्षीरपयोनिधि
Kṣīrapayonidhi --the residence of Hari. 1) Bhā. X. 1. 19. see Kṣīroda (s.v.), Kṣīrasāgara, and Kṣīrābdhi. 2) Br. III. 28. 8; IV. 9. 56 and 64; 31. 19.

क्षीरम्
Kṣīram --one of the eight Saubhāgyam. M. 60. 9 and 27.

क्षीरसमुद्र
Kṣīrasamudra --see Kṣīroda, and Kṣīrābdhi. Bhā. X. [65 (v) 24]; M. 249. 14 and 20.

क्षीराब्धि
Kṣīrābdhi --the birth-place of Śrī; 1) Vi. I. 8. 16. churned for nectar; 2) Ib. I. 9. 77 and 148. on its banks lived Viṣṇu. 3) Ib. V. 1. 32.

क्षीराब्धिशायि
Kṣīrābdhiśāyi --is Viṣṇu. Vā. 106. 48; 107. 34.

क्षीरोद
Kṣīroda --the milk ocean encircling Śākadvīpa; (Krauñca-Bhā. P., Kuśa-M. P); churning of, for amṛta; 1) Bhā. V. 1. 33; 20. 18; X. [65. (v) 24]. Br. II. 19. 102; 21. 71; 25. 45. M. 122. 49; 124. 48; Vā. 35. 37-41; 54. 49; Vi. II. 4. 71. cursed by Brāhmaṇas to be deprived of all drinkable water; here lies Hari in yoganidra guarded by Garuḍa. Viṣṇu in the form of Ādikūrma. 2) Bhā. X. [52 (v) 7; 10]; Br. II. 27. 25; III. 69. 32; 72. 21; IV. 9. 46 and 60. Encircles Trikūṭa; 3) Bhā. VIII. 2. 1; 4. 18. Śuka to Parīkṣit on the legend of the churning of ocean. 4) Bhā. VIII. 5. 11-15.

क्षीरोदा
Kṣīrodā --a R. of the Bhadrā. Vā. 43. 29.

क्षुद्रक
Kṣudraka --a son of Prasenajit and father of Raṇaka. (Kuṇḍaka-Vi. P.). (Kṣulika-Vā. P.). Bhā. IX. 12. 14-15; M. 271. 13; Vā. 99. 289; Vi. IV. 22. 9. 

क्षुद्रभृत्
Kṣudrabhṛt --a son of Devaki killed by Kamsā. Kṛṣṇa recovered him from Sutala, and took him to Dvāraka. After being seen by his parents, went to heaven. Bhā. X. 85. 51-56.

क्षुद्रराक्षस
Kṣudrarākṣasas --the insignificant Rākṣasas born of Nilā. Vā. 69. 178.

क्षुधि
Kṣudhi --a son of Kṛṣṇa and Mitravindā. Bhā. X. 61. 16.

क्षुप
Kṣupa --the father of Vimśa. Vā. 86. 6.

क्षुपण
Kṣupaṇas--(c)  people of a hilly country. Vā. 45. 135.

क्षुभ्य
Kṣubhya --a Bhārgava gotra. M. 175. 22.

क्षुलिक
Kṣulika --a son of Kṣudraka. His son was Suvrata. Vā. 99. 290.

क्षेत्र
Kṣetra--avyaktam  and Kṣetrajña are Brahmā; the union of these two leads to the eternal being; also aviṣaya and viṣaya. Br. I. 3. 37; Vā. 102. 34-6, 111-14.

क्षेत्रक्षेत्रज्ञ
Kṣetra-kṣetrajña --kṣetra and Brahman or aviṣaya and viṣaya. Vā. 102. 36.

क्षेत्रज्ञ
Kṣetrajña  (I)--the son of Kṣemadharman and father of Vidhisāra. Bhā. XII. 1. 5. 

क्षेत्रज्ञ
Kṣetrajña  (II)--is Puruṣa; 1) Br. II. 32. 85; IV. 3. 86-90, 102 and 108; 4. 19. four powers of jñānam, Vairāgyam, aiśvaryam and Dharma; ety. 2) M. 145. 72-8. Lord of Prakṛtis; 3) Vā. 101. 223, 228; 102. 33, 108-9; 103. 27. called Mati by his knowledge of kṣetrā. 4) Vā. 59. 70; Br. I. 3. 37.

क्षेत्रज्ञ
Kṣetrajña  (III)--involuntary for his action and stands in its own natural place; when kṣetra and kṣetrajña have equal guṇas and no vaiṣamya takes place; vaiṣamya or excess or otherwise of these guṇas when they take to the quality of Bhojya bhoktṛtva; the 24 guṇas from Mahat to viśeṣa. Vā. 103. 15-19.

क्षेत्रपाल
Kṣetrapālas --attendants to Śiva; 1) Br. III. 41. 33; IV. 14. 7. Kārtavīrya known as. 2) M. 43. 27; Vā. 94. 24.

क्षेत्रोपेक्ष
Kṣetropekṣa --a son of Śvaphalka and Gāndinī. Bhā. IX. 24. 16.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (I)--one of the seven divisions of Plakṣadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 3.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (II)--born of Dharma and Titikṣā. Bhā. IV. 1. 52.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (III)--the son of Śuci and father of Suvrata; ruled for 28 years. Bhā. IX. 22. 48; M. 271. 25.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (IV)--a son of Śānti. Br. II. 9. 61; Vā. 10. 37.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (V)--a Satya god. Br. II. 36. 35. 

क्षेम
Kṣema  (VI)--a son of Brahmadhāna; 1) Br. IV. 7. 98; Vā. 69. 132. Ajita deva. 2) Vā. 67. 34.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (VII)--the son of Sunītha, and father of Ketumat. Br. III. 67. 73.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (VIII)--of Bṛhadratha line, ruled for 28 years. Br. III. 74. 116; Vā. 99. 302.

क्षेम
Kṣema  (IX)--a son of Ugrāyudha. M. 49. 78; Vā. 99. 193.

क्षेमक
Kṣemaka  (I)--the son of Nimi, the last king of his line. Bhā. IX. 22. 44-5.

क्षेमक
Kṣemaka  (II)--a son of Medhātithi, and founder of the kingdom Kṣemakam in Plakṣadvīpam. Br. II. 14. 37 and 39; Vā. 33. 33; Vi. II. 4. 4-5.

क्षेमक
Kṣemaka  (III)--a Rākṣasa who made Benares desolate. Br. III. 67. 27.

क्षेमक
Kṣemaka  (IV)--a son of Nirāmitra; (Nimitta-Vi. P.), the last son of the Aila line (Paurava) (Kurus-Vi. P.); with him ends the source of the Brahma-kṣetra stock, the family honoured of gods and sages; the last dynasty consisting of 25 kings. Br. III. 74. 245; M. 50. 87-8; Vā. 99. 277-79; Vi. IV. 21. 16-18.

क्षेमक
Kṣemaka  (V)--a son of Maṇivara. Vā. 69. 160.

क्षेमकम्
Kṣemakam--(c)  the country adjoining the Vṛṣabha or Surmāna hill in Plakṣadvīpa; 1) Br. II. 14. 39; 19. 16; Vā. 49. 14; Vi. II. 4. 4-5. same as the Maināka varṣa. 2) M. 122. 25. 

क्षेमजित्
Kṣemajit --a son of Kṣemadharma; ruled for 24 years. M. 272. 8.

क्षेमधनवन्
Kṣemadhanavan (Kṣemadhanvā) --son of Puṇḍarīka and father of Devānīka. Bhā. IX. 12. 1-2; Br. III. 63. 202-3; M. 12. 53; Vā. 88. 202; Vi. IV. 4. 106.

क्षेमधर्मन्
Kṣemadharman  (I)--the son of Kākavarṇa--ruled for 20 (36 (?) Mat. P.) years; father of Kṣetrajña (Kṣatraujas-Vi. P.). Bhā. XII. 1. 5; Br. III. 74. 129; M. 272. 7; Vi. IV. 24. 11-12.

क्षेमधर्मन्
Kṣemadharman  (II)--(Kṣemadharmā) a son of the third Sāvarṇa Manu. Br. IV. 1. 81; Vā. 100. 84.

क्षेमभूमि
Kṣemabhūmi --the son of Vikramitra; ruled for 10 years. Vā. 99. 342-43.

क्षेममूर्ति
Kṣemamūrti --a Vānara chieftain and son of Śveta. Br. III. 7. 181.

क्षेमवर्मन्
Kṣemavarman --ruled for twenty years. Vā. 99. 316.

क्षेमा
Kṣemā --an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 7.

क्षेमाधि
Kṣemādhi --a son of Citraratha and king of Mithilā. Bhā. IX. 18. 23-24.

क्षेमानन्द
Kṣemānanda --a god of the epoch of the Uttama Manu. Vā. 62. 32. 

क्षेम्य
Kṣemya  (I)--a son of Ugrāyudha. Father of Suvīra. (Sudhīra-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 21. 29; Vi. IV. 19. 55.

क्षेम्य
Kṣemya  (II)--a son of Śuci and father of Suvrata. Vi. IV. 23. 6.

क्षैमी
Kṣaimī --a Śyāma Parāsara. M. 201. 37.

क्षोनि
Kṣoni --was instructed in Vāraha Purāṇa by Hari. M. 53. 39.

क्ष्वेला
Kṣvelā --a mind-born mother. M. 179. 25.

खगण
Khagaṇa --the son of Vajranābha and father of Vidhṛti. Bhā. IX. 12. 3.

खट्वाङ्ग
Khaṭvāṅga  (I)--a son of Viśvasaha, and Cakravartin. Fought for the devas and slew Daityas in battle. Knowing he had an hour of life left he returned and devoted himself to Nārāyaṇa in a detached spirit, and attained Brahmaloka in a muhūrta. A Rājaṛṣi who sought refuge in Hari towards the end of his life. His son was Dīrgabāhu. Bhā. IX. 9. 41-49; II. 1. 13; XI. 23. 30; IX. 10. 1; Vi. IV. 4. 76-83.

खट्वान्ग
Khaṭvānga  (II)--a son of Yaśodā, 1) Br. III. 10. 90. a rājaṛṣi. 2) Vā. 73. 41.

खट्वान्ग
Khaṭvānga  (III)--A daitya. Bhā. XII. 3. 9. 

खट्वाङ्गद
Khaṭvāṅgada --the son of Dilīpa; descended from heaven and lived here for a muhūrta. Vā. 88. 182.

खड्ग
Khaḍga siddhi --a yoga siddhi. Br. IV. 36. 52.

खड्गि
Khaḍgi --a name of Gaṇeśa. Br. IV. 44. 70.

खण्ड
Khaṇḍa --the son of Jambha. Vā. 67. 78.

खद्योत
Khadyota --a stage in which Īśvara roamed like insect during night of Brahmā. Br. II. 24. 9; 32. 78.

खद्योता
Khadyotā --one of the Eastern entrances of the city of Purañjana, allegorically the left eye. Bhā. IV. 25. 47; 29. 10.

खनपान
Khanapāna --born of Anga and father of Diviratha. Bhā. IX. 23. 6.

खनित्र
Khanitra --the son of Pramati, (Prajāpati-Vi. P.) and father of Cākṣuṣa (Kṣupa-Vā. P.) (Cakṣuṣa-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 2. 24; Vā. 86. 5; Vi. IV. 1. 24.

खनिनेत्र
Khaninetra --the son of Rambha, (Vivīmśa-Vā. P., Vi. P.) and a righteous king; father of Karamdhama (in Tretāmukha-Vā. P.), (Ativibhūti-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 2. 25; Vā. 86. 7; Vi. IV. 1. 28.

खर
Khara  (I)--vanquished by Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. II. 7. 34. 

खर
Khara  (II)--Śiva cursed to become Khara by the sages of Dāruvana inadvertently--described. 1) Br. II. 27. 5-20. Donkey born of Sugrīvi. 2) M. 6. 33.

खर
Khara  (III)--a son of Vijvara. Br. III. 6. 33.

खर
Khara  (IV)--a son of Viśravas and Puṣpotkaṭa; 1) Br. III. 8. 55; Vā. 70. 49; 99. 406. a Rākṣasa in the third talam (Vitalam); 2) Bhā. IX. 10. 9; Vā. 50. 27. in the Tārakamāya; 3) M. 173. 17; 177. 7. killed by Rāma. 4) Br. II. 20. 28; Vi. IV. 4. 96.

खरपथ
Khara(ā)patha --a region through which Pāvanī flows; a kingdom. Br. II. 18. 57; M. 121. 56; Vā. 47. 54.

खररोमा
Khararomā --a nāga. Vā. 69. 74.

खरवाच
Kharavāca --a Trayārṣeya. M. 198. 5.

खर्वट
Kharvaṭa --a territorial division where the four-armed Kumāra may be established; 1) M. 260. 47; 283. 3. a village at the foot of the mountain; 2) Vā. 91. 30. a mixed township. 3) Vi. V. 2. 13.

खर्वम्
Kharvam --one thousand crores. Vā. 101. 96.

खला
Khalā  (I)--a daughter of Bhadrāśva and Ghṛtāci. Vā. 70. 69. 

खला
Khalā  (II)--one of the ten daughters of Raudrāśva. Vā. 99. 126.

खलीयान्
Khalīyān --(Khāliya-Vā. P.). a pupil of Śākalya. Br. II. 35. 2; Vā. 60. 64.

खल्यायन
Khalyāyanas --Dhūmra Parāśaras. M. 201. 38.

खश
Khaśa --defeated by Bharata; 1) Bhā. IX. 20. 30. a kingdom of the East watered by the Cakṣuṣ and Gaṅgā. 2) Br. II. 18. 46 and 50; 31. 83; M. 121. 43; 144. 57.

खस
Khasas --an inferior tribe purified of sin by devotion to Hari. 1) Bhā. II. 4. 18: Vā. 58. 83; 62. 124; 98. 108. A Vindhyan forest tribe being a degraded Kṣatriya clan, Niṣādhas; 2) Br. II. 36. 145; III. 63. 120. a hilly country. 3) Vā. 45. 135; 47. 47.

खशा
Khaśā --a consort of Kaśyapa; mother of two sons, Vikarṇa and Vilohita, one of four hands and four feet and the other of three hands and three feet, who were born in the evening and Uṣa period respectively. The eldest wanted to make a meal of of the mother herself and this the younger prevented. The father who noted this, named the elder Yakṣa, and the latter Rakṣa and said ‘tri’: it is said a son serves his mother and a daughter her father; and that the sons take after their mother. Seeing them ever hungry, he blessed them to get strength in the night and weakness in the day time and eat meat and flesh and disappeared. They married Brahmadhanā and Jantudhanā, daughters of two Piśacas, Aja and Śaṇḍa, and gave birth to a number of Rākṣasas, all given to fierceness; 1) Br. III. 3. 56; 7. 37, 132-42, 467; Vā. 69. 74-126; Vi. I. 15. 124. mother of Rākṣasa  clans and of seven daughters who in their turn produced Rākṣasas. 2) Vā. 69. 164, 170-2.

खसृम
Khasṛma --a son of Vipracitti. Vi. I. 21. 11.

खद्ग
Khadga --rhinoceros; flesh very good for śrāddha, but horn to be thrown away. Vā. 80. 51.

खाण्डवप्रस्थ
Khāṇḍavaprastha --the place where Kṛṣṇa, Arjuna and Bhīma met Yudhiṣṭhira after the fall of Jarāsandha. Bhā. X. 73. 32.

खाण्डव
Khāṇḍava --forest burnt by Arjuna, and Maya was liberated from the fire. Here Arjuna defeated Indra. Bhā. I. 15. 8; X. 58. 25-7; 71. 45-46; 89. 34 [4].

खाण्डव
Khāṇḍava --an Arṣeya pravara of Bhārgavas. M. 195. 40.

खाण्डिक्य
Khāṇḍikya  (I)--the son of Mitadhvaja. He knew the truth of Karma. He was afraid of Keśidhvaja. Bhā. IX. 13. 20-21.

खाण्डिक्य
Khāṇḍikya  (II)--(Janaka, Vasudeva) the latter of which name is explained by Keśidhvaja in early times; 1) Vi. VI. 1. 81-7. heard on yoga; son of Amitadhvaja and king; in hostility driven out by Keśidhvaja came to him to consult on the form of expiation; after being instructed and after the penance, Keśidhvaja called over again to pay the preceptor's fee; Khāṇḍikya who had no more concerns in this life asked for instruction on the doctrine of the soul; heard of the nature of yoga from Keśidhvaja; making his son master of his belongings went to the woods for penance. 2) Ib. VI. 6. 5-50; 7. 102-03. 

खिलिखिलि
Khilikhilis --not to have marital relations with Viśvāmitra, etc. M. 198. 21.

खेचर
Khe-caras --presented dance, song and music to Pṛthu. Bhā. IV. 15. 19.

खेचरी
Khecarī --a Varṇa śakti; a mudrā Devī. Br. IV. 37. 10; 42. 14; 44. 59 and 86. 114.

खेट
Kheṭa --a small village. Vā. 91. 30.

खेटक
Kheṭaka --a rural territorial division. M. 283. 3; Vā. 8. 99, 116; Br. II. 7. 93 and 111.

खेटा
Kheṭā --a mind-born mother. M. 179. 17.

खेत
Kheta --a smaller division than a Kharvaṭa. Vi. V. 2. 13.

ख्याती
Khyātī  (I)--a son of Ulmuka and Puṣkariṇī. Bhā. IV. 13. 7.

ख्याति
Khyāti  (II)--a son of Tāmasa Manu. Bhā. VIII. 1. 27; Br. II. 36. 49; Vi. III. 1. 19.

ख्याति
Khyāti  (III)--a son of Ūru (Kuru-Vi. P.) and Āgneyi. Br. II. 36. 108; M. 4. 43; Vi. I. 13. 6.

ख्याति
Khyāti  (IV)--a daughter of Kardama, (Dakṣa-Vā. P., Vi. P.) married to Bhṛgu. Mother of sons Dhātṛ and Vidhātṛ and daughter of Śri. Bhā. III. 24. 23; IV. 1. 43; Br. I. 9. 52. 54; 11. 1; III. 25. 77; Vā. 10. 27, 30; 62. 43; Vi. I. 7. 7, 25. 

ख्याति
Khyāti  (V)--a daughter of Bhṛgu; same as Śrī; wife of Nārāyaṇa; sons, Bala and Utsāha by him; others Mānasa, mind-born. See Śrī. Vā. 28. 1-3.

ख्याती
Khyātī  (VI)--a R. in Krauñcadvīpa. Br. II. 19. 75; M. 122. 88; Vā. 49. 69.

ख्याति
Khyāti  (VII)--(ety.) knowledge; all known. Vā. 4. 35.

ख्यातेय
Khyāteyas --Nīla Parāśaras. M. 201. 34.

गगनमूर्ध
Gaganamūrdha --a Dānava; a son of Danu. Br. III. 6. 10: Vā. 68. 10.

गंगा
Gaṃgā  (I)--a R. source of, sacred to Hari; 1) Bhā. VII. 14. 29, VIII. 4. 23, Br. II. 16. 11, 24. brought to the earth from Heaven; a mahānadī from the Himalayas. 2) Vā. 42. 39-49: 71. 5. Originating from the foot of Viṣṇu and watering the region of the moon falls from heaven into Brahmā's city; issuing from the nail of the great toe of Hari's left foot; Dhruva holds her in his crown; the seven sages perform austerities with her waters; issuing again from the moon she falls on Sumeru and thence to the four quarters of the earth; hearing of her, the desire to go to Gangā, see, touch, bathe in her waters--all purify a person; falling in four directions, takes the names of Śītā, Alakanandā, Cakṣu and Bhadrā. 3) Vī. I. 9. 103: II, 2. 334: 8. 108-13, 120-2: III. 14. 18 IV. 4. 26-30: 18-28. Effort made by Amśumān, Dilīpa and Bhagīratha and hence her name Bhāgīrathī. Held up by Hara and then let; flowed in seven streams through several territories in the four directions, sanctifying the regions and the people there. 4) Bhā. IX. 9. 1-13: Br. III. 13. 118: 55. 51: 56. 38-54. Its waters drunk by Janhu, and let out by his ears and hence called Jānhavī. 5) Bhā. IX. 15. 3: Br. III. 66. 25-6: 73. 117: M. 12. 44: 121. 26. The seed cast off by Śiva in the  sky was borne by Gangā and was swallowed by Agni; phoetus left on the Himalayan slopes became gold, which was utilised in building the yagñaśāla at Naimiṣa. At her confluence with Yamunā (s.v.) was the avabhṛta of the sacrifice of Prajāpatis. On its banks Bharata performed horsesacrifice. 6) Bhā. IV. 7. 63-4: Vā. 2. 17-18: 72. 28-32. Br. II. 16. 11 and 24. Bhā. VII. 14. 29; VIII. 4. 23 Vā. 42. 39-40: 71. 5. Bhā. IX. 9. 1-13. Br. III. 13. 118: 55.51: 56. 38-54. M. 15. 3. Br. III. 66. 25. 6: 73. 117: M. 12. 44: 121. 26. Bhā. IV. 7. 63-64. Vā. 2. 17-18: 72. 28-32. Bhā. IV. 2. 35. IX. 20-25: 22. 19: X. 10. 4. Here Yudhiṣṭhira had his avabhṛta bath after Rājasūya. 7) Bhā. X. 75. 19. Here were done funeral rites of the dead children of Draupadī. 8) Ib. I. 8. 1. Here again Parīkṣit observed vow of fasting unto death. 9) Ib. 3. 43; 4. 10; 12. 28; 18. 3. Visited by Balarāma. 10) Ib. X. 78. 20. The Sagaras sent to heaven by the Ganges waters. 11) Ib. IX. 9. 14. Gangā as devī. 12) Ib. I. 19. 15. Originally of three-fold path, the Chāyāpathā being in the nakṣatramaṇḍala; 13) Br. II. 18. 26-42, 50-52: addressed by Agni to bear Rudra's garbha, Gangā accepted the task and gave birth to Kumāra. 14) Br. III. 7. 355: 9. 4: 10. 30-5: 14. 84: 37. 5: 54. 49: IV. 9. 78. Gangā refilled the ocean, after Agastya drank it dry. 15) Br. III. 63. 167. Manu put the growing fish in; washed off the city of Hastināpuram; contains 3(1/2) crores of tīrthas; forms the cure for all ills; released in seven streams by Śankara, three to the west, three to the north and one Bhagīrathī, sacred in Kanakhala. 16) M. 1. 23: 13. 25: 36. 5: 50. 78: 102. 5-6: 106. 57-8; 114. 20: 121. 38-41; 133. 23: 183. 107: 186. 10; 192. 11; 239-18. Wife of the ocean; 17) Vā. 13. 35: 30. 32 and 92: 45. 95: Tripathagā; 18) Vā. 2. 7; 51. 21, 46; 58. 88. a consort of Śiva, served by Trayambaka and other gods. 19) Vā. 42. 39-40: 71. 5. Fit for śrāddha; 20) Vā. 77. 68. the right side of the Veda; 21) Vā. 98. 117: 99. 63: 104. 13, 27, 77: 106. 67: 111. 16. particularly sacred at three spots--Gangādvāra, Prayāga and Gangā sāgara-sangama. 22) M. 106. 53. 

गंगा
Gaṃgā  (II)--(personified) a bearer of flywhisk to Lalitā. Br. IV. 39. 74. Gangādvāra--a place sacred to Pitṛs. Bhā. VI. 2. 39: M. 22. 10: 246. 92.

गंगेश्वरम्
Gaṃgeśvaram --a tīrtham on the Narmadā. M. 193. 14-20.

गज
Gaja  (I)--the name of an asura. Bhā. XI. 12. 6.

गज
Gaja  (II)--a pupil of Rathītara. Br. II. 35. 4.

गज
Gaja  (III)--a son of Uttama Manu. Br. II. 36. 39.

गजा
Gajā  (IV)--a chief Vānara. Br. III. 7. 241.

गज
Gaja  (V)--a son of Mṛga (Nāga). Br. III. 7. 332.

गजकर्ण
Gajakarṇa --city of, in atalam. 1) Br. II. 20. 32. IV tala or Gabhastalam. 2) Vā. 50. 31.

