Gopucchabhrāmaṇam --waving of cow's tail over children to remove fear from their minds, an ancient Yādava practice. Vi. V. 5. 12.

गोभानु
Gobhānu  (I)--a son of Vanhi, and father of Trisānu. Br. III. 74. 1; Vā. 99. 1.

गोभानु
Gobhānu  (II)--a son of Garbha. M. 48. 1.

गोभिल
Gobhila  (I)--a Pravara sage. M. 199. 16. 

गोभिल
Gobhila  (II)--a ṛtvik at the yajña of Brahmā. Vā. 106. 37.

गोम
Goma(t)  (I)--a son of Śambhu. Br. III. 5. 40; Vā. 67. 81.

गोमत्
Gomat  (II)--a Mauneya Gandharva. Br. III. 7. 2.

गोमति
Gomati  (I)--a R. in Bhāratavarṣa from the Himalayas visited by Balarāma; in the Naiṣameya region. Bhā. V. 19. 18; X. 79. 11; Br. I. 2. 9; II. 16. 26. M. 114. 22; 163. 63. Vā. 2. 9; 45. 95; Vi. III. 14. 18.

