Gomatī  (II)--the capital of Divodāsa when Kāśī was destroyed by Kṣemaka. Br. III. 67. 29; Vā. 92. 26.

गोमती
Gomatī  (III)--a goddess enshrined at Gomanta. M. 13. 28.

गोमती
Gomatī  (IV)--a tīrtham sacred to Pitṛs; the birth-place of Yajñavarāha. M. 22. 13 and 31.

गोमतीपुत्र
Gomatīputra  (I)--(Gomatin-Br. P.) a king; son of Arindama and father of Pūrīṃat. Bhā. XII. 1. 26.

गोमतीपुत्र
Gomatīputra  (II)--a son of Śivasvāti and father of Alimat. Vi. IV. 24. 47.

गोमन्त
Gomanta --the hill fortress far south of Mathurā. Kṛṣṇa and Rāma went on a visit to it. At its foot lay Karavīrapura. Its crest was Pravarṣaṇa. Besieged by Jarāsandha  on all four sides, Rāma and Kṛṣṇa ascended it and leapt off the hill into the plain to gain Dvārakā unknown to the enemy. 1) Bhā. X. [52 (v) 16], [28 and 32]; [53 (v) 1-5]; 52. 11. [1 and 4], 12-13. Sacred to Gomatī. 2) M. 13. 28.

गोमय
Gomaya --cowdung as disinfectant. Br. III. 7. 431; 13. 130.

गोमयान
Gomayānas --Kaśyapa gotrakaras. M. 199. 4.

गोमुख
Gomukha  (I)--city of, in Sutalam. Br. II. 20. 22.

गोमुख
Gomukha  (II)--second Tala; Asura in. Vā. 50. 21.

गोमुख
Gomukha  (III)--a son of Śambhu. Vā. 67. 87.

गोमुख
Gomukha  (IV)--a pupil of Vedamitra--Śākalya. Vi. III. 4. 22.

गोमुखी
Gomukhī --a Svara śakti. Br. IV. 44. 56.

गोमेद
Gomeda(ka) --Mt. one of the seven hills of Plakṣadvīpa; gives its name to Gomedavarṣa. Br. II. 19. 7, 138; M. 123. 28; Vā. 49. 6; Vi. II. 4. 7.

गोमेदगन्धिक
Gomedagandhika --a pravara of Angiras. M. 196. 16. 

गोमेदम्
Gomedam --another name for the country Śāntabhayam in the Plakṣadvīpa; 1) Br. II. 19. 15. surrounding the sea of wine and surrounded by sugar-cane juice sea; 2) M. 123. 1-4; 124. 50. encircles the Kumuda hill. 3) Ib. 123. 7.

