Gomedavarṣa --in Plakṣadvīpa; see Gomedam. Br. II. 19. 7.

गोयज्ञम्
Goyajñam --the cult of cattle appropriate to the profession of a pastoral tribe; 1) Vi. V. 10. 36, 37-8. circumambulating of cows and bulls. 2) Ib. V. 10. 46.

