Gorakṣyam --introduced by Pṛthu. Vi. I. 13. 84.

गोरथ
Gorathas --sages. M. 200. 10.

गोलक
Golaka --a disciple of Śākalya. Vā. 60. 64.

गोलांगूल
Golāṃgūla --a Vānara chief. Br. III. 7. 244.

गोलांगूलस्
Golāṃgūlas --born of Pulaha--a Vānara tribe. Br. III. 7. 175.

गोलोक
Goloka --the residence of Surabhi; 1) Bhā. X. 27. 1; Br. III. 32. 40; 41. 55; 42. 19; 43. 29; IV. 1. 156; Vā. 100. 159; 104. 53-55. bathers in Soma tīrtham and givers of presents of a cow with calf go to this region. 2) M. 191. 99; 205. 8. 

गोलोकनाथ
Golokanātha --surname of Kṛṣṇa. Br. III. 33. 22.

गोवर्धन
Govardhana  (I)--Mt. a hill in Bhāratavarṣa, near Brindāvan, 1) Bhā. V. 19. 16; X. 11. 36; 13. 29. held by Kṛṣṇa for a week warding off rain; 2) X. 25. 19; 27. 1; Vi. V. 11. 16-25; 12. 1; 13. 1 and 4, 28; 15. 1. sacred to Bharadvāja who brought down heavenly trees and plants on behalf of Rāma; 3) M. 114. 38. worship of, with prayers and viands; sacrifice of goats to. 4) Vi. V. 10. 8, 38.

गोवर्धन
Govardhana  (II)--a city founded on the Godāvarī by Rāma; 1) Br. II. 16. 44. a tīrtham sacred to Pitṛs; 2) M. 22-52. established by Indra for Rāma's sake; Bharadvāja took his birth at. 3) Vā. 45. 113.

गोविन्द
Govinda  (I)--the name given to Kṛṣṇa by Indra the lord of Gokula; 1) Bhā. X. 27. 23, 28; Br. III. 33. 8. the Yādava king; went in search of maṇi by tracing the steps of Prasenajit when he was supposed to have killed him for the sake of the jewel, and came upon a place where Prasena and his horses were dead; proceeding he saw a dead lion and further a cave of a bear in the Vindhyas and heard the talk of a muse fondling the son of the bear; overhearing he heard: “dont cry„ Syamantaka is yours”. Then he entered the mouth of the cave and saw Jāmbavān, the king of bears; had hand-to-hand fight for 21 days; the followers of Kṛṣṇa returned to Dvāravatī and spread the news that Kṛṣṇa was dead; defeating the bear he got the hand of his daughter Jāmbavatī with the maṇi and returned home; gave it to Śakrajit in an assembly. 2) Vā. 96. 32-50.

गोविन्द
Govinda  (II)--an epithet of Viṣṇu. Vi. I. 4. 43; 14. 15; 19. 37; V. 5. 18; 12. 12; 13. 23; 16. 3; 18. 1; 20. 11; 23. 12; 29. 20; 30. 55; 31. 17; 33. 24; 37. 66; 38. 46; VI. 8. 36. 

गोविन्द
Govinda  (III)--a hill of the Krauñcadvīpa. M. 122. 80.

गोवीथि
Govīthi --the residence of the constellations--hastam, citra, svāti; one in the Madhya mārga. Br. III. 3. 50; M. 124. 57; Vā. 66. 49.

गोवृष
Govṛṣa --the overlord of humped animals (quadrupeds). Br. III. 8. 11; Vā. 70. 10.

गोवृषांक
Govṛṣāṃka --the Bull, the riding animal of Śiva. Vā. 54. 45; 101. 237, 246.

गोष्ठ
Goṣṭha --not a place for committing nuisance; 1) Vi. III. 11. 122. the residential quarters of cowherds; 2) Ib. V. 10. 49; 11. 14; 14. 1. of Kāśi's king. 3) Ib. V. 34. 42.

गोष्ठायन
Goṣṭhāyana --a Bhārgava gotrakara. M. 195. 24.

गोसव
Gosava --a sacrifice performed by Nanda at the suggestion of Kṛṣṇa; one produced by Brahmā. Bhā. III. 2. 32; 12. 40.

गोसवम्
Gosavam --the seventh Gāndhāra grāmikā. Vā. 86. 43.

गोसहस्रम्
Gosahasram --a gift of cows, a thousand in number properly adorned with bronze milking vessels and a bull in the midst, leads one to Śiva's abode. M. 274. 7; 278. 1-29.

गौ
Gau  (I)--the mind-born daughter of Pitṛs and wife of Śukra. Br. III. 1. 77; M. 15. 15; Vā. 73. 36. 

गौ
Gau  (II)--technical name of the Earth first milked by Pṛthu, and then by others to get the essence each wanted. M. 10. 2-28.

गौ
Gau  (III)--another name for Kṛtvī, a daughter of Śuka. M. 15. 10.

गौडदेश
Gauḍadeśa --noted for Śrāvasti. M. 12. 30.

गौडिनी
Gauḍinī --an Ekārṣeya sage. M. 200. 5.

गौतम
Gautama  (I)--came to see Bhiṣma in his death-bed and called on Parīkṣit engaged in Prāyopaveśa. Bhā. I. 9. 7; 10. 9; 19. 10.

गौतम
Gautama  (II)--a siddha; his wife was Ahalyā and son Śatānanda (Gotama-Br. P.); cursed Indra. Bhā. IX. 21. 34; Br. II. 27. 23.

गौतम
Gautama  (III)--a sage of the Vaivasvata epoch; present at Ambarīṣa's aśvamedha. Bhā. VIII. 13. 5; IX. 4. 22; M. 9. 27.

