Gautama  (IV)--a name of Kṛpa--invited for Yudhiṣṭhira's rājasūya. Came to Syamantapañcaka to see Kṛṣṇa on the occasion of a solar eclipse. Bhā. X. 49. 2; 74. 7; 84. 3.

गौतम
Gautama  (V)--the sage who presides over the month tapas. Bhā. XII. 11. 39; Br. II. 23. 12. Vi. 52. 12; 61. 44. 

गौतम
Gautama  (VI)--a son of Utathya; also known as Śaradvat; a pupil of Kṛta. Br. II. 35. 52; 38. 28.

गौतम
Gautama  (VII)--the 20th Vedavyāsa. Br. II. 35. 121; Vi. I. 9. 21; III. 1. 32; 3. 16.

गौतम
Gautama  (VIII)--officiated at Paraśurāma's sacrifice; 1) Br. III. 36. 5; 47. 48. āśrama near the town Jayanta; 2) Br. III. 64. 2; Vā. 59. 2. after him was named a forest region. 3) Vā. 23. 163.

गौतम
Gautama  (IX)--originally Dīrghatamas, became Gautama rid of the curse of Bṛhaspati by Surabhi's favour. Heard the Vāyu Purāṇa from Bharadvāja and narrated it to Nīryantra. Br. III. 74. 94. IV. 4. 63. Vā. 99. 92; 103. 63; 106. 38.

गौतम
Gautama  (X)--the avatār of the Lord in the 14th dvāpara of the family of Angiras in the Gautamavana with four sons at the end of the yuga. Vā. 23. 163.

गौतम
Gautama  (XI)--a son of Uśija and brother of Dīrghatamas, (s.v.) Praised Tripurāri. M. 48. 53; 126. 13; 133. 67.

गौतम
Gautama  (XII)--a mind-born son of Brahmā. M. 171. 27; 192. 10.

गौतम
Gautama  (XIII)--a son of Surūpā and a gotrakara. M. 196. 4-5.

गौतम
