Devaka  (I)--a Bhoja, and son of Āhuka (ĀhukāndhaVā. P.); brother of Ugrasena, hated by Kamsa. 1) Bhā. I. 14. 27; III. 1. 33; X. 36. 24 [31]
and 34; Br. III. 71. 129-30; M. 44. 71-2; Vi. IV. 14. 16-17. Devakī was one of his seven daughters, all of whom were married to Vasudeva. Father of four sons Devavān and others. 2) Bhā. IX. 24. 21-23; Vā. 96. 128-9; Vi. IV. 14. 18-19; V. 1. 5. Gave rich presents to his daughter Devakī when she was married. 3) Bhā. X. 1. 32.

