Nāgas  (I)--creatures born with human forms above the naval and of snakes below; born of Kaśyapa and Kadru; their capital was Bhogavatī; their chief was Ananta; 1) Bhā. I. 11. 11; II. 6. 13; III. 20. 48; XI. 16. 19; 24. 13; M. 261. 47-50. came to Dvārakā with the gods; 2) Bhā. XI. 6. 3; 12. 3; 14. 6. attacked the chariot of the Lord; 3) Ib. XII. 11. 48. residents of the Naiṣadha Hill, of all talams and especially Pātalam; capital Māhiṣmatī, renowned for Karkoṭaka sabhā; worship Pitṛs; 4) Br. II. 16. 9, 21; 17. 34; 20. 45; III. 69. 26; IV. 2. 26; 6. 72; 9. 72; Vi. II. 5. 4. Vāsuki, as their overlord; 5) M. 8. 7. when milking the cow-earth Takṣaka was the calf; 6) Ib. 10. 19-20. celebrated the marriage of Śiva and Umā; 7) Ib. 154. 462. to be worshipped in Palace buildings. 8) Ib. 266. 46; 268. 17; 273. 71.

