Nāgnajitī --(Satyā s.v.) a daughter of Nāgnajit; married by Kṛṣṇa in a svayamvara after curbing the seven bulls with noses unbored; had two sons, one of whom was Bhadravinda. Bhā. III. 3. 4; X. 58. 32; 61. 13; M. 47. 13, 19; Vi. V. 32. 3.

