Nābhi  (I)--the eldest of Agnīdhra and of the country, Himāhva; married Merudevī; performed a sacrifice for the birth of a son; the Lord appeared in the course of the sacrifice and promised to be born as his son; this was Ṛṣabha the eighth avatār of Viṣṇu 1) Bhā. I. 3. 13; II. 7. 10; V. 2. 19; 3. 1-2, 17-20; 4. 1-3; XI. 2. 15; Br. II. 14. 45, 59-60; Vā. 33. 38, 41, 50; Vi. II. 1. 16 and 18, 27. after he came of age, Nābhi had Ṛṣabha installed on the throne, and left with his queen for Viśālā for tapas and having propitiated Nārāyaṇa became a jīvanmukta. 2) Bhā. V. 4. 3-5. 

नाभि
Nābhi  (II)--a pupil of Kuśumi. Br. II. 35. 43.

