परशु
Paraśu  (III)--a son of Rukmiṇī and Kṛṣṇa. M. 47. 16.

परशुनाभ
Paraśunābha --a Rākṣasa. Vā. 69. 166.

परशुराम
Paraśurāma  (I)--a Siddha: the 16th avatār of Viṣṇu; a foe of the Haihayas; rid the world of the Kṣatriyas twenty one times; and made three pools of blood at Syamantapañcaka; 1) Bhā. I. 3. 20; II. 7. 22; VI. 15. 13; X. 40. 20; 82. 3; XI. 4. 21. defeated by Rama 2) Ib. IX. 10. 7; chh. 15 and 16 (whole). spoke highly of the valour of Bhīṣma, 3) Ib. IX. 22. 20. while in tapas was met by Kṛṣṇa and Balarāma on their way to Gomanta; he asked them to kill the king of Karavīrapura at its foot and thus clear the way uphill; 4) Ib. X. [52 (V) 18-30]. was met by Balarāma; 5) Ib. X. 79-12; Vi. IV. 4. 94. son of Jamadagni with an amsa of Nārāyana; a Bhargava; 6) Vā. 94. 38; Vā. IV. 7. 36. killed Kārtavīrya Arjuna. 7) Vi. IV. 11. 20.

परशुराम
Paraśurāma  (II)--a Purohita of Kṛṣṇa in his Yajñas at Kurukṣetra. Bhā. X. 90. 46[2].

