Parā  (IV)--the fourth stage of Kāmākṣī, of four arms with Pāśa, Aṅkuśa, Ikṣukodaṇḍa, and Pañcabāṇa, in this form Lalitā got established at Kāñci. Br. IV. 39. 13; 44. 141.

परा
Parā  (V)--a R. rising from the Ṛkṣa hill of the Bhāratavarṣa. Vā. 45. 98.

