परार्धम्
Parārdham --measurement of ten antas, (Vedic): two Parārdhams constitute Brahmā's life (first Prajāpati); 1) Vā. 100. 240. Vi. I. 3. 5. The present Varāhakalpa is the second Parārdha; 2) Ib. I. 3. 27-8; VI. 3. 4. of Brahmā; 3) Br. I. 4-31. a crore of 1000 crores. 4) Vā. 101. 92, 99.

परावसु
Parāvasu  (I)--the Gandharva who sang the glory of Indra for defeating Namuci: with the śarat sun. Bhā. VIII. 11. 41; Br. II. 23. 13; Vā. 79. 13.

परावसु
Parāvasu  (II)--an asura who entered the ocean. M. 61. 4.

परावह
Parāvaha --one of the seven Maruts. M. 163. 32.

पराशक्ति
Parāśakti --is Māyā; 1) Vā. 104. 33. worship of, to get rid of Raurava hell and of other sins. 2) Br. IV. 7-75; 8. 57-8; 10. 90; 12. 41-66; 14. 22; 15. 46.

पराशर
Parāśara  (I)--the son of Śakti and Adṛśyantī; wife Kālyā (Satyavatī, Acchoda Matsya Gandhi) and son Kṛṣṇadvaipāyana; 1) Bhā. I. 3. 21; 4. 14; VI. 15. (14); IX. 22. 21; XII. 6. 49, 55; Br. I. 1. 9; 2. 12; III. 8. 91; M. 14. 15; 47. 246; 201. 31; Vā. 70. 83. a Ṛṣika became sage by satya; 2) Br. II. 32. 102. a pupil of Yājñavalkya; 3) Ib. II. 35. 29; Vā. 77. 74; Vi. III. 4. 18. of Bāṣkala, a Vāsiṣṭha; 4) Br. II. 32. 115. a Śrutaṛṣi; 5) Ib. II. 33. 3; M. 145. 96, 109. a Vedavyāsa 6) Br. II. 35. 124; Vā. 23. 212. of the 26th dvāpara; heard the Br. Purāṇa (Vāyu P.) from Śakti when in embryo and narrated it to Jātu-karṇi; 7) Br. IV. 4. 65-6; Vā. 61. 47; 103. 65; 106. 35. praised Śiva, out to destroy Tripura; 8) M. 133. 67. invited for the Rājasūya of Yudhiṣṭhira, 9) Bhā. X. 74. 8. came to see Parīkṣit preaching prāyopavesa; 10) Ib. I. 19. 9; Vā. 1. 138; 2. 12. questioned by Maitreya on the origin of the world etc: narrated the Bhāgavata to the sage; 11) Bhā. III. 8. 8; Vi. I. 1. 1-10. recollected Vasiṣṭha's narration to him of his father's death at the hands of a Rākṣasa set up by Viśvāmitra: his anger and the sacrifice he performed for the extinction of the Rākṣasas; 12) Ib. I. 1. 11-14. The advice of Vasiṣṭha, his grand-father, to abate his anger  because fate must run its course and anger was unworthy of the wise: his compliance; 13) Ib. I. 1. 15-21. the arrival of Pulastya the son of Brahmā, who granted P. boons comprising knowledge of the sāstras, authorship of Viṣṇu Purāṇa and correct knowledge of the truth about Gods and Karma: the conformation of the boons by Vasiṣṭha: states that the Universe is born of Viṣṇu, depends on him and is Sahiṣṇu avatār of the Lord; 14) Vā. 23. 212; Vi. I. 1. 22-31. praise of Hari having realised the Yoga power of Hari. 15) Bhā. II. 7. 45; Vi. II. 2. 7.

पराशर
Parāśara  (II)--the son and pupil of Kuśumi. Br. II. 35. 42.

पराशर
Parāśara  (III)--a son of Ṛṣabha avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 144.

पराशर
Parāśara  (IV)--a Mantra-brāhmaṇa-kāraka and resident of Brahmakṣetra. Vā. 59. 105.

पराश्रुति
Parāśruti --the great Vedic dictum. Vā. 18. 3.

