Parivatsara  (I)--the sun god; 1) Br. II. 21. 131; IV. 32. 15; Vā. 31. 38; 56. 20. lord among the varṣas. 2) M. 141. 18; 167. 52.

परिवत्सर
Parivatsara  (II)--the second year of the five year yuga, 1) Vā. 31. 27; 50. 183; Br. II. 13. 114, 117, 126-7; Vi. II. 8. 72. yuga of five years: Samvatsara, Parivatsara, Idvatsara, Anuvatsara, and Vatsara; 2) Bhā. III. 11. 14; V. 22. 7; M. 141. 18-19. Agni, Surya, Soma, Vāyu and Rudra respectively of the five years.

परिवह
Parivaha  (I)--a variety of wind controlling the Parjanya clouds. Vā. 51. 45.

परिवह
Parivaha  (II)--the sixth of the seven Maruts helping, the Parjanya and Diggajas to rain dew; 1) Br. II. 22. 50; M. 163. 33; Vā. 67-120. the chief of the seventh Vātaskandha situated between the planets and Druva. 2) Br. III. 5. 89; Vā. 67. 120. 

परिवाय
Parivāya --a Janapada of the Bhadra country. Vā. 43. 20.

