Parivṛttā --a daughter of Ṛṣā brought forth oyster, conch, aiṇeya, śambūka and different kinds of poison like Kālakūṭa. Br. III. 7. 414, 419-20; Vā. 69. 291, 296.

परिवेष
Pariveṣa --the circle round the sun and moon indicates danger to the Kingdom. M. 233. 8.

