Parjanya  (II)--An Āditya and Lokapāla; the name of the sun in the month of Tapasya (Phālguna): father of Hiraṇyaroma. Bhā. XII. 11. 40; Br. II. 21. 157; 23. 12; 30. 40; III. 3. 68; 8. 20; Vā. 50. 206; 66. 66; Vi. II. 10. 12.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (III)--one of the important clouds raining dew for the growth of corns; 1) Br. II. 22. 49. overlords of seas, rivers, clouds, rains besides Āditya; 2) Ib. III. 8. 14; Vā. 70. 13. they are under the control of wind, Parivaha; they also carry the heavenly Gangā. 3) Ib. 51. 43-6. 

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (IV)--a Parivaha and sage of the Raivata epoch; 1) Br. II. 36. 62; M. 9. 19; Vi. III. 1. 22. attained heaven by tapas. 2) M. 143. 39.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (V)--same as Hiranyaroma. M. 124. 95.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (IV)--a son of Agni and Samhūti; 1) Vā. 28. 16. his wife Mānu and son Hiraṇyaroma. 2) Br. II. 11. 19.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (VII)--a deity with the sun in the śarat season. Vā. 52. 12.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (VIII)--a Rājaṛṣi. Vā. 57. 122.

पर्जन्य
Parjanya  (IX)--a Mauneya. Vā. 69. 3.

