Parṇacira --leaves as dress of mountain residents. Vi. IV. 24. 96.

पर्णमाल
Parṇamāla --a Mt. in the Sālmalidvīpa: one of the haunts of the Garuḍa family. Br. III. 7. 453.

पर्णवि
Parṇavi --a Trayārṣeya Pravara. M. 197. 6.

पर्णाश
Parṇāśa --a R. from Ṛṣyavān; 1) M. 114. 23. got transformed into a girl and became the wife of Devavṛddha. 2) Br. III. 71. 7, 12. 

पर्णिनी
Parṇinī --an apsaras coupled with Puñjikasthalā. Br. III. 7. 14; Vā. 69. 4, 49.

पर्यङ्क
Paryaṅka --1000 hooded serpent shedding golden lustre as bed of the Lord. Vā. 24. 11, 17.

