Parvata  (II)--a son of Kaśyapa; brother of Nārada and a devaṛṣi; 1) Br. II. 19. 9; Vā. 61. 85; 70. 79. a sage born in Nārada hill in Plakṣa. 2) Br. II. 35. 95; III. 7. 27; 8. 86; Vā. 30. 86; 49. 8.

