Parvaśa --a son of Pūrṇamāsa and Sarasvatī; the lord of all gaṇas; his wife, Parvaśā; had Puṇyā and Sumatī as daughters-in-law; 1) Vā. 28. 10-12, 33. father of Yajurdhāma and Stambha Kāśyapa. 2) Br. II. 11. 13.

पर्वशा
Parvaśā --the wife of Parvaśa; 1) Br. II. 11. 15. mother of Yajurdhāma and Stambha Kāśyapa. Br. II. 11. 15. Vā. 28. 13.

पर्वसन्धि
Parvasandhi --the last day of the Kṛṣṇa and Sukla Pakṣas; 1) M. 141. 28, 32. fit for the rituals of agniādhāna. 2) Vā. 56. 34. 

पलम्
Palam --a measurement: thirteen palas make one Māgadha measure, (jalaprastha-Vā. P.): [N.B. 40 palas make at present one Madras measure.]
Br. IV. 1. 217; Vā. 100. 219; Vi. VI. 3. 8.

पललक
Palalaka --a son of Hālāhala and father of Pulindasena; a King. Vi. IV. 24. 47.

पलाण्डु
Palāṇḍu --a Śrutaṛṣi. Br. II. 33. 6.

पलाशा
Palāśā --a R. of the Ketumālā country. Vā. 44. 18.

पलाशिनी
Palāśinī --a R. of the Śuktimat. Br. II. 16. 38; Vā. 45. 107.

पल्लव
Pallavas --a southern tribe. M. 114. 40; Br. II. 16. 47.

पल्हव
Palhavas (Pahlavas)  1) Vā. 88, 122; 136; 45. 118; 58. 82, 93, 107.--defeated by Sagara; allowed to escape with moustaches. 2) Br. III. 48. 26, 19, 44.

पवन
Pavana  (I)--a Mt. on the west of Meru Bhā. V. 16. 27.

पवन
Pavana  (II)--a name of Vāyu; 1) Bhā. VI. 3. 14; Vi. V. 21. 16. in Indraś host, with Ankuśa for his weapon. 2) M. 148. 83. 

पवन
Pavana  (III)--a son of Uttama Manu. Bhā. VIII. 1. 23.

पवन
Pavana  (IV)--a son of Vasiṣṭha and Ūrjā. Br. II. 11. 41.

पवन
Pavana  (V)--the Pārthiva Agni. Br. II. 24. 10.

पवनपुरम्
Pavanapuram --description of; here are Dvādaśārkas Vālukeśvara, eleven Rudras, Hanumān and four Kuṇḍas; a tīrtha; bath in which rids one of Brahmahatti doṣa. Vā. 59. 110.-30; 60. 68.

पवनम्
Pavanam vratam --the performer of it becomes a Rāja. M. 101. 78.

पवना
Pavanās --a tribe. Br. III. 73. 108.

