Bāṣkali  (II)--an Angirasa and a Mantrakṛt; a Śrutaṛṣi; a pupil of Paiḷa in charge of the Ṛg Veda; he arranged it into four Samhitās; his disciples were Bodhya, Agnimāṭhara, Parāśara and Yājñavalkya. Br. II. 32. 107; 33. 4, 13; 34. 25; M. 196. 12; Vā. 59. 98; 60. 25-26; 61. 2.

