Bāhyatodaras --a Northern tribe. Vā. 45. 118.

बाह्य
Bāhyas --snow-making rays of the sun. Vā. 53. 21.

बाह्या
Bāhyā --a R. from the Sahya Mountains. Br. II. 16. 35.

बाह्लीक
Bāhlīka  (I)--a son of Pratipa and father of Somadatta; 1) Bhā. IX. 22. 12 and 18; 49. 2; Vā. 99. 234; Vi. IV. 20. 9; V. 35. 12, 27, 30. father of seven sons, kings of Bāhli Kingdom; 2) M. 50. 39. the  foremost among the Kurus; 3) Bhā. X. 52. 11 [9]. was stationed by Jarāsandha at the southern gate of Mathurā; 4) Ib. X. 50. 11 [4]. placed on the south during the siege of Gomanta; 5) Ib. X. 52. 11 [9]. informed by Uddhava of Rāma's visit to Hastināpura; 6) Ib. X. 68. 17. his sons took active part in Yudhiṣṭhira's Rājasūya and in Duryodana's army; 7) Ib. X. 75. 6; [95 (v) 16]. could not vanquish Arjuna, supported by Kṛṣṇa; 8) Ib. I 15. 16. went with his sons to Syamantapañcaka for the solar eclipse where he met the Vṛṣṇis; left Syamantapañcaka; 9) Ib. X. 82. 26; 84. 69. [1]. sisters, Rohiṇī and Pauravī, married to Vasudeva. 10) Br. III. 71. 163.

बाह्लीक
Bāhlīka  (II)--(c) a Northern Kingdom; 1) Br. II. 16. 46; 18. 46. after the son of Bāhlīka. 2) M. 50. 39; 114. 40; 163. 72.

बाह्लीक
Bāhlīkas  (I)--a name given to the thirteen sons of the Kings of Kilikilā; 1) Bhā. XII. 1. 34. took part in the Rājasūya of Yudhiṣṭhira; 2) Ib. X. 75. 6. three of the thirteen sons were of the Nandana family; Ekalas or lords of small regions. 3) Vi. IV. 24. 57. 58.

बाह्लीक
