Bindumatī  (II)--a daughter of Śaśabindu (ŚatabinduVī. P.) and queen of Māmdhātā also known as Caitrarathi (s.v.) and mother of three sons, Mucukunda, Ambarīṣa and Purukutśa. Bhā. IX. 6. 38; Vi. IV. 2. 66; Vā. 88. 70-2. 

