Bilvam --a place to be attained by pure jñānam. Vi. I. 6. 13.

बिल्वल
Bilvala --a place sacred to the Goddess Bilvapatrikā. M. 13. 31.

बिल्वस्थली
Bilvasthalī --a place between the hills Samūla and Vasudhāra; inhabited by Siddhas, Nāgas, Brahmanas, etc. Vā. 38. 23-6.

बिल्वा
Bilvā --a Goddess following Bhavamālinī. M. 179. 71.

बिल्वि
Bilvi --a Bhārgava and a Pañcārṣeya. M. 195. 33.

बीज
Bīja --from Īśvara and Yoni; from Prakṛti; from Nārāyaṇa. Vā. 101. 228.

बीजकर्षणिका
Bījakarṣaṇikā --a gupta Śakti. Br. IV. 19. 20; 36. 71.

बीजभावा
Bījabhāvā --a follower of Māyā. M. 179. 69.

