बीभत्सु
Bībhatsu --Arjuna (s.v.). Bhā. X. [67 (v) 36]. 

बुध
Budha  (I)--the son of Veghavān and father of Tṛṇabindhu. Br. III. 8. 36; 61. 10; Vi. IV. 1. 45-6; Vā. 86. 15.

बुध
Budha  (II)--a Vānara chieftain, and a son of Śveta. Br. III. 7. 180.

बुध
Budha  (III)--one of the twenty Sutapa Gods. Br. IV. 1. 15; Vā. 100. 15.

बुध
Budha  (IV)--one of the nine planets; son of Soma (moon) [Tviṣi (Vā. P.)]
and Tārā wife of Bṛhaspati; known as Rājaputra; of brown colour; has a lustrous white chariot drawn by ten horses of different colours; originator of the Hastiśāstra; and learned in the Arthaśāstra; got the kingdom on the earth; 1) M. 24. 3-10; 93. 10, 17; 115. 1; 127. 1-3; Vā. 52. 72; Vi. I. 8. 11; IV. 6. 32-34. occupies a position above (below Vi. P.) that of Śukra; generally good and benevolent; but when separated from the sun preceding him, he causes showers or draughts; 2) Bhā. V. 22. 13; M. 264. 8; Vi. II. 7. 8. enamoured of the figure of Ilā (Ilā converted into the other sex at Śaravaṇa); in the guise of a Brahmana, he approached her; she consented to be his wife on his saying that he was Budha; father of Pururavas; Rajaputraka Aila; 3) Bhā IX. 1. 34-5; 14. 14-15; Br. II. 24. 49-134; III. 3. 23; 65. 44; 66. 1; M. 11. 54; 12. 14. in the chariot of Tripura; 4) Ib. 128. 48, 65; 133. 20. at the bottom of all Tārāgrahas; 5) Vā. 101. 132. with the Prakṛti of Nārāyaṇa; in extent three-fourths of Kuja and Saura; has eight rays; lies above the nakṣatras; 6) Ib. 53. 31, 67, 87 and 97. above 200,000 yojanas from the constellar regions; 7) Vi. II. 7. 7. chariot of, made of wind and fire and drawn by eight horses; 8) Ib. II. 12. 18. Sudhyumna, son of Manu, cursed by Śiva, became a woman on whom Budha begot Pururavas. 9) Ib. IV. 1. 11-12; Vā. 85. 17. 

बुध
Budha  (V)--a son of Mahādeva and Rohiṇī. Vā. 27. 56; 66. 22.

