Buddha  (I)--the 20th avatār of Viṣṇu after the advent of Kali; born of Ajana (Añjana-Bhā. P.) in the land of Kīkaṭas; 1) Bhā. I. 3. 24; VI. 8. 19. Hari addressed as; 2) Ib. X. 40. 22. according to M. P. the 9th incarnation. 3) M. 47. 247; 54. 19; 285. 7.

बुद्ध
Buddha  (II)--a son of Bautya Manu. Br. IV. 1. 114.

बुद्ध
Buddha  (III)--one of the names of Śiva. Vā. 30. 216; 54. 71; 97. 172; Br. III. 72. 177.

बुद्धावस्था
Buddhāvasthā --the condition of dhyāna. Vā. 101. 85.

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (I)--a daughter of Dakṣa and a wife of Dharma; gave birth to Artha; 1) Bhā. IV. 1. 50-51. Br. II. 9. 50 and 60; Vā. 10. 25. mother of Budha (BodhaVi. P.) and Apramāda. 2) Ib. 10. 36; Vi. I. 7. 23 and 30.

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (II)--a Tuṣita god. Br. III. 3. 19; Vā. 66. 18.

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (III)--a son of Śatarūpā. M. 4. 25. 

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (IV)--a deity, attendant on Vināyaka. M. 260. 55.

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (V)--is four-fold; jñānam, vairāgyam, aiśvaryam and dharma. Vā. 4. 34; 59. 74.

बुद्धि
Buddhi  (VI)--a term for mahat. Vā. 102. 21.

बुद्धिसंकीर्ण
Buddhisaṃkīrṇa --a maṇṭapa with 54 pillars. M. 270. 3 and 9.

बुद्धीन्द्रिय
Buddhīndriyas --the ear, the skin, the eyes, the tongue and the nose; to attain knowledge. Vā. 4. 60, 62.

बुद्बुदा
Budbudā --a R. from the Himālayas. Br. II. 16. 26.

बृन्दावनम्
Bṛndāvanam --the Gopas left Bṛhadvana and settled here as it was quite suitable for their cattle; nearby was Govardhana as also the Yamunā; 1) Bhā. X. 11. 28, 36. Agha's form as a boaconstrictor mistaken for the landscape of Bṛndāvana by the cowherd boys; his skin used as an artificial cavern by the cowherds; 2) Ib. X. 12. 18-23. 36; 13. 59. made holy by Kṛṣṇa's rambles; 3) Ib. X. 15. 1. a description of; here summer presented the appearance of the spring season; description of winter and spring at the place; 4) Ib. X. 15. 5-8; 18. 2-8; 20 (whole). music of the Lord at; Gopis met Kṛṣṇa at the place and enjoyed his presence; 5) Ib. X. 21 5 and 10. Gopis searched for Kṛṣṇa at. 6) Ib. X. 30. 23; 47. 43. 

