Muni  (II)--a son of Dyutimān, after whom came the Maunideśam in Krauncadvīpa. Br. II. 14. 23, 26; Vā. 33. 21, 23. Vi. II. 4. 48.

मुनि
Muni  (III)--a god of Prasūta group. Br. II. 36. 71.

मुनि
Muni  (IV)--a son of Vaidya. Br. III. 59. 7. Vā. 84. 7.

मुनि
Muni  (V)--a son of Pradyumna and father of Ūrjavaha. Br. III. 64. 20; Vā. 89. 19. 

मुनि
Muni  (VI)--one of the twenty Amitābha gods. Br. IV. 1. 17; Vā. 100. 17.

मुनि
Muni  (VII)--a sage of the Raivata epoch; 1) M. 9. 9. a Viśvedeva. 2) Ib. 203. 13; Br. III. 3. 30.

