Munis --those who delight in the Ātman, after many births, and renounce even the region of Brahmā; realise the Supreme Spirit by shaking off the three dreamy stages-bhāvādvaita, kriyādvaita, and dravyādvaita. Bhā. III. 27. 27; VII. 15. 62-5; X. 2. 25.

