Mura --an Asura of five heads; got up from sleep under waters on hearing the sound of Pāñcajanya (s.v): His head was cut off by Kṛṣṇa. His seven sons rose with Pīṭha, their commander, and were put to death by Garuḍa in charge of the outskirts of the city of Prāgjyotiṣa; father of 7000 sons. Bhā. X. 59. 6-19; 37. 16; III. 3. 11; IV. 26. 24; Vi. V. 29. 17-18.

