Muraripu (Murāri) --is Viṣṇu. Bhā. IV. 26. 24; X. 14. 58; Br. III. 36. 34; M. 54. 19 etc.

मुरासुर
Murāsura --an Asura in the disguise of Viṣṇu. Br. IV. 29. 125. 

मुर्धा
Murdhā --a son of Bhṛgu. Vā. 65. 87.

मुषिक
Muṣika (c) --a country under Kanakas (Wilson's suggested identification with the pirate coast of the Konkan). Vi. IV. 24. 67.

मुष्टिक
Muṣṭika --an Asura friend (wrestler-Vi. P.) of Kamsa. Invited by Kamsa, he got ready for a wrestling match with Kṛṣṇa and Balarāma. Took his seat in the enclosure; challenged by Rāma, fought according to rules, and courted death. (Balabhadra,-Vi. P.) Bhā. X. 2. 1; 36. 21-24; 37. 15; 42. 37; 43. 40; 44. 1, 19, and 24-25; Br. IV. 29. 123. Vi. V. 15. 7 and 16; 20. 18, 65. 78.

