Mṛtyu  (II)--the sixth Vyāsa in the sixth dvāpara: avatār of the Lord Lokākṣi; father of Sunīthā, given to Anga; 1) Br. II. 35. 118; 36. 127; Vā. 23. 133; Vi. III. 3. 12. Heard the Purāṇa from the Sun god and narrated it to Indra. 2) Br. IV. 4. 60; Vi. I. 13. 11; Vā. 103. 60. 

