Meghavāhana --the twenty-second kalpa where Viṣṇu became Meghī. Vā. 21. 50.

मेघशैल
Meghaśaila --a Mt. north of the Mahābhadra. Vā. 36. 32.

मेघस्वाति
Meghasvāti  (I)--a son of Cibilaka (Vikala Br. P., Pikala, Vi. P.), and father of Aṭamāna (Paṭuman Vi. P.). Bhā. XII. 1. 24; Vi. IV. 24. 45.

मेघस्वाति
Meghasvāti  (II)--an Andhra King a son of Āpītaka; ruled for 18 years. M. 273. 5.

मेघा
Meghā --a R. of the Bhadrā country. Vā. 43. 26. 

मेघी
Meghī --the guise of Viṣṇu in the 22nd Kalpa, bore Kṛttivāsa for a thousand divine years; on account of the heavy weight breathed hard when Kāla came from the mouth. Vā. 21. 50.

मेढ्या
Meḍhyā --compared to Dhruva among the luminaries. Bhā. IV. 12. 39.

