Laukikas --a class of Manuṣya Pitṛs, as distinguished from Deva Pitṛs; fed in monthly ceremonies; attain this status after duly performing the seven-fold karma; 1) Br. II. 28. 69-78. their path cannot be known even by tapas, much less seen with mortal eyes; how they benefit by śrāddha in a wide sense; how those who get no śrāddha suffer. 2) Vā. 56. 63-5, 68-79. Laukikamānam--kāṣṭha, nimeṣa, kalā, muhūrta, ahas, rātri, etc., one 100 Laukika years equal to 3 years of Pitṛs; one year (Laukikamānam) equals one day for Devas.-Uttarāyanam is the day time and Dakṣiṇāyanam the night of gods, 3030 years equal to one Saptaṛṣi vatsara. Br. II. 29. 5-17.

लौकिकाग्नि
Laukikāgni --the first son of Brahmā; 1) Vā. 29. 7. father of Brahmodanāgni, well-known as Bharata; also Atharvā. 2) Br. II. 12. 7, 9.

