Varṇāśrama --social polity; 1) M. 2. 23; Vā. 61. 97. truth, charity and selfcontrol are equal to tīrthas for homekeepers; 2) Br. II. 14. 41-2. M. 22. 80. Yayāti speaks of four Varṇas born of one body and their respective duties of whom the Brāhmaṇa is superior; 3) Ib. 30. 20. lost in a period of anarchy; 4) Ib. 47. 257. in the Śākadvīpa; 5) Ib. 122. 38. said by Manu; 6) Ib. 123. 23; 142. 42. restrictions get loosened in Dvāpara; 7) Ib. 142. 53; 143. 4; 144. 6 and 26. disappearance of, in Kali; 8) Ib. 144. 96; 215. 63; 273. 32 and 46. Vi. VI. 1. 10, 32-3. (see Varṇa dharma). In Tretā Kṣatriyas followed the Brāhmaṇas, the Vaiśyas the Kṣatriyas and the Śūdras the Vaiśyas; there was thus peace everywhere and everything bore fruit; 9) Vā. 30. 294; 49. 117; 57. 52. leads to enjoyment in heaven; 10) Ib. 59. 22 and 36; 99. 425; 101. 6. 137 and 174; 102, 70 and 96; 104. 21. no such system in Kṛtayuga. 11) Br. II. 7. 55.

