Varma Nārāyaṇātmakam --a Vaiṣṇavī vidyā, taught by Viśvarūpa to Indra. Here the various manifestations of Hari  including that of the Buddha are recalled. Once a certain Kauśikan practised this and gave up his life in a desert. When a Gandharva crossed the bones of this dead man, he fell down on the earth. Instructed by Vālakhilyas, he collected the bones, and after throwing them into the Sarasvatī, and bathing there, returned to his place. Taught originally to Tvaṣṭri by Dadhyanga; Tvaṣṭri taught it to Viśvarūpa. Bhā. VI. 8 (whole); 9. 53.

वर्मभृत्
Varmabhṛt --a son of Citraka. Br. III. 71. 115.

वर्य
Varya --the Rākṣasa presiding over the month of Nabha. Bhā. XII. 11. 37.

वर्ष
Varṣa  (I)--a god of Sutāra group. Br. IV. 1. 89.

वर्ष
Varṣa  (II)--the mind-born son of Brahmā in the 16th kalpa. Vā. 21. 35.

वर्ष
Varṣa  (III)--one of the ten branches of Supāra devas. Vā. 100. 94.

वर्षपर्वत
Varṣaparvatas --six in Jambūdvīpa; Himavān, Hemakūṭa, Nisadha, Meru, Nīla, and Śṛṅgavān; served by Siddhas and Cāraṇas; the inner viṣkambha is 9000. 1) M. 113. 10; Vā. 34. 13, 21. in Kuśadvīpa. 2) Ib. 49. 52-3. 

वर्षपर्वणि
Varṣaparvaṇi --see Śarmiṣṭhā. Vi. IV. 10. 4.

वर्षयन्ति
Varṣayanti --a queen of Varṣa ṛtu. Br. IV. 32. 29.

वर्षा
Varṣā --of the Dhruva Maṇḍala. Vā. 51. 11.

वर्षिन
Varṣina --heard the Vāyu Purāṇa from Antarikṣa. Vā. 103. 63.

वर्हय
Varhayas --one of the 14 Gaṇas of Apsarasas born of Kuśavatī. Br. III. 7. 19.

वलभीच्छन्दक
Valabhīcchandaka --the round arch of a temple where the images of Gaurī and Vināyaka are enshrined. M. 269. 35, 54-6.

वलित
Valita --a son of Parāvṛt. Vi. IV. 12. 11.

वलेय
Valeyas --a class of Gandharvas originating from Vikrānta; famous for valour and liberality; had three daughters, each an originator of a gaṇa. Vā. 69. 18. 20. 22.

वल्मीकजन्मन
Valmīkajanmana (Vālmīkī) --due to his curse Lakṣmī (wealth) is not stationary. Br. IV. 7. 19. 

वशवर्तिन्
Vaśavartins --a group of gods of the epoch of Uttama Manu, 12 in number; also Vamśavartins. Br. II. 36. 26-30; Vi. III. 1. 14.

वशित
Vaśita --a Siddhi devī. Br. IV. 19. 4; 44. 140.

वशित्वम्
Vaśitvam --one of the eight attributes of yoga; controls all creatures; whatever he desires results. Vā. 13. 4, 16.

वशिन्
Vaśin --a son of Kṛti; with him the Mithilā line came to an end. Bhā. IX. 13. 26-27.

वशिनि
Vaśini --a Rahasya Yogini devī. Br. IV. 19. 48; 37. 3.

वश्याश्व
Vaśyāśva --a Ṛṣika who became a sage by truth (satya). Br. II. 32. 102.

वषट्कार
Vaṣaṭkāra  (I)--is Śiva. Br. II. 26. 34; III. 1. 22.

वषट्कार
Vaṣaṭkāra  (II)--sacrifices (Vedic); neglect of, before Pṛthu's advent (see Vaṣaṭkriyā); 1) M. 10. 11. call to gods. 2) Vā. 65. 23.

वषट्कारा
Vaṣaṭkārā --a mind-born mother. M. 179. 20. 

वषट्क्रिया
Vaṣaṭkriyā --a Vedic rite; not observed in Vena's reign (see Vaṣaṭkāra). Br. II. 28. 42-53; 36. 130; M. 141. 47; Vā. 56. 48 and 52.

वस
Vasas --a tribe to be conquered by Kalki. Br. III. 73. 108.

वसकरिणि
Vasakariṇi (sarvādyā) --a Mudrā Devī. Br. IV. 44. 114.

वसती
Vasatī --(c) a kingdom of the west, watered by the Sindhu. Br. II. 18. 48.

वसन्त
Vasanta  (I)--(personified) a friend of Manmatha. Br. IV. 30. 68; 32. 21-58.

वसन्त
Vasanta  (II)--a mind-born son of Brahmā in the 16th kalpa. Vā. 21. 35.

वसन्त
Vasanta  (III)--the spring season of Citra and Vaikāśi; the Saptakas who reside in the sun are Dhāta and Aryamā, Pulastya and Pulaha, Vāsuki and Samkīrṇāra snakes, Tumburu and Nārada Gandharvas, Kratastāli and Puñjikasthala Apsarasas, Rathakṛchra and Ūrja Grāmaṇis, Heti and Praheti Rākṣasas. Vā. 50. 177 and 193; 52. 6; 53. 25.

वसन्तमास
Vasantamāsa --tṛtīya of the bright half recommended for commencing Saubhāgyaśayanam; then Satī married Śiva. M. 60. 14-15. 

वसिन
Vasina  (I)--(Vāsiṣṭha) a sage of the Rohita epoch. Br. IV. 1. 63.

वसिन
Vasina  (II)--(known also as Cyavana) a son of Bhṛgu and Paulomi. Vā. 65. 88.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (I)--a sage who called on Bhīṣma lying on his death-bed; also called on Parikṣit practising prāyopaveśa; 1) Bhā. I. 9. 7; 19. 9. was invited for Yudhiṣṭhira's Rājasūya; 2) Ib. X. 74. 7. came to see Kṛṣṇa at Syamantapañcaka; 3) Ib. X. 84. 4. one of the sages who left for Piṇḍāraka. 4) Ib. XI. 1. 12.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (II)--a son of Brahmā, born of his breath; married Kardama's daughter, Arundhatī. Father of seven sons, all Brahmaṛṣis; cursed the fires Pāvaka, Pavamāna and Śuci who were born sons of Vijitāśva; 1) Bhā. III. 12. 22-3; 24. 23; IV. 1. 40; 24. 4; 29. 43; Br. II. 32. 96 and 115; III. 8, 82; M. 187. 45. when invited to be Nimi's Ṛtvik, he went away to Indra's yajña to which he had been called earlier and asked Nimi to wait till his return. On Nimi continuing his sacrifice with the help of other Ṛtviks, Vasiṣṭha cursed him and was in turn cursed to be born of Ūrvaśī and Mitrāvaruṇa. 2) Bhā. VI. 18. 5; IX. 13. 1-6. A sage of the Kṛtayuga: Heard the Nīlakaṇṭha legend from Kārtikeya; present at Rati's marriage; 3) Br. II. 25. 15; 27. 103; IV. 40. 48; M. 201. 1, 14-6. suggested to Diti the observance of the Madanadvādaśīvratam. 4) M. 3. 7 and 34; 7. 5, 9.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (III)--a siddha; 1) Bhā. VI. 15. 13. the ācārya of Śrāddha deva. Finding no issue to him. Vasiṣṭha offered a sacrifice to Mitra and Varuṇa. At this time Śrāddhā,  the king's wife desired to have a daughter and expressed it to the Hotā who uttered the mantra in such a way as to get a daughter. Ilā was born; but Śrāddhadeva was not pleased. So Vasiṣṭha converted Ilā into a male by name Sudyumna; 2) Ib. IX. 1. 13-22, 36-7; M. 245. 86. was present at Ambarīṣa's asvamedha; 3) Bhā. IX. 4. 22. the ideal Purohīta. 4) Ib. XI. 16. 22.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (IV)--a sage of the Vaivasvata epoch; his sons Mānasa pitṛs; fought in the form of a bird for years a battle with Viśvāmitra concerning Hariścandra; acted as Sāmaga in his Puruṣamedha; 2) Bhā. IX. 7. and 23. cursed Saudāsa to become a Rākṣasa; with the king's assent, Vasiṣṭha begot Aśmaka on Madayantī. 3) Ib. IX. 9. 18-23, 38. ^1 Bhā. VIII. 13. 5; 1. 24; M. 9. 27; 12. 4-5; 15. 12; Vi. III. 1. 32.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (V)--the sage presiding over the months of Śuci (Āṣāḍha) and Śukra; 1) Bhā. XII. 11. 36; Br. II. 23. 6. in the Viśvacakra. 2) M. 285. 6.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (VI)--the eighth Veda Vyāsa. Heard the Brahmāṇḍa Purāṇa from Indra and narrated it to Sārasvata; 1) Br. II. 35. 118; IV. 2. 47; 4. 60. āśrama of, on the Ūrjjanta hill. 2) Ib. III. 13. 53 and 74.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (VII)--born in the Vāruṇi-yajña from the centre of Vasu (sacrificial fire), and hence Vasumat; progenitor of Pitṛs, Sukātas. Br. III. 1. 21 and 46; 10. 96; M. 195. 11; 200. 1.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (VIII)--cursed Haihaya to be ruined; of madhyama bhakti; 1) Br. III. 30. 70; 34. 40. a mahaṛṣi and a Brahmavādin. 2) M. 145. 90 and 109; 171. 27.  

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (IX)--a contemporary of Sagara; the kulaguru of the Ikṣvākus; narrated Paraśurāma's story to Sagara; blessed Sagara who enjoyed rule after world conquest; consoled him on the death of Sāgaras; agreed to anointing Amśumat as yuvarāja. 1) Br. III. 31. 1; 47. 99; 48. 29; 49. 1 and 38; 54. 20-22. Gave Prathiṣṭhāna to Sudyumna. 2) Ib. III. 60. 21. Took Ikṣvāku to task for getting hare's flesh already tasted by Vikukṣi; was in charge of the kingdom when Trayyāruṇi went to the forest; met Kalmāṣapāda's queen for Aśmaka's birth; 3) Ib. III. 63. 15, 82-93, 177; 64. 4; 73. 91. Purohita of Daśaratha and Rāma. 4) Ib. IV. 15. 40; 20. 103; 40. 48 and 89; M. 47. 245; Vi. IV. 4. 99. Observed Ādityaśayanavratam. 5) M. 55. 32.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (X)--another name for Āpava sage. Br. III. 69. 44.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XI)--(Dvaipāyana) a sage of the first epoch of Sāvarṇa Manu; 1) Br. IV. 1. 11. father's father of Parāśara; on the evils of anger. 2) Vi. I. 1. 12-16.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XII)--the younger brother of Agastya cursed Nimi to become bodyless, a purohita of Nimi. M. 61. 19, 32-33; 201. 14-16.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XIII) the purohita of Dharmamūrti of Bṛhatkalpa; 1) M. 92. 21; 102. 19; 126. 7. praised Śiva out to burn Tripuram 2) Ib. 133. 67.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XIV)--a master of the science of architecture. M. 252. 2.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XV)--a son of Vāli the avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 160. 

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XVI)--a resident of Brahmakṣetra. Vā. 59. 105.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha  (XVII)--(Hiraṇyanābha Kauśalya). a disciple of Jaimini who taught him 500 samhitas; he in his turn taught them to Yājñavalkya. Vā. 88. 207; 98. 92.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha tīrtham --sacred to the Pitṛs. M. 22. 68.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭha putra --Ūrja. Vā. 62. 16.

वसिष्ठ
Vasiṣṭhas --see Vāsiṣṭhas; to them the Pravara is Ekārṣeya. M. 200. 2.

वसु
Vasu  (I)--a son of Vastara and Svarvīthi. Bhā. IV. 13. 12.

वसु
Vasu  (II)--a son of Hiraṇyaretas; also the name of a territorial division of Kuśadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 14.

वसु
Vasu  (III) (Vāstu-Br. P.)--a Vasu, wife Angirasī, and son Viśvakarman. Bhā. VI. 6. 11 and 15. 

वसु
Vasu  (IV)--the son of Bhūtajyotis, and father of Pratīka. Bhā. IX. 2. 17-18.

वसु
Vasu  (V)--a daughter of Dakṣa and one of the ten wives of Dharma; gave birth to eight Vasus. Bhā. VI. 6. 4, 10-11; Br. II. 9. 50, 61; III. 3. 2 and 20. M. 5. 15: Vi. I. 15. 105; Vā. 66. 2.

वसु
Vasu  (VI)--one of the four sons of Kuśa. Bhā. IX. 15. 4; Br. III. 66. 32; Vā. 91. 62; Vi. IV. 7. 8.

वसु
Vasu  (VII)--a son of Mura (s.v.). Bhā. X. 59. 12.

वसु
Vasu  (VIII)--a son of Kṛṣṇa and Sāmbā. Bhā. X. 61. 13.

वसु
Vasu  (IX) (also Vasudhāma)--another name for Brahmajyoti Agni. Br. II. 12. 43; Vā. 29. 21.

वसु
Vasu  (X)--one of the ten sons of Kardama; attained heaven by tapas. Br. II. 14. 9; 30. 39.

वसु
Vasu  (XI)--is Soma. Br. II. 24. 88.

वसु
Vasu  (XII)--a son of Uttānapāda: Asked to arbitrate in the dispute involving animal sacrifice; said that yajña involved himsa and justified Vasu's action: cursed therefor  by sages to live in Rasātala (Pātāla-M.P.): attained heaven by tapas; 1) Br. II. 30. 23-32, 39 and 47; 36. 89; M. 143. 18-25. Vā. 1. 111; 57. 101-11; 62. 76. his daughter Acchodāmatsyagandhi married Parāśara and gave birth to Vyāsa; 2) M. 14. 14. a Rājaṛṣi. 3) Vā. 57. 122.

वसु
Vasu  (XIII)--a Pratardana god. Br. II. 36. 30.

वसु
Vasu  (XIV)--a god of Ādya group. Br. II. 36. 69.

वसु
Vasu  (XV)--a Yakṣa: a son of Puṇyajanī and Maṇibhadra. Br. III. 7. 123. Vā. 69. 154.

वसु
Vasu  (XVI)--the great grand-son of Pṛthu and son of Kṛmi and equal to Indra: Cedipati; 1) Br. III. 8. 98; 68. 27; M. 50. 25-6; Vā. 93. 26. father of Upamanyu from whom the Upamanyava clan sprang. 2) Ib. 70. 89.

वसु
Vasu  (XVII)--a devī attending on Soma. Br. III. 65. 26.

वसु
Vasu  (XVIII)--a son of Devarakṣitā and Vasudeva, killed by Kamsa. Br. III. 71. 181; Vā. 96. 178.

वसु
Vasu  (XIX)--(Kāśyapa), a sage of the Rohita epoch. Br. IV. 1. 62; Vi. III. 2. 23. 

वसु
Vasu  (XX)--a son of Purūravas and Ūrvaśī. M. 24. 33.

वसु
Vasu  (XXI)--one of the ten sons of Svāyambhuva Manu; 1) M. 9. 5; Br. II. 13. 104; Vā. 31. 17. attained heaven by tapas. 2) M. 143. 38.

वसु
Vasu  (XXII)--a son of Sāvarṇi Manu. M. 9. 33.

वसु
Vasu  (XXIII)--left her consort, Mārīcakaśyapa for Soma. M. 23. 25.

वसु
Vasu  (XXIV)--a son of Bhṛgu; one of the ten Viśvedevas. M. 195. 13; 203. 13.

वसु
Vasus --eight in number, and sons of Dharma and Vasu; 1) Bhā. VI. 6. 10; 7. 2; 10. 17; Br. II. 38. 2; IV. 15. 24. worshipped for wealth; 2) Bhā. II. 3. 3; IX. 24. 53; Vi. III. 1. 31. fought with Kāleyas in a Devāsura war; gods of the Vaivasvata epoch, who wait on Hari; 3) Bhā. VIII. 10. 34; 13. 4; IX. 24. 52; X. 39. 54. came with other gods to Dvārakā to ask Kṛṣṇa to go to Vaikuṇṭha. 4) Ib. XI. 6. 2; 16. 13. Brothers of Sādhyas and cursed to experience birth by sexual union; vanquished by Rāvaṇa; their overlord was Agni; 5) Br. II. 27. 24; III. 3. 20 and 80; 7. 254; 8. 5; M. 8. 4; Vi. I. 22. 3; V. 1. 17; 4. 5. also Jyotiṣmantas and Vyāpakas; 6) M. 5. 17; Vi. I. 9. 64 and 70; 15. 105. one of the seven classes of deities of the Vaivasvata epoch; 7) M. 9. 29. eight in number considered as amśā of Vāsudeva; 8) Ib. 5. 20-21; 25. 43; 36. 1; 52. 21; Vā. 10. 71; 39, 49; 30. 83, 99; 64. 2; 66. 19; 69. 44; 106. 59; 109. 22; Vi. I. 15. 109-10. Pitṛs said to be Vasus; 9) M. 19. 3. Somapas. 10) Ib. 69. 62; 132. 3; 203. 3; 246. 60; 247. 11. 

वसुज्येष्ठ
Vasujyeṣṭha --a son of Puṣyamitra, ruled for seven years. M. 272. 28.

वसुद
Vasuda  (I)--a son of Bhṛgu; a deva. Br. III. 1. 89; M. 195. 13.

वसुद
Vasuda  (II)--a son of Purukutsa and Lord of Narmadā. M. 12. 36.

वसुदान
Vasudāna  (I)--a son of Hiraṇyaretas of Kuśadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 14; Vā. 62. 29.

वसुदान
Vasudāna  (II)--a Śiva god. Br. II. 36. 32.

वसुदामा
Vasudāmā --a son of Bṛhadratha. M. 50. 85.

वसुदास
Vasudāsa --a son of Bṛhadratha. Vi. IV. 21. 13.

वसुदेव
Vasudeva  (I)--of the family of Yayāti; a son of Devamīḍha (also Śūra) and Māriṣā. He had a surname Ānakadundubhi because at his birth anakas and dundubhis were sounded as a sign of receiving Hari's grace. Married the seven daughters of Devaka; six other wives of: 1) Bhā. IX. 24., 23-45; Br. III. 61. 23; 71. 146, 160-1, 174; M. 44. 72; Vā. 86. 28; 96. 144, 159-161, 198; 98. 94; Vi. IV. 14. 19. Father of Kṛṣṇa by Devakī; when marrying her he promised Kamsa, who drove the chariot and who heard a voice  from air that her eighth son would kill him, to give him all sons born of Devakī to be killed by him. Took her first son to Kamsa who spared him; was thrown in prison with Devakī by Kamsa. Vasudeva's prayer to the new born Kṛṣṇa; took the babe to Nandagopa's house and exchanged him for the daughter, born to Yaśoda at that time, without anybody knowing it. Released by Kamsa; 2) Bhā. I. 1. 12; 2. 7; 8. 33; III. 2. 25; X. 26. 17; 1. 23 to the end; ch. 3 (whole); 4. 14 and 24; Br. III. 71. 210-35; M. 46. 1-2; 47. 2-6; Vi. V. 1. 5; 3. 15-23. met Nanda who went to the capital for paying annual tribute and after enquiring of his welfare advised him to return home as he expected some trouble at the Vraja. Requested Garga to go to Vraja and perform samskāras to his sons. 3) Bhā. X. 5. 20-31; 8. 1. Visited by Nārada. Vasudeva enquired of Bhāgavata dharma; listened to the traditional account of the talk between the nine sons of Ṛṣabha and Nimi and was pleased along with Devakī; 4) Ib. XI. 2. 3; 31. 15-22. met by Kṛṣṇa at Sudharmā sabhā painted by Citralekhā; 5) Ib. X. [67 (v)  42, 47]; 62. 20. joined the Yadus in defeating Pauṇḍraka Māyā. Vasudeva cut off Sālva before Kṛṣṇa in battle. Welcomed Kṛṣṇa after the Kurukṣetra war; went to Syamantapañcaka for the solar eclipse; here he met the sages and asked them how to get rid of karma by karma. Nārada's praise of. The sages induced him to undertake a sacrifice; requested by Vasudeva to be his Ṛtviks for the yajña they agreed. At the end of the sacrifice, he had his avabhṛta with all his eighteen wives to the great satisfaction of Rāma and Kṛṣṇa, when all castes and even animals were fed; others were honoured with presents. At leave-taking Vasudeva took hold of Nanda's hands and showed that the tie of friendship was the greatest of all ties and wept in joy. Gave Nanda presents; praise of Kṛṣṇa and Rāma and his joy. 6) Ib. X. 66. [2]; 77. 25-9; 80. [13]; 82. 5; chh. 84. and 85 (whole). Kamsa who heard from Nārada that Vasudeva had kept his sons Rāma and Kṛṣṇa under the safe custody of Nanda wanted to kill him. When he was persuaded not to do so, Kamsa imprisoned Vasudeva until Kṛṣṇa released him; celebrated his upanayana. 7) Ib. X. 36. 17-24, [29 and 31]; 44. 33 and 51; 45. 2-9, 26-9. Stationed to defend the eastern gate of Mathurā; consulted by Kṛṣṇa on the eve of attack on Jarāsandha. His part in the third campaign of Jarā; came with Devakī and Kṛṣṇa  to Rukmiṇī's residence where Pradyumna and Māyāvatī had already arrived. His concern at Kṛṣṇa not returning for a long time from the cave of Jāmbavatī. 8) Ib. X. 50. 20 [2]; [50 (v)  8]; [51 (v) 26]; 55. 35; 56. 24. In previous births Sutapa and Kaśyapa (see Devakī). Heard of Kṛṣṇa's decease and also of all the Vṛṣṇis 9) Ib. XI. 31. 15 and 18. and wept; gave his sons Saumī and Kauśika in adoption to his brother, Vṛka; 10) Br. III. 71. 192, 73. 94. nine brothers and four sisters; 11) Vi. IV. 14. 27-31. chastised by Kamsa in the Yādava assembly; 12) Ib. V. 15. 4-5, 18. praise of Kṛṣṇa by Vasudeva; 13) Ib. V. 15. 20-28. entered fire after Kṛṣṇa's death. 14) Ib. V. 38. 4.

वसुदेव
Vasudeva  (II)--a Kaṇva and a minister of the Śunga king Devabhūti; (M. and Br. P.-Devabhūmi); killed his master and became king. Father of Bhūmitra; ruled for five years; began the line of Kāṇvāyanas. Bhā. XII. 1. 19-20; Br. II. 74. 156; M. 272. 32; Vi. IV. 24. 39-40.

वसुदेव
Vasudeva  (III)--a son of Cancu. Vi. IV. 3. 25.

वसुदेवा
Vasudevā --a daughter of Gādinī. Vā. 96. 111.

वसुधा
Vasudhā  (I)--(also Vasundharā); ety. of. Br. II. 37. 1; 36. 226; Vā. 63. 1.

वसुधा
Vasudhā  (II)--the deity to be remembered in installing a new image; the presiding deity is Śarva. M. 265. 38, 40. 

वसुधार
Vasudhāra --a Mt. where there are eight temples to the Vasus. Vā. 38. 23; 39. 44; 42. 30.

वसुन्धरा
Vasundharā --from which the whole world springs and ends. Vā. 62. 193.

वसुन्धर
Vasundharas --a class of people in Śālmalidvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 11.

वसुप्रदम्
Vasupradam --a tīrtha sacred to Pitṛs. M. 22. 72.

वसुभृद्यान
Vasubhṛdyāna --one of the seven sons of Vasiṣṭha. Bhā. IV. 1. 41.

वसुमत
Vasumata --a son of Haryaśva and Dṛṣadvatī. Vā. 88. 76.

वसुमती
Vasumatī  (I)--R. a river of the Bhadrā country. Vā. 43. 27.

वसुमती
Vasumatī  (II)--a daughter of the Vāleya Gandharvas; originator of Vasumati Suta gaṇa. Vā. 69. 21.

वसुमती
Vasumatī  (III)--earth. Vā. 97. 16.

वसुमन्
Vasuman  (I)--a son of Vaivasvata Manu. Bhā. VIII. 13. 3. 

वसुमन्
Vasuman  (II)--a son of Śrutāyu. Bhā. IX. 15. 2.

वसुमन्
Vasuman  (III)--a son of Jamadagni. Bhā. IX. 15. 13.

वसुमन्
Vasuman  (IV)--a son of Kṛṣṇa and Jāmbavatī. Bhā. X. 61. 12.

