Vasuruci  (I)--the milk-man of the Gandharvas on the earth; in his guise, Yakṣa enjoyed Kratusthalā. Br. II. 36. 221; III. 7. 106; Vā. 69. 140.

वसुरुचि
Vasuruci  (II)--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 11.

वसुरूप
Vasurūpa --an Andhaka. Br. III. 71. 143.

वसुरेतस्
Vasuretas --one of the five deities to be propitiated in installing a new image; the presiding deity is Paśupa. M. 265. 38, 40.

वसुर्धामन्
Vasurdhāman --another name for Brahmajyoti Agni. Br. II. 12. 25.

वसुवाह
Vasuvāha --a son of Jaigīsavya, an avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 139.

वसुहंस
Vasuhaṃsa --a son of Śrīdevā and Vasudeva. Bhā. IX. 24. 51.

वसूत्तम
Vasūttama --a name of Bhīsma. Bhā. I. 9. 9. 

वसोर्धारा
Vasordhārā --a wife of Agni, a Vasu. Bha. VI. 6. 13.

वस्तावनि
Vastāvani --being sonless, adopted the sons of Kṛṣṇa. Vā. 96. 189.

वस्तु
Vastu --a son of Lomapāda. Vā. 95. 37.

वस्त्रपदम्
Vastrapadam --a place sacred to Śiva. M. 181. 25.

वस्वनन्त
Vasvananta --a son of Upagupta, and father of Yuyudha. Bhā. IX. 13. 25.

वस्वोकसारा
Vasvokasārā --the city of Indra on the top of the Mānasa to the east of Meru; (see Vasvaukasārā). Vā. 50. 87.

वस्वौकसा
Vasvaukasā --a R. On its bank is the forest Surabhi. Br. II. 18. 62.

