Vākā --a daughter of Mālyavān; one of the four wives of Viśravas; mother of Triśiras, Dūṣana and Vidyu(t)jjihva; Anupālikā (Asalikā-Vā. P.) was her daughter. Br. III. 8. 39-56; Vā. 70. 34, 50.

