Vāgīśa --also Vāgadhīśa and Vākpati; God of learning. M. 22. 79; 23. 33, 46.

वागीश्वरी
Vāgīśvarī --a Śakti created by Nṛsimha from his tongue on behalf of Rudra. M. 179. 63. 

वाग्दुष्ट
Vāgduṣṭa --one of the seven sons of Kauśika. M. 20. 3.

वाग्भूतक
Vāgbhūtakas --an Ātreya clan. Br. III. 8. 85.

वाग्वलि
Vāgvali --a great yogin of the eighth dvāpara. Vā. 23. 141.

