Vāsiruci --an expert in divine music. Vā. 69. 46.

वासिष्ठ
Vāsiṣṭhas  (I)--a deva gaṇa of eleven groups. Br. II. 35. 64; III. 1. 50; 8. 100; IV. 39. 55.

वासिष्ठ
Vāsiṣṭhas  (II)--had seven sons by Urjā: they are Raja, Putra, Ardhabāhu, Savana, Ādhana, Sutapa and Śukla; also daughter Puṇḍarīkā; according to the Br. P. the seven are Rakṣa, Garta, Urdhvabāhu, Savana, Pavana, Sutapa and Śamku. Vā. 28. 34-6; Br. II. 11. 41-2.

वासुकि
Vāsuki  (I)--a son of Kadru: a chieftain of the Nāgaloka. He was used as the rope in the amṛtamathana. Identified with Hari. 1) Bhā. V. 24. 31; VIII. 6. 22 and ch. 7 (whole); XI. 16. 18; Br. III. 7. 32 and 444; 8. 13; 36. 15; IV. 9. 51, 56-9; M. 6. 39; 8. 7; Vi. I. 9. 77 and 84; 21. 21. A friend of Indra: the milkman of the Nāgas for milking the earth: moving with the sun for two months; 2) Br. II. 17. 34; 20. 41; 23. 3; 36. 213; Vi. II. 10. 3. in the Vaiḍūrya śālā of Lalitā; 3) Br. IV. 20. 53; 33. 36. his aid to Tripurāri; 4) M. 114. 83; 126. 3; 133. 25 and 42. an ear ornament of Śiva; shaken by Hiraṇyakaśipu: sports in Amarakaṇṭaka; 5) Ib. 154. 444; 163. 56; 188. 92; 193. 35; 249. 64. heard the Viṣṇu Purāṇa from Dhṛtarāṣṭra the Nāga and narrated it to Vatsa. 6) Vi. VI. 8. 46. 

वासुकि
Vāsuki  (II)--the Nāga presiding over the month of Madhu. Bhā. XII. 11. 33.

वासुकि
Vāsuki  (III)--a son of Surasā and Kaśyapa and a King of the Nāgas; the hundred headed snake in Sutalam; 1) Vā. 50. 39; 70. 12. with the sun in the spring. 2) Ib. 52. 3.

वासुकि
Vāsuki  (IV)--a Nāga living in the Niṣadha hill. Vā. 46. 34; 62. 180; 69. 69.

वासुकिह्रद
Vāsukihrada --a place near Prayāgā; nearby are Kambala, Aśvatara and Bahumūlaka reptiles. M. 104. 5.

वासुदेव
Vāsudeva  (I)--another name for Kṛṣṇa (s.v.) equal to Nārāyaṇa in qualities; value of bhakti towards: His immanence in the Universe: worshipped in the Kaliyuga by the righteous; 1) Bhā. X. 8. 14 and 19; I. 2. 7-34; XII. 2. 22 and 38. Br. I. 2. 37; Vā. 1. 148; 23. 218; Vi. II. 12. 44-7; 15. 35; IV. 13. 105; V. 17. 15; 18. 58; 37. 28; 38. 9. VI. 3. 41; 5. 76, 80. Manu takes the fish to be; 2) M. 1. 26; 2. 16; 45. 18; 52. 20-22; 69. 7; Vi. I. 2. 12; 4. 18; 11. 55; 19. 24. requested by the gods to vanquish Hiraṇyakaśipu; created Śuṣkarevatī to vanquish the Asuras; 3) M. 161. 29-31; 179. 35-6. the presiding deity of planets; 4) M. 230. 9; 242. 16. as a son of Aditi; 5) Ib. 244. 35-42; 245. 20-36; 248. 46. Incon of gifts pleasing to; 6) Ib. 258. 9; 274. 5; 285. 16. eternal and real; 7) Vi. III. 8. 24, 32; IV. 4. 80; VI. 7. 56. numerous sons of; 8) M. 47. 20-21; Vā. 96. 45, 244; 111. 21. got the divine chariot. 9) Ib. 93. 27.

वासुदेव
Vāsudeva  (II)--an author on architecture. M. 252. 3.

वासुदेव
Vāsudeva  (III)--a Vamśavīra. Vā. 97. 1.

