Vikukṣi --the eldest of the 100 sons of Ikṣvāku; Asked by his father to secure some māmsa for his aṣṭaka ritual, he went to the forest, secured some by killing a thousand animals, and feeling hungry, he ate of a portion of the hare's flesh. When this was found out the father abandoned him. He wandered about the land as Śaśāda. But on his father's demise, he was enthroned at Ayodhyā and came to be known as Śaśāda. He pleased Hari by sacrifices. Father of Puramjaya: 1) Bhā. IX. 6. 6-12; Vā. 1. 141; 88. 9-20; 89. 1. Vi. IV. 2. 12-20. Father of 500  sons beginning with Śakuni: Brother of Nimi: went to hell; 2) Br. III. 63. 9-23; 64. 1. had 15 sons who were kings of countries north of Meru and 148 others ruling south of it; the eldest of the latter was Kakustha. 3) M. 12. 26-8.

विकुण्ठ
Vikuṇṭha --a name of Hari. Bhā. III. 16. 6.

