Vicitravīrya --a Kṣetraja son of Matsyagandhī; 1) M. 14. 17; Vi. IV. 20. 34. a son of Śantanu and Dāsayī: married the two daughters of the Kāśī king--Ambikā and Ambālikā, gained in svayamvara by Bhīṣma. Being too much attached to them he took ill and died. 2) Bhā. IX. 22. 21-4; X. 49. 17; Br. III. 10. 70; Vā. 73. 18; 99. 240; Vi. IV. 20. 36-7. By his appointment Kṛṣṇadvaipāyana gave two sons  Dhṛtarāṣṭṛa, and Pāṇḍu to Ambikā and Vidura to Ambālikā, his queens. 3) M. 50. 45-7.

