Vijvara --a son of Anāyuṣa (also Vijara): Father of two sons, Kālaka and Khara. Br. III. 6. 31.

विडम्बिनी
Viḍambinī --a mind-born mother. M. 179. 19. 

विडालव्रतम्
Viḍālavratam --sham observance of vows; such men are disqualified to receive gifts. M. 74. 14.

विड्भुज
Viḍbhuja --the heinous hell for those who eat poisonous food in a row. Vā. 101. 167.

विण्मूत्रभोजन
Viṇmūtrabhojana --a hell. Vi. III. 11. 119.

वितथ
Vitatha  (I)--a name for Bharadvāja, after his adoption by Bharata: father of Manyu. M. 49. 32; Vā. 99. 156; Vi. IV. 19. 19. Bhā. IX. 21. 1.

वितथ
Vitatha  (II)--a god to be worshipped in house building; 1) M. 253. 25. before building a palace. 2) Ib. 255. 8; 268. 13.

वितल
Vitala --a thigh of the personified Lord: an under-world Here Śiva resides with Pārvatī under the name of Hāṭakeśvara. The place is noted for hāṭaka gold with which the asura ladies of the place make ornaments. Bhā. II. 1. 27; 5. 40; V. 24. 7 and 17.

वितलम्
Vitalam --red earth; here are cities of Prahlāda. Anuhlāda. etc; 1) Vā. 50. 11. 15. 25-30. a region of Pātāla. 2) Vi. II. 5. 2-3. 

वितस्ता
Vitastā  (I)--a R. in Bhārata varṣa from the Himālayas; 1) Bhā. V. 19. 18; Br. II. 12. 15; 16. 25; Vā. 45. 90; M. 114. 21. sacred to the pitṛs. 2) Ib. 22. 36.

वितस्ता
Vitastā  (II)--one of the sixteen wives of Havyavāhana; 1) M. 51. 13; Vā. 29. 13. in the chariot of Tripurāri. 2) M. 133. 23.

वितस्ति
Vitasti --a measurement by the little finger, 12 aṅgulas; 1) M. 58. 8; Vā. 8. 104; 101. 122; Br. II. 7. 98. in connection with gṛhabalikuṇḍam. 2) M. 93. 7.

