Vidarbha  (III)--(Vaiśa) son of Jyāmagha and Śaibyā: married the young Bhoja girl (Snuṣā-Vā. P.) got in war and  already appointed as his wife before his birth by his parents. Father of three sons of whom Romapāda (Lomapāda-M. P.) was the most famous; the others were Krathu and Kauśika. all of them warriors. Bhā. IX. 23. 39; 24. 1; Br. III. 70. 36-8. M. 44. 36; Vā. 95. 35; Vi. IV. 12. 35-38.

