Vidiksthānam --the place where Śrāddha is performed; generally south west; three holes to be made and three pieces of khādira (acacia catechu) measuring the length of a cubit (aratni) to be placed; then is the śodhana or purification of agni by milk and ghee. Vā. 74. 7-11.

विदिग्ध
Vidigdha --a Vājin. Vā. 61. 25.

