Vidūratha  (III)--a brother of Dantavaktra: Heard of his brother's death and attacked Kṛṣṇa who cut off his head. 1) Bhā. X. 78. 11-12; II. 7. 34. Stationed by Jarāsandha on the eastern gate of Mathurā: arrived at Kuṇḍina. 2) Ib. X. 50. 11[2]; 53. 17.

विदूरथ
Vidūratha  (IV)--(Vidūra-Vā. P.)--a son of Bhajamāna, a skilled charioteer. Br. III. 71. 136; Vā. 96. 135. 

