Vidyunmālī  (II)--the Asura of great penance who took a glorious part in the Tārakāmaya war; 1) M. 129. 5. on the side of Maya; he received a deadly wound from Nandi and fell dead; restored to life by Maya with the medicinal waters of the tank; 2) Ib. 131. 22. his battle with Nandi and death. 3) Ib. 136. 16 f; 138. 47; 140. 18-36.

