Śukī  (II)--a daughter of Tāmrā and Kaśyapa; married Garutmat and had six sons Triśira, Sumukha, Bala, Pṛṣṭa, Triśankunetra and Surasa who had in their turn a number of sons and grandsons; 1) Br. III. 7. 8-9, 446; Vā. 69. 328-30. brought forth parrots and owls; gave birth to parrots, owls, and crows (Vi. P.) 2) M. 6. 30-31; Vi. I. 21. 15-16.

