सुद्ध
Suddhas --a Janapada of the Bhadrā country. Vā. 43. 19.

शुद्धि
Śuddhi --the goddess enshrined at Kapālamocana. M. 13. 48.

शुद्धोद
Śuddhoda  (I)--the sea of fresh water. Bhā. V. 1. 33.

शुद्धोद
Śuddhoda(na)  (II)--a son of Śākya, and father of Lāngala (Rāhula-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 12. 14; Vā. 99. 288; Vi. IV. 22. 8.

शुद्धौदन
Śuddhaudana --a son of Śākya. M. 271. 12.

शुनक
Śunaka  (I)--a son of Ṛta, and father of Vītahavya. Bhā. IX. 13. 26.

शुनक
Śunaka  (II)--a son of Gṛtasamada, and father of Śaunaka. Bhā. IX. 17. 3; Br. III. 67. 4; Vā. 92. 4.

शुनक
Śunaka  (III)--the minister of Puramjaya; killed his king and placed his own son Pradyota on the throne. Bhā. XII. 1. 3; Br. III. 74. 123.

शुनक
Śunaka  (IV)--a disciple of Pathya. Bhā. XII. 7. 2.

शुनक
Śunaka  (V)--approached by Keśidhvaja to give him a form of expiation. Vi. VI. 6. 16. 

शुनश्शेफ
Śunaśśepha  (I)--the second son of Ajigarta (Satyavati and Ṛcīka) purchased by Rohita and used by Hariścandra as a sacrificial animal in the place of his son. Adopted as son by Viśvāmitra. When his first fifty sons refused to recognise him as their brother, they were cursed to be Mlecchas. The younger fifty agreed to regard him as their brother and were blessed. He is Śuna to Bhṛgu family and Devarāta to the Gādhi line. His advent with the Kauśika family distinguished it from the Viśvāmitras; compared to Prahlāda. Bhā. IX. 7. 21; 16. 30-37; VII. 5. 46; Br. III. 66. 66 and 74; Vā. 91. 92-6.

शुनश्
Śunaś śepha  (II)--the second son of Jamadagni. Br. III. 66. 64.

शुनः
Śunaḥ puccha --the last son of Jamadagni (Satyavatī and Ṛcīka). Br. III. 66. 64; Vā. 91. 92.

सुनादेवि
Sunādevi --the daughter of Samudra and wife of Varuṇa; two sons Kali and Vaidhya and a daughter, Surasundarī. Vā. 84. 6.

शुनामुखा
Śunāmukhā --a kingdom of the west watered by the Sindhu. Br. II. 18. 49; M. 121. 47; Vā. 47. 46.

शुनी
Śunī --a R. from the Ṛṣyavān. M. 114. 26.

शुपर्ण
Śuparṇa --a Sudhāmāna god. Br. II. 36. 28. 

शुभ
Śubha  (I)--born of Śraddhā. Bhā. IV. 1. 50.

शुभ
Śubha  (II)--a god of Sutāra group. Br. IV. 1. 90.

शुभ
Śubha  (III)--a son of Tāmasa Manu. Br. II. 36. 49.

शुभ
Śubha  (IV)--a son of Havirdhāna. M. 4. 45.

शुभ
Śubha  (V)--one of the ten branches of the Supāra group of devas. Vā. 100. 94.

शुभ
Śubhas --a class of Apsaras from the sacrificial altar. Vā. 69. 56.

शुभक्षण
Śubhakṣaṇa --a Vānara chief. Br. III. 7. 241.

शुभक्षत्र
Śubhakṣatra --a Vānara chief. Br. III. 7. 240, 243.

शुभलक्षण
Śubhalakṣaṇa  (I)--born of Pulaha. Br. III. 7. 179.

शुभलक्षण
Śubhalakṣaṇa  (II)--(of horses) devasvastika, devapadmam, devamaṇi, phalaśukti, śvetaśukti, puṣpagaṇḍika, svastika śukti, gaḍura. Br. IV. 16. 21-22. 

शुभवती
Śubhavatī --the sabhā of Varuṇa in the fifth slope of Meru; the lord of waters. Vā. 34. 89.

शुभसप्तमी
Śubhasaptamī --to be observed in the month of Āśvayuja in honour of the sun god; he becomes one among the devagaṇas and lives as such upto the final dissolution of the world. M. 74. 3; 80. 1, 11.

शुभा
Śubhā  (I)--a wife of Pulaha; mother of Hamsa and others. Br. III. 7. 178.

शुभा
Śubhā  (II)--a mother goddess. M. 179. 29.

शुभा
Śubhā  (III)--one of the ten daughters of Raudrāśva. Vā. 99. 125.

शुभ्र
Śubhra  (I)--the father of Vaikuṇṭha Hari. Bhā. VIII. 5. 4.

शुभ्र
Śubhra  (II)--took part in Devāsura war between Bali and Indra. Fought with Bhadrakālī. Bhā. VIII. 10. 21 and 31.

शुभ्र
Śubhra  (III)--a son of Vasudeva and Rohiṇī. Br. III. 71. 165; Vā. 96. 163.

शुम्भ
Śumbha  (I)--a commander of Tāraka's force; had the sheep for his riding animal; 1) M. 148, 43, 55; 151. 5. threw darts on Janārdana; a Citrayodhi against Janārdana who threw bhusuṇḍi at him  and his goat and said “you are to be killed by a girl; get away;” 2) Ib. 150. 224; 152. 25-52; 245. 32. killed by Durgā; 3) Br. IV. 29. 76. killed by Yoganidrā. 4) Vi. V. 1. 82.

शुम्भ
Śumbha  (II)--a son of Ganeṣṭhi. Vā. 67. 77.

शुल्क
Śulka --a price for marriage; Kṛṣṇa was not prepared to pay any price for Satyā; 1) Bhā. X. 58. 40. one selling a daughter to be punished; 2) M. 227. 20. a tax gathered by kings of Kali age. 3) Vi. VI. 1. 34.

शुश्रवस्
Śuśravas --a Prajāpati. Br. III. 1. 53.

शुष्क
Śuṣka --a sage who waited on Paraśurāma with other sages for the reclamation of Gokarṇa and insisted that an established rule may be broken for the sake of dharma. Br. III. 57. 1, 23-4.

शुष्करेवती
Śuṣkarevatī (Suṣkā) --created by Vāsudeva for vanquishing the Asuras by name Andhakas at the request of Rudra; she drank their blood and destroyed the whole lot; aided Nṛsimha in creating further mother goddesses to overpower the mātṛ gaṇa of Rudra; 1) M. 179. 36. 65. will grant children if worshipped. 2) Ib. 179. 85.

शुष्का
Śuṣkā --see Śuṣkarevatī. M. 179. 85.

शुष्मीण
Śuṣmīṇa --the Kṣatriya caste of Kuśadvīpa. Vi. II. 4. 38. 

शूक
Śūkas --a deva gaṇa. Vā. 10. 21.

शूकर
Śūkara --a hell, intended for the five heinous offences. Br. IV. 2. 146, 154.

शूद्र
Śūdras  (I)--the members of the fourth Varṇa; 1) Bhā. I. 13. 15; II. 1. 37; 7. 38 and 46; VII. 11. 24. their duty was service; 2) Ib. VIII. 5. 41; XI. 17. 19. not fit for the study of the Vedas; 3) Ib. X. 24. 20; 38. 4. invited for the Rājasūya of Yudhiṣṭira; 4) Ib. X. 74. 11. kings of Kali age, especially after Puramjaya; 5) Ib. XI. 4. 22; 5. 4; 12. 4; 27. 4; XII. 1. 8 and 38; 2. 35. receive gifts, become ascetics and expound dharma from high places in Kali; 6) Ib. XII. 3. 38. duty was dharma paricāra yajña; take to Brāhmaṇa dharma in Kali yuga; not fit for panktibhojanam. For the sake of 1,000 Śūdras, one Brāhmaṇa may be killed; creation of: Pṛṣadhra born a Śūdra by cow-slaughter; 7) Br. II. 29. 55; 31. 394 and 367; III. 10. 96; 11. 87; 15. 44; 68. 67; IV. 6. 43. meditate on Devī's 108 names; perform śrāddha with no mantras; 8) M. 4. 28; 12. 25; 13. 63; 17. 64, 70-71. observe a month's pollution for father's death; Yayāti's benevolence to; Śūdra kings rooted out by Kalki; 9) Ib. 18. 3; 34. 5; 47. 250. 50. 75; 144. 39-54. may observe Rohiṇicandra śayanam and Angāraka vratam. 10) Ib. 57. 6; 72. 20-1; 114. 12; 217. 2.

शूद्र
Śūdras  (II)--created out of the feet of the Lord; 1) Vi. I. 6. 6. Gāndharvam sthānam; 2) Ib. I. 6. 35. duties of; 3) Ib. III. 8. 33-4. as kings from the time of Mahāpadma; 4) Ib. IV. 24. 21 and 68. take to asceticism and become followers of heretical sects; no regard for age, learning and family; 5) Vā. 58. 40-41; Vi. VI. 1. 37. fortunate, because they do not have to undergo the ordeals of performing rituals and ceremonials incumbent on the twice born castes; not fettered by restrictions of any sort. 6) Ib. VI. 2. 23. 4.

शूद्र
Śūdras  (III)--a tribe. M. 114. 40. 

शूद्रहत्याव्रतम्
Śūdrahatyāvratam --the vow for killing a Śūdra; for murder of a woman, for reaping fruits and flowers, for cutting trees for injuring bony and boneless animals. M. 227. 34, 36.

शूद्रा
Śūdrā  (I)--(Prabhākara, s.v.); a daughter of Bhadrāśva and Gḥṛtācī; one of the ten wives of Atri. Br. III. 8. 75; Vā. 70. 68.

शूद्रा
Śūdrā  (II)--one of the ten daughters of Raudrāśva. Vā. 99. 125.

शून्यकम्
Śūnyakam --the city of Bhaṇḍa on the banks of the Mahārṇava (sea?) near Mahendra hill: In extent 100 Yojanas: filled with candraśālas, pleasure parks, sabhā, temples and so on: protected by Kuṭilākṣa on all sides when it was attacked by fifty akṣauhinis of soldiers; 1) Br. IV. 21. 3-20, 96; 22. 22; 23. 98; 26. 21. burnt by Lalitā with civil population. 2) Ib. IV. 29. 21. 143.

शून्यकनाथ
Śūnyakanātha --the Lord of the city of Śūnyaka. Br. IV. 22. 108.

शून्यबन्धु
Śūnyabandhu --a son of Kubera. Bhā. IX. 2. 33.

शूर
Śūra  (I)--the grand-father of the Pāṇḍavas by mother's line; 1) Bhā. I. 14. 26; III. 1. 26. father of Vasudeva. 2) Ib. X. 1. 29; 3. 47 and 51.

शूर
Śūra  (II)--a son of Vīdūratha and father of Bhajamāna. (Śami, Vi. P.). 1) Bhā. IX. 24. 26; Vi. IV. 14. 23. A great king and father of eight sons. 2) Br. III. 71. 137-9. 

शूर
Śūra  (III)--Devamīdha. Bhā. IX. 24. 26-27.

शूर
Śūra  (IV)--a son of Madirā and Vasudeva. Bhā. IX. 24. 48.

शूर
Śūra  (V)--a son of Kṛṣṇa and Bhadrā: His picture drawn by Citralekha. Bhā. X. 61. 17; 62. 20.

शूर
Śūra  (VI)--a kingdom: Dvijas of this became vrātyas after Puramjaya's days. Bhā. XII. 1. 38.

शूर
Śūra  (VII)--one of Kārtavīryārjuna's five sons who escaped; 1) Br. III. 41. 13; M. 43. 46; Vā. 94. 79; Vi. IV. 11. 21. a mahāratha; 2) Br. III. 69. 50. in the course of a hunt he entered the hermitage of Jamadagni with sword in hand and killed him; 3) Ib. III. 45. 1. killed by Paraśurāma. 4) Ib. III. 46. 17, 23.

शूर
Śūra  (VIII)--a son of Aśmaki? (Devagarbha-Vi. P.): wife Mahiṣā or Bhojā (Mārīṣā-Vi. P.); Father of ten sons, the eldest being Vasudeva: also of 5 daughters; 1) Br. III. 71. 144, 151; Vi. IV. 14. 25-7. had a friend Kuntī who was childless; to him he gave his daughter Pṛthā in adoption; Pāṇḍu married her. 2) Ib. IV. 14. 32-4.

शूर
Śūra  (IX)--a son of Agāvaha. Br. III. 71. 257.

शूर
Śūra  (X)--a name of Vīgneśvara. Br. IV. 44. 68. 

शूर
Śūra  (XI)--a son of Aikṣvāki; married Bhojā and had 10 sons and 5 daughters. M. 46. 1, 4.

शूर
Śūra  (XII)--a son of Bhajamāna; wife Asmakī; had a number of sons, Vāta, Nivāta, etc. Vā. 96. 135-6, 143.

शूर
Śūras  (XIII)--the country of the. Vi. II. 3. 16.

शूरभू
Śūrabhū --a daughter of Ugrasena and wife of Śyāmaka. Bhā. IX. 24. 25 and 42.

शूरसेन
Śūrasena  (I) (c)--the kingdom of Citraketu. Bhā. VI. 14. 10; XI. 30. 18.

शूरसेन
Śūrasena  (II)--a son of Arjuna (Kārtavīrya); a mahāratha. Bhā. IX. 23. 27; M. 43. 46; Vā. 94. 49. 99. 325; Vi. IV. 11. 21.

शूरसेन
Śūrasena  (III)--the Lord of the Yadus and overlord of Māthuras and Śūrasenas. Bhā. X. 1. 27.

शूरसेन
Śūrasena  (IV)--a son of Śatrughna: capital Mathurā. Br. III. 63. 187; Vā. 88. 186; Vi. IV. 4. 104.

शूरसेन
Śūrasenas --the people of Śūrasena territory. Fought with their kinsmen and ended their lives; 1) Bhā. I. 10. 34; 15. 39; IX. 24. 63; XI. 30. 18; Vā. 45. 110. a kingdom of madhyadeśa; 2) Br. II. 16. 41; III. 74; 138. the tribe with Śūra as their chief: Pañcarathas: honoured Sagara and were killed by Paraśurāma; 3) Ib. III. 45. 1; 46. 17; 49. 5; M. 114. 35. kings of the line, 17 in number. 4) Ib. 272. 17. 

शूरि
Śūri --a name of Kṛṣṇa born to Devaki. M. 46. 15.

शूर्पकर्ण
Śūrpakarṇa --a name of Vināyaka. Br. III. 42. 37; IV. 44. 67.

शूर्पणखा
Śūrpaṇakhā --a daughter of Viśravas and Kaikasī; sister of Rāvaṇa; 2) Br. III. 8. 47. disfigured by Rāma. 3) Bhā. IX. 10. 4. ^1 Vā. 70. 41.

शूर्पवात
Śūrpavāta --the wind of a winnowing basket blowing upon a person, makes him lose his lustre. Vi. V. 38. 40.

शूर्पाकार
Śūrpākāra --sages of this place visited Dvārakā; visited by Balarāma. Bhā. X. 90. 28 [5]; 79. 20.

शूलक्षेत्रम्
Śūlakṣetram --near Gṛdhrakūṭa hill in Gayā. Vā. 108. 64.

शूलदन्त
Śūladanta --the Rākṣaṣa residing in Tatvalam (AtalamVā. P.). Br. II. 20. 17; Vā. 50. 17.

शूलपाणि
Śūlapāṇi --(see Śūlabhṛt or Śūladhara): a name of Śiva; 1) M. 104. 10; 140. 48; 154. 396; Vi. V. 33. 45. admitted for share in sacrifice due to fear of Daṇḍa; 2) M. 225. 18. approaches Nārāyaṇa after Brahmā issues from his belly; his approach is noticed by Brahmā and reported to Nārāyaṇa who explains his nature asking Brahmā to join him in a praise of; dialogue between Brahmā and Nārāyaṇa on the greatness of; praise of by both; gives boons to Brahmā who wants him as son or one equal to him; appreciates Viṣṇu and disappears. 3) Vā. 24. 36-165; 25. 1-27. 

शूलप्रोत
Śūlaprota --one of the twenty-eight hells for those who allure innocents by magical and other practices. Bhā. V. 26. 7 and 32.

शूलभृत्
Śūlabhṛt --Śūlapāṇi, Śūladhara, Śūli, Śiva: living in the city of Bāṇa; 1) Br. II. 13. 62; M. 6. 13. lord of different classes of spirits; 2) Ib. 8. 5. blessed Yama son of Vivasvān to be a lokapāla and Lord of Pitṛs; 3) Ib. 11. 19. married Dākṣāyaṇī and was not invited to Dakṣa's sacrifice; 4) Ib. 13. 13. with 18 hands, residing at Gomati; 5) Ib. 22. 13. acted as Protector for Soma's Rājasūya. 6) Ib. 23. 19; 252. 5.

शूलभेदम्
Śūlabhedam --a tīrtha on the Narmadā; sacred to Śiva. M. 191. 3-4.

शूलम्
Śūlam  (I)--the trident, held by Gangā in worshipping Śiva in Meru. Vā. 30. 92.

शूलम्
Śūlam  (II)--a stake, mounting on; a punishment in hell. Vi. VI. 5. 47.

शूलि
Śūli --is Śiva, 1) Br. IV. 11. 28; 30. 74. the avatār of the Lord in the 24th dvāpara in the Naimiṣa. 2) Vā. 23. 206.

शूलिका
Śūlikās --the kingdom of; a northern kingdom. Br. II. 31. 83; M. 121. 45; Vā. 47. 44; 58. 83.

शृगालवासुदेव
Śṛgālavāsudeva --chieftain of Karavīrapura resented Kṛṣṇa and Rāma going to Gomanta and was killed by Kṛṣṇa. His capital occupied by Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. [52 (V) 29-41]; [53 (V) 22]; 52. [56 (V) 7]. 

शृङ्ग
Śṛṅga --a Mt. three hillocks of jewels, gems and gold. M. 113. 68-9.

शृङ्गवत्
Śṛṅgavat  (I) (c)--a kingdom north of Śvetam, of Kuru. Br. II. 14. 51; 15. 34; Vā. 33. 44.

शृङ्गवत्
Śṛṅgavat  (II)--a Mt. in Jambūdvīpa, noted for gold and gems, abode of Pitṛs, north of the Śveta. Br. II. 15. 22, 28, 69-70; 17. 36. 21. 138-41; M. 113. 23; Vā. 34. 20, 25; 45. 2; 114. 84.

शृङ्गवत्
Śṛṅgavat  (III)--a varṣa, next to Hiraṇmaya. Vā. 34. 30.

शृङ्गारनायिका
Śṛṅgāranāyikā --a name of Lalitā. Br. IV. 18. 17.

शृङ्गि
Śṛṅgi  (I)--a Ṛṣika. M. 145. 96.

शृङ्गि
Śṛṅgi  (II)--the country to its north formed a division of Jambūdvīpa; 1) Vi. II. 1. 22. north of Jambūdvīpa; 2) Ib. II. 2. 11. contains three peaks, resembling horns. 3) Ib. II. 8. 73.

शृङ्गिन
Śṛṅginas --a group of gods doing śrāddha. Br. III. 10. 109.

शृङ्गिपुत्र
Śṛṅgiputra  (I)--a sage and author of Sāmaveda. Br. II. 35. 43.

शृङ्गिपुत्र
Śṛṅgiputra  (II)--a Kauthuma, composed three samhitās. Vā. 61. 39, 40. 

शृञ्जय
Śṛñjaya --a son of Bheda; 1) Vā. 99. 196. His daughters married by Bāhyaka. 2) Ib. 96. 3.

शृञ्जया
Śṛñjayā --queen of Bhajamāna. Vā. 96. 3.

शृष्टचय
Śṛṣṭacaya --a son of Gāndini. Vā. 96. 111.

शेनी
Śenī --a mantrakṛt and of Angirasa branch. Vā. 59. 98.

शेष
Śeṣa  (I)--the amśa of Hari: his bed; 1) Bhā. VIII. 4. 20; III. 8. 23; V. 25. 11. the force of Hari: personified; 2) Ib. X. 2. 8; VI. 16. 30. not finished yet chanting the glories of Viṣṇu; 3) Ib. II. 7. 41. a Prajāpati; 4) Br. III. 1. 53; Vā. 65. 53. a chief of 1000 headed snakes, protected the chariot of Tripurāri; 5) M. 6. 39. bed of Brahmam, (Viṣṇu) son of Kadru and Kaśyapa; 6) Ib. 133. 62; 138. 39; 146. 22. of the Pātāla, shaken by Hiraṇyakaśipu; 7) Ib. 163. 57. the Lord identified with; 8) Ib. 167. 53. offerings to before house construction. 9) Ib. 249. 15; 268. 17.

शेष
Śeṣa  (II)--(Ananta): a tāmasa form of Viṣṇu down below the Pātāla regions; with 1000 jewelled heads, purple garment, white necklace; in his hands are the plough and mace; worshipped by Lakṣmī and Vāruṇī; when the deluge sets in, he vomits venomed fire devouring the three worlds; Nāga maids adorn him with fragrant sandal paste; celestials and Asuras worship him; Gangā worshipped him and learnt from him astronomy and astrology; supports the whole earth with his head; 1) Vi. II. 5. 13-27. the best of Nāgas; 2) Ib. III. 2. 51. is Balarāma. 3) Ib. V. 25. 1; 35. 3. 

शेष
Śeṣa  (III)--the Nāga, King of Pātālam. Follows the Vaiṣṇava policy; 1) Br. II. 17. 34; 20. 54-5; III. 7. 32; 8. 13; 36. 53, 57; IV. 33. 36; Vā. 45. 53; 46. 34; 50. 53; 70. 12; 99. 366. described as in Pātalam. 2) Vā. 50. 46-53.

शेषवानुरु
Śeṣavānuru --a Dānava. Br. III. 6. 16.

शैनेय
Śaineya --a name of Sātyakī. Bhā. I. 13. 16[1].

शैन्या
Śainyās --(Śaineyas): beginning with Śini and ending with Yugandhara. This is the line of Anamitra, a branch of the Vṛṣṇis. (Kṣetropetadvijas). M. 45. 24; Vi. IV. 14. 4; 19. 23.

शैब्जा
Śaibjā  (Śaibyā-M. P., Vi. P.), a wife of Kṛṣṇa, and mother of Samgrāmajit and other sons. Br. II. 71. 243; M. 47, 13: Vi. V. 32. 3.

शैब्य
Śaibya  (I)--the king of Suvīras: placed on the west during the siege of Gomanta by Jarāsandha; 1) Bhā. X. 52. 11 [12]. joined the Pāṇḍavas against the Kurus; 2) Ib. X. 78 [95 (v) 13]. his daughter Ratnā, was married to Akrūra. 3) M. 45. 28.

शैब्य
Śaibya  (II)--the name of a horse of the chariot of Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. 53. 5; 89. 49.

शैब्या
Śaibyā --(Śaivyā) wife of Jyāmagha: welcomed by Draupadī to Hāstinapura. Bhā. IX. 23. 34; X. 71. 43; Vi. 12. 14. 

शैभ्या
Śaibhyās --(Gargas): descendants of Śibi; the Brahmans with Kṣatriya profession. M. 49. 38.

शैमिमण्डलकोष्ठम्
Śaimimaṇḍalakoṣṭham --the place where the R. Pāvanī ends. M. 121. 59.

शैलमुखी
Śailamukhī --a mind-born mother. M. 179. 19.

शैलराजसुता
Śailarājasutā --resides in Jyotiṣka on Meru with Śiva, and worshipped by all. Vā. 30. 83.

शैलश्रिशिखर
Śailaśriśikhara --a Mt. on the south of the Mānasa lake. Vā. 36. 22.

शैलालय
Śailālaya --a sage. M. 200. 7.

शैलूज
Śailūja --a Mt. in the Gajāśilā. Vā. 108. 48.

शैलूस
Śailūsa --a tribe. Br. IV. 7. 19.

शैलोद
