Śrāvasta --a son of Yuvanāśva and the founder of the city of Śrāvasti; the father of Brahmadaśva. Br. III. 63. 27; M. 12. 30; Vā. 88. 26-7.

श्रावस्ति
Śrāvasti --the city built by Śrāvasta of the Ikṣvāku line; capital of Uttarakośala where Lava ruled; 1) Br. III. 63. 28, 200; Vā. 88. 200. in Gauḍadeśa built by Vatsaka son of Śrāvasta. 2) M. 12. 30.

श्राविष्ठायन
Śrāviṣṭhāyana --of Śveta Parāśara clan. M. 201. 36.

श्रिंगवान्
Śriṃgavān --a varṣa parvata north of the Śveta of three tops of which one is Iṣuvatam śringa; 1) Vā. 1. 85; 50. 189. residence of Pitṛs. 2) Ib. 46. 35.

श्रिंगि
Śriṃgi --see Śringavān. Br. I. 69; Vā. 64. 7.

श्री
Śrī  (I)--(Khāyāti), a daughter of Bhṛgu and Khyāti devoted to Bhagavān; 1) Bhā. I. 10. 26; 11. 26 and 33; IV. 1. 43; 24. 49. requested by Devas to approach Nṛsimha with a view to appease his wrath, she dared not go near him; 2) Ib. VII. 9. 2; VIII. 4. 20; 5. 40; 23. 6; IX. 4. 60; X. 3. 50; 9. 20; 29. 37; 31. 17; XI. 14. 15 & 39; XII. 11. 20. elder sister of Dhātā and Vidhātā; married Nārāyaṇa and gave birth to Bala and Unmāda (utsāha) besides mind-born sons; 3) Br. II. 11. 2; 13. 78; Vā. 28. 2. alias Mahālakṣmī or Lakṣmī. 4) Br. IV. 39. 70-71. 44. 71; Vā. 37. 38. 

श्री
Śrī  (II)--came out of the churning of the milk ocean, whom Viṣṇu placed on his breast: the dweller in the lotus: also Śrīdevī. Br. IV. 9. 76, 79; 33. 46; 36. 21, 31 and 90.

श्री
Śrī  (III)--a Kala of the moon. Br. IV. 35. 92.

श्रीकण्ठ
Śrīkaṇṭha --see Śiva. Br. III. 24. 63; 25. 19; IV. 30. 40.

श्रीकण्ठदयित
Śrīkaṇṭhadayita --is Lalitā. Br. IV. 13. 4.

श्रीखण्ड
Śrīkhaṇḍa --a name for camphor. M. 284. 9.

श्रीगिरि
Śrīgiri --sages of this Mt. visited Dvārakā. Bhā. X. 90. 28[3].

श्रीगुरु
Śrīguru  and Gurupatnī--represent Brahmam. Br. IV. 43. 7.

श्रीचक्रम्
Śrīcakram --the mantra of: is Mahālakṣmī: worshipped by Viṣṇu, Śiva and Brahmā: propitiation of, makes one learned: Icon of: the mudras in connection with the worship of; Dīkṣa and its methods. Br. IV. 41. 3-5; chh. 42-3.

श्रीचक्ररूपिणी
Śrīcakrarūpiṇī --is Kāmākṣī. Br. IV. 40. 119.

श्रीचीन्तामणिमन्त्र
Śrīcīntāmaṇimantra --to be uttered in Devi's offering. Br. IV. 43. 19. 

श्रीतलम्
Śrītalam --of rocky earth; here are cities of Kesari, Suparvaṇa, Vāsuki, the king of the Nāgas. Vā. 50. 12, 38-40.

श्रीदण्डनाथा
Śrīdaṇḍanāthā --the leader of Lalitā's hosts against Bhaṇḍa; also Potrinī; her march described; in Kiricakraratha: Her mount was the lion Vajraghoṣa; 1) Br. IV. 16. 31; 17. 8, 27; ch. 21. hit Kuṭalākṣa, the chief commander of Bhaṇḍa: consulted Mantrinī: helped Kumārī in her expedition against sons of Bhaṇḍa: ascended Geyacakra and fought with Viṣanga: became happy at the end. 2) Ib. IV. 26. 1-113; 27. 45 and 58; 28. 14-20; 34. 55.

श्रीदामन्
Śrīdāman --a playmate of Kṛṣṇa in his Hariṇākāiḍana sport. Expressed to Kṛṣṇa the desire to rid the palmyra grove of Asura Dhenuka. Being victor in a game, he had the honour of being borne on the back by Kṛṣṇa; 1) Bhā. X. 15. 20; 18. 23-4; 22. 31; Vi. V. 9. 13-14. was placed by Śiva on his lap as a token of affection. 2) Br. III. 42. 55; 43. 29.

श्रीदेवा
Śrīdevā --a daughter of Devaka; a queen of Vasudeva and mother of six sons of whom Nandaka was one. Bhā. IX. 24. 23 & 51; Br. III. 71. 131, 162 and 181; IV. 29. 2; Vā. 96. 130; Vi. 14. 18.

श्रीधर
Śrīdhara --a name of Viṣṇu. Vā. 111. 21.

श्रीनगरम्
Śrīnagaram --is Śrīpuram. Br. IV. 37. 98; 38. 28.

श्रिपति
Śripati tīrtham --sacred to the Pitṛs. M. 22. 74. 

श्रिपर्णि
Śriparṇi --a R. sacred to the Pitṛs. M. 22. 49.

श्रिपर्वतम्
Śriparvatam --Mt. a hill in India, fit for Śrāddha offerings; 1) Br. II. 16. 23; III. 13. 28, 31; Vā. 45. 92; 77. 28. sacred to Śiva. 2) M. 181. 28.

श्रीपादुकास्मृति
Śrīpādukāsmṛti --superior to mahādānas and mahāyajñas. Br. IV. 43. 57.

श्रीपार्वतीय
Śrīpārvatīyas --foresters? ruled for 52 years. M. 273. 23.

श्रीपाशायुधसम्भव
Śrīpāśāyudhasambhava --he who came out of the Pāśa of Lalitā rode on a superior horse. Br. IV. 16. 14 and 29.

श्रीपीठम्
Śrīpīṭham --is Bindupīṭha. Br. IV. 37. 46; 44. 95.

श्रिपुरम्
Śripuram --(Śrīnagara) the city of Lalitā: built by Viśvakarman and Maya; in the Ṣoḍaśakṣetra madhya: Of this nine were bhauma and the seven waters: It is called Kāmeśvarīpurī, Bhayamalīpuri, Nityaklinnapuri: surrounded by Brahmā, Viṣṇu and Śiva lokas: seven prākāras, all of metal. Br. IV. 30. 106-7; 31. 1, 106; 32. 1-10.

श्रीपूर्ती
Śrīpūrtī --a devī in Cintāmaṇi gṛha. Br. IV. 36. 26.

श्रीभानु
Śrībhānu --a son of Kṛṣṇa and Satyabhāmā. Bhā. X. 61. 11. 

श्रीभूशक्ति
Śrībhūśakti --on the Geyacakra. Br. IV. 19. 74.

श्रिमद्भागवत
Śrimadbhāgavata --produced by the great sage Vyāsa; taught by him to Śuka who narrated it to Parīkṣit, when Sūta heard it. Bhā. I. 1. 2; 3. 40-44.

श्रिमल्लकर्णि
Śrimallakarṇi --a son of Kṛṣṇa, ruled for 10 years. M. 273. 3.

श्रीमहापादुका
Śrīmahāpādukā --in the Cintāmaṇi gṛha. Br. IV. 36. 26.

श्रीमान्
Śrīmān  (I)--the most celebrated among the Nīpas. M. 49. 53.

श्रिमान्
Śrimān  (II)--a son of Āpa, the Vasava. M. 203. 6.

श्रीमूर्ति
Śrīmūrti --the manifestation of Hari in the epoch of the tenth Manu: born of Viśvasrk. Bhā. VIII. 13. 21[1].

श्रीरङ्ग
Śrīraṅga --visited by Balarāma; 1) Bhā. X. 79. 14. sacred to Pitṛs. 2) M. 22. 44.

श्रीवत्स
Śrīvatsa --the jewel of Kṛṣṇa; 1) Vā. 96. 204. of Pauṇḍarīka Vāsudeva. 2) Vi. V. 34. 17.

श्रीवनम्
Śrīvanam --a bilvavanam east of Ś(r)īsaras; served by the Gandharvas, Kinnaras, Yakṣas, Siddhas; the residence of Śrī. Vā. 37. 13-15. 

श्रीविजया
Śrīvijayā --is Lalitā. Br. IV. 13. 4.

श्रीवृक्ष
Śrīvṛkṣa --near the Cītrakūṭa hill fit for Śrāddha. 1) Br. III. 13. 38. 2) Vā. 77. 38.

श्रिवृक्षक
Śrivṛkṣaka --a palace; see Padmaka. M. 269. 44.

श्रीशान्तकर्ण
Śrīśāntakarṇa(i) --a son of Kṛṣṇa, and father of Paurṇamāsa: ruled for 56 years. Bhā. XII. 1. 23; Br. III. 74. 162.

श्रीसूक्तम्
Śrīsūktam --in honour of Śrī; 1) Br. IV. 9. 77; Vi. I. 9. 101. to be uttered when founding temples. 2) M. 265. 24.

श्रीशैल
Śrīśaila --a Mt in Bhārata varṣa, sacred to Śiva. Rukmī addressed himself to this god: visited by Balarāma; 1) Bhā. V. 19. 16; X. 61. 23[1]; 79. 13. sacred to Lalitāpīṭha; 2) Br. IV. 44. 98. sacred to Goddess Mahādevī and the Pitṛs; 3) M. 13. 31; 22. 43. a part of the burning Tripura fell there. 4) Ib. 188. 79.

श्रीसोमनाथ
Śrīsomanātha --Candra (s.v.) arising out of Atri's eyes: 27 nakṣatras being his śaktis. Br. IV. 35. 54-5.

श्रुत
Śruta  (I)--a son of Bhagiratha (Suhotra-Vi. P.) and father of Nābha(ga). Bhā. IX. 9. 16; Br. III. 63. 169; Vā. 88. 160; Vi. IV. 4. 36.

श्रुत
Śruta  (II)--a son of Subhāṣaṇa, and father of Jaya. Bhā. IX. 13. 25. 

श्रुत
Śruta  (III)--a son of Kṛṣṇa and Kālindī. Bhā. X. 61. 14.

श्रुत
Śruta  (IV)--a son of Medhā. Br. II. 9. 59; Vā. 10. 35.

श्रुत
Śruta  (V)--a son of Svārociṣa Manu. Br. II. 36. 19.

श्रुत
Śruta  (VI)--a son of Suvarca. Vā. 89. 21.

श्रुतऋषि
Śrutaṛṣi --a learned Purāṇa reader. Vā. 99. 417.

श्रुतऋषि
Śrutaṛṣis --8000 in number, are born again and again and take up the arrangement of the Śamhitās; 1) Br. II. 33. 2; 35. 146; M. 145. 88. remembered 88,000 Samhitās which return again and again. 2) Vā. 59. 86; 61. 122.

श्रुतकर्मन्
Śrutakarman  (I)--a son of Sahadeva and Draupadī. Bhā. IX. 22. 30; M. 50. 52; Vi. IV. 20. 42.

श्रुतकर्मन्
Śrutakarman  (II)--a son of Chāyā and Mārtāṇḍa (sun); became later Śanaiścara. Br. III. 59. 48; Vā. 84. 50.

श्रुतकीर्ति
Śrutakīrti  (I)--a son of Arjuna and Draupadī. Bhā. IX. 22. 29; M. 50. 52; Vi. IV. 20. 42.

श्रुतकीर्ती
Śrutakīrtī  (II)--a daughter of Sura 1) Br. III. 71. 150 & 57; (Śūra and BhojāM. P.) and queen of Dhṛṣṭaketu Kaikeya; a paternal aunt of Kṛṣṇa, and mother of Bhadrā, married to Kṛṣṇa; also  mother of Anuvrata (Santardanā-Vi. P.) besides four other sons; a viramātā. 2) Bhā. IX. 24. 30 and 38; X. 58. 56; M. 46. 4-5; Vā. 96. 149; 156. 7; Vi. IV. 14. 31, 41-2.

श्रुतदेव
Śrutadeva  (I)--a Brahman follower of Kṛṣṇa; knew his yoga power; lived as householder in Mithilā, earning bread for the day and contented; was visited by Kṛṣṇa and was happy at the honour done to him. Bhā. I. 14. 32; II. 7. 45; X. 78. [95 (v) 1]; 86. 13 to 57.

श्रुतदेव
Śrutadeva  (II)--a siddha; attacked the Asura followers of Bali. Bhā. VI. 15. 15; VIII. 21. 17; X. 86. 13.

श्रुतदेव
Śrutadeva  (III)--a son of Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. 90. 34.

श्रुतदेवा
Śrutadevā --a daughter of Śūra; a sister of Vasudeva; wife of Vṛddhaśaman Kārūṣa (Vṛddhadharma, the kārūśa king-Vi. P.) mother of Dantavaktra (the great Asura). Bhā. IV. 24. 30 and 37; Br. III. 71; 150 and 156; Vā. 96. 149, 155; Vi. IV. 14. 31, 39, 40.

श्रुतदेवी
Śrutadevī --a daughter of Devaka and one of the seven wives of Vasudeva. M. 44. 73.

श्रुतधर
Śrutadhara --the companion who followed Puramjana to Uttara and Dakṣiṇa Pāñcāla; allegorically, the hearing. Bhā. IV. 25. 50-51; 29. 13.

श्रुतधर
Śrutadharas --a class of people in Śālmalidvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 11. 

श्रुतंजय
Śrutaṃjaya  (I)--a son of Satyāyu. Bhā. IX. 15. 2.

श्रुतंजय
Śrutaṃjaya  (II)--a Bṛhadratha; ruled for 24 years. Br. III. 74. 114.

श्रुतंजय
Śrutaṃjaya  (III)--ruled for 40 years. M. 271. 23; Vā. 99. 300.

श्रुतवर्मन्
Śrutavarman --a minister of Bhaṇḍa. Br. IV. 12. 53.

श्रुतविन्दा
Śrutavindā --a R. in Kuśadvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 15.

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (I)--a son of Somāpī; 1) Bhā. IX. 22. 9. ruled for 67 years; 2) Br. III. 74. 111. father of Ayutāyu. 3) Vi. IV. 23. 4.

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (II)--a son of Mārjāri, and father of Ayutāyu. Bhā. IX. 22. 46.

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (III)--a daughter of Śūra and Bhojā; 1) M. 46. 4, 6. a sister of Vasudeva and queen of Damaghoṣa, the Cedi king; 2) Bhā. IX. 24. 30 and 39; Br. III. 71. 150 and 158; Vi. IV. 14. 31, 44-5. mother of Śisupāla; a Vīramātā. 3) Vā. 96. 149, 157-8.

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (IV)--a son of Chāyā and the Sun god; was Sāvarṇi Manu. Br. III. 59. 48; Vā. 84. 50.

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (V)--a son of Somavit. M. 50. 34. 

श्रुतश्रवस्
Śrutaśravas  (VI)--(Māgadha) in the line of Somādhi (tasyānvaya) ruled for 64 years; this gap between Somādhi and Śrutaśravas seems to account for the discrepancy between the names given and the total No. 32 of the kings. M. 271. 20; Vā. 99. 228, 297.

श्रुतसेन
Śrutasena  (I)--a son of Śatrughna. Bhā. IX. 11. 12.

श्रुतसेन
Śrutasena  (II)--a son of Bhīma and Draupadī. Bhā. IX. 22. 29; M. 50. 52; Vi. IV. 20. 42.

श्रुतसेन
Śrutasena  (III)--a son of Parīkṣit. Bhā. IX. 22. 35; Vi. IV. 20. 1; 21. 3.

श्रुतादेवी
Śrutādevī --a daughter of Śūra and Bhojā, wife of Kṛta, and mother of Sugrīva. M. 46. 4-5.

श्रुतानीक
Śrutānīka --a son of Nakula by Draupadī. Vi. IV. 20. 42.

श्रुतायुस्
Śrutāyus  (I)--a son of Ariṣṭanemi and father of Supārśva(ka). Bhā. IX. 13. 23; Vi. IV. 5. 31.

श्रुतायुस्
Śrutāyus  (II)--a son of Purūravas and Ūrvaśī. Father of Vasumat. Bhā. IX. 15. 1 and 2; Br. III. 66. 23; Vi. IV. 7. 1.

श्रुतायुस्
Śrutāyus  (III)--a Vānara chief. Br. III. 7. 236. 

श्रुतायुस्
Śrutāyus  (IV)--a son of Bhānuścandra, was slain in the Bhārata battle. M. 12. 55.

श्रुतार्थकृत्
Śrutārthakṛt --a son of Jāmbavān. Br. III. 7. 303.

श्रुति
Śruti  (I)--the Vedas: interpreted in two ways in the Dvāpara; 1) Br. II. 31. 6, 72; 32, 35; IV. 6. 64; M. 52. 12; 144. 7; Vā. 34. 95; 39. 11; 41. 90; 55. 7; 61. 75; 76. 3; 100. 33; 101. 9, 22, 57. the same, Ṛg, Yajus, and Sāma in every manvantara though in different redactions; here are four stotras-Dravyastotram, Guṇastotram, Karmastotram, and Abhijanastotram; above all these is Brahmastotram; mantras were originally five fold; 2) M. 145. 58-63. having learnt the Śrauta from their predecessors the seven sages repeated the same. 3) Vā. 3. 8; 32. 44; 59. 31.

श्रुति
Śruti  (II)--a son of Uttama Manu. Br. II. 36. 40.

श्रुति
Śruti  (III)--a daughter of Anasūyā and mother of Śankhapadā, wife of Kardama, Pulaha Prajāpati. Vā. 28. 18, 27; Br. II. 11. 22.

श्रुति
Śrutis --awaken the Lord sleeping after a pralaya, as bards the emperor from his bed. Śrutigītā on the greatness and glory of Lord. Bhā. V. 87. 1, 12-41; XI. 5. 5.

श्रुतिकेवल
Śrutikevala --a ṛtvik at Brahmā's sacrifice. Vā. 106. 35.

श्रुतिपराग
Śrutiparāga --one of Bhaṇḍa's eight men. Br. IV. 12. 12. 

श्रुतिर्गृणान
Śrutirgṛṇāna --a deva. Br. II. 13. 96.

श्रुतिभेद
Śrutibheda --in dvāpara. Vā. 61. 76.

श्रुतिश्रव
Śrutiśravas --a son of Somapa; the last of the Māgadhas. Vi. IV. 19. 84-5.

श्रुतिशृन
Śrutiśṛna --a Śukradeva. Vā. 31. 9.

शृंगवत्
Śṛṃgavat --a Mt. range to the north of Ilāvṛta; a boundary limit of Kuru; from it descends the stream Bhadrā. Bhā. V. 16. 8; 17. 8.

श्रेणि
Śreṇis --military republics; 1) M. 273. 68. treated with respect by Pṛthu; help kings. 2) Bhā. IV. 17. 2; Br. III. 7. 264.

श्रेयोव्रतम्
Śreyovratam --leads to Śiva, salvation. M. 101. 70.

श्रेष्ट
Śreṣṭa --a Sudhāmāna god. Br. II. 36. 28.

श्रोणी
Śroṇī --a R. of the Bhāratavarṣa. Vā. 45. 100.

श्रोत
Śrota --the Yakṣa presiding over the month, Nabha. Bhā. XII. 11. 37.

श्रोतन
Śrotanas --of Kaśyapa gotra. M. 199. 3. 

श्रोतामन्त
Śrotāmanta --a god of Ādya group. Br. II. 36. 69.

श्रोतोगुणात्मक
Śrotoguṇātmakas --the three guṇas, satva, rajas and tamas revolve round and round among all worldly creatures. Vā. 102. 56.

श्रोत्रम्
Śrotram --a Tuṣita god. Br. III. 3. 19. Vā. 66. 18.

श्रोत्रि
Śrotri --guides the month of Nabhas. Bhā. XII. 11. 37.

श्रोत्रीय
Śrotrīya --eligible for Pārvaṇa śrāddha, as also his son. M. 16. 8; 105. 17; Vi. III. 15. 2.

श्रौत
Śrauta --from śravaṇa--to hear or heard; principally of the sacrifice and Veda. Vā. 59. 38.

श्रौतगेपि
Śrautagepi --an Ārṣeya Pravara of the Bhārgavas. M. 195. 38.

श्रौतम्
Śrautam Dharmam  and Smārta--promulgated by the seven sages and Manu at the commencement of the Tretā yuga; 1) Br. II. 29. 44-51; 32. 33-5. two-fold, dhārāgnihotrasambandham said in four days; hearing is śrauta; 2) Ib. II. 32. 33-5, 43, 44; III. 21. 47. lost in Arājaka; 3) Ib. II. 31. 95. the śruta consists of marriage, agnihotra, and Vedic studies; this is according to the Sapta ṛṣis. 4) Vā. 57. 39-40.

श्रौतस्मार्तम्
Śrautasmārtam --commences with Tretāyuga; originally told by seven sages; 1) M. 142. 40. it is called jñānadharma; characteristics  of; the one deals with sacrifices and the other with Varṇāśrama; 2) Ib. 144. 96; 145. 22, 30-31, 40. is lost towards the close of Kali (in Kali). 3) Ib. 273. 46; Vi. IV. 24. 98.

श्वनरक
Śvanaraka --a kind of hell. Vā. 101. 149.

श्वपाक
Śvapākas --Caṇḍālas; with minds controlled and resigned to Hari are better than Brahmans not devoted to God; were honoured by Kṛṣṇa; become pure by bhakti (also śvāda s.v.); 1) Bhā. I. 11. 22; VII. 9. 10; XI. 14. 21. meat eaters with whom Satyavrata-Triśanku lived. 2) Br. III. 63. 81; Vā. 88. 82.

श्वफल्क
Śvaphalka --a son of Vṛṣṇi; elder brother of Citraka; married Gāndinī, daughter of a Kāśī king. Akrūra was the foremost of his twelve sons. Kāśī, not visited by rains for long had a heavy shower just at his marriage, and during his stay at the invitation of the Kāśī king, whose daughter he married. A righteous king in whose kingdom there was neither famine nor disease. Bhā. III. 1. 32; IX. 24. 15; X. 38. 24; 57. 32; XI. 12. 10; Br. III. 71, 102; Vi. IV. 13. 115-16; 15. 5-7.

श्वभोजन
Śvabhojana --a hell; the abode of Vratins and Brahmacārins with an uncontrolled body, taught and disciplined by sons, and Brahmacāris that sleep during day time. Br. IV. 2. 149, 176; Vā. 101. 148, 173; Vi. II. 6. 5 and 29.

श्वमुख
Śvamukhas --the country of, watered by Nalinī. Br. II. 18. 60.

श्वर
Śvara --a son of Dadhīci. Vā. 21. 42. 

श्वलभ
Śvalabha --a Dānava. Br. III. 6. 12.

श्वशृप
Śvaśṛpa --a nephew of Hiraṇyakaśipu. M. 6. 27.

श्वा
Śvā --unfit to be seen during a śrāddha; touching it is a sin. Br. III. 14. 48; 78, 88; 27. 15; Vi. III. 16. 12.

श्वाजित
