Sadhyā --a wife of Dharma; sons known as Sādhyas, participators in yajña. Vā. 66. 2, 12.

सनक
Sanaka  (I)--a mind-born son of Brahmā; went on a visit to Vaikuṇṭha with his brothers; obstructed by Jaya and Vijaya, cursed them; and this was approved by Kṛṣṇa. His joy to see Hari; the avatār of Śiva; a son of Kanka; a celibate who waits on Hari; went with the latter to Pṛthu's sacrifice; was taught the knowledge of yoga by Hari in the form  of a Hamsa and in the presence of Brahmā; 2) Bhā. IV. 8. 1: 19. 6. 29 42; X. 39. 53; XI. 13. (whole). entered Umāvanam and seeing Śiva sporting with Umā, returned. 3) Br. III. 36. 5 and 52; 60. 23; IV. 15. 8 and 40; 39. 56; 47. 66. He and others formed the Sadasyas for Soma's Rājasūya; 4) M. 23. 21; 102. 17; 245. 77. got mokṣa through jñānam. 5) Vā. 24. 79. ^1 Bhā. III. 12. 4; 15. 12-13, 30 and 34; 16. 1-4, 25-28; Vā. 9. 72; 23. 131; 101. 337; 105. 2; Vi. VI. 4. 5.

सनक
Sanaka  (II)--Ārṣeya Pravara, (Bhārgavas). M. 195. 44.

सनति
