Sanatkumāra  (I)--a son of Brahmā and elder brother of Śiva; met by Pṛthu, he taught him ātmajñāna; one of the twelve who knew of Hari's dharma; did not comprehend his māyā; present at the anointing of Vāmana; praised the Lord and Aditi; 1) Bhā. I. 3. 6; III. 8. 3; 12. 4; IV. 16. 25; 17. 5. 22. 6, 18-40; 23. 9 and 41; VI. 3. 20; VIII. 23. 20, 26-7; IX. 4. 57; XI. 16. 25; M. 4. 27. with other sages serve the Ganges; 2) Ib. 160. 16. Bhagavān asked Nandikeśvara about the shrines where Maheśvara stands pillar like (Sthāṇu); 3) Ib. 141. 77; 162. 13; 181. 2-4. created first with Ṛbhu and Kratu; when born was called Kumāra; 4) Vā. 9. 72, 106; Br. I. 5. 79. a son of Kanka, an avatār of Śiva was under father's control; 5) Vā. 23. 132; 24. 79: 25. 92; 30. 85; 35. 45; 56. 86. one of the chief sages; 6) Ib. 5. 4. spoke to Aila on the śrāddha. 7) Vi. III. 14. 11.

