सनन्द
Sananda  (II)--a Brahmaṛṣi; water oblation to, after bath. M. 102. 17.

सनन्दन
Sanandana --a son of Brahmā; fit to contemplate on the glory of Kapila; came to see Trivikrama avatār of Viṣṇu; honoured for the Śrutigītā 1) Bhā. VIII. 21. 1; IX. 8. 24; X. 87. 12-13, 42; Vā. 9. 72; 101. 337. Vi. II. 7. 13. by the assembly members of Brahmā; 1) Bhā. VIII. 21. 1; IX. 8. 24; X. 87. 12-13, 42; Vā. 9. 72; 101. 337. Vi. II. 7. 13. a son of Kaṅka an avatār of Śiva; got mokṣa by jñānam; 2) Vā. 23. 131; 24. 79; Vi. I. 4. 27, 30; 7. 9; V. 18; 42; a perfect sage. 3) Ib. VI. 7. 50.

