Sanātana  (I)--a mind-born son of Brahmā; 1) Bhā. III. 12. 4; Vā. 9. 72; 101. 337. a son of Kaṅka, an avatār of Śiva; got mokṣa by jñānam; 2) Ib. 23. 131; 24. 79; 61. 155 and 161. a Brahmaṛṣi. 3) M. 102. 17. 

सनातन
Sanātana  (II)--an epithet of Viṣṇu. M. 248. 37.

