Sanātanadharma --the eternal dharma of all 1) Vā. 57. 116. comprises being faithful, not being covetous, tapas, pity to creatures, control, celibacy, truth, anukrośa, patience and courage. 2) Br. II. 30. 37-38; M. 143. 32.

