सप्तऋषि
Saptaṛṣis  (II)--the seven sages born on the earth in Dvāpara; conquered death by foregoing desire for progeny; were followed in the path of Ūrdhvaretasas by 88,000 others; all immortals decline after the deluge; 1) M. 124. 106-11. their permanent abode in front of Dhruva; 2) Br. II. 21. 168; 24. 122; 29. 17, 45; IV. 2. 134. M. 4. 37: 128. 74. Vi. II: 9. 10. a lakh of yojanas above Śanaiścara; 3) Vā. 53. 97: 101. 134: Vi. II. 7. 9. lived with Magha during the age of Parīkṣit; 4) M. 273. 39, 44. their one year = 3030 years of our reckoning; 5) Ib. 142. 13. Vā. 57. 18. gave out śrautadharma at the commencement of the Tretāyugam; 6) M. 142. 40-41; Br: II. 32. 34, 42, 91-4; 35. 103, 184, 189. remembered by Indra they went to Umā and Śiva and got their marriage celebrated; they tested Umā's firmness in her love in different ways and found her not wanting at all. 7) M. 154. 311-41.

सप्तऋषिशैल
Saptaṛṣiśaila --Mt., a hill. M. 163. 89.

