Samudgaka  (II)--16 sided in the shape of a small box; on its sides are candraśālas with two bhūmikas. M. 269. 38. 

समुद्र
Samudra  (I)--gave śankha to Pṛthu; the lavaṇa samudra encircles Jambūdvīpa. Bhā. IV. 15. 19: Br. II. 15. 13.

समुद्र
Samudra  (II)--Agni at Viśvasya (Viśvavyaca-Br. P.) located in Brahmasthāna. Vā. 29. 22: Br. II. 12. 24.

समुद्रप
Samudrapa --is Agastya. Br. IV. 36. 29.

समुद्रम्
Samudram --1,000×1,000×10 crores. Vā. 101. 97.

समुद्र
Samudras --the seven seas; source of the waters; 1) M. 2. 34. Vā. 27. 26: 56. 57. lord of rivers; 2) M. 8. 6. southern ocean sacred to Pitṛs; 3) Ib. 22. 39. rise as the moon waxes and go down as the moon wanes as also at moon rising and setting every day; the rise is estimated to be about 115 inches in height; 4) Ib. 123. 32-4. the residence of the Lord. 5) Vā. 97. 22.

समुद्रमाला
Samudramālā --a R. of the Ketumālā continent. Vā. 44. 20.

समुद्रयायि
Samudrayāyi --one who has crossed the seas. Vā. 83. 62.

समुद्रसेन
Samudrasena --a Kinnara gaṇa; horsefaced. Vā. 69. 32.

समुद्रान्तरक
Samudrāntarakas --a Janapada of the Ketumālā continent. Vā. 44. 10. 

समूल
Samūla --a Mt. south of the Mānasa. Vā. 36. 23: 38. 23: 42. 30.

सञ्जय
Sañjaya  (I)--a son of Kolāhala. M. 48. 11.

सञ्जय
Sañjaya  (II)--a son of Raṇejaya (Raṇamjaya-Vā. P. and Vi. P.). M. 271. 11: Vā. 99. 288: Vi. IV. 22. 8.

सञ्जय
Sañjaya  (III)--the name of Vyāsa of the sixteenth dvāpara; Gokarṇa, the avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 171.

सञ्जय
Sañjaya  (IV)--the father of Jaya. Vā. 93. 8.

संजय
Saṃjaya --son of Pratikṣatra. Vi. IV. 9. 26.

संजाति
Saṃjāti --a son of Buhugavī. Vā. 99. 122.

संजीविनि
Saṃjīvini(vidyā) --a science which enables one to bring the dead back to life; known to Śukrācārya and not known to Bṛhaspati; learnt as a disciple from Śukra by Kaca son of Bṛhaspati; revived Kaca done to death twice by the Asuras. M. 25. 13, 36, 54, 65: 27. 19: 249. 4.

संजेय
Saṃjeya --a son of Kūti; father of Mahiṣmat. Vā. 94. 5.

संज्ञा
Saṃjñā  (I)--daughter of Viśvakarman (Tvaṣṭ(r)a-M. and Br. P.); consort of Sūrya (Vivasvat-Bhā. P.) gave birth to Manu, Yama and Yamī; unable to bear the effulgence of  her husband, she engaged Chāyā, her servant maid, to take her place, and left for penance; to Chāyā were born Śanaiścara, Manu (Sāvarṇi), Tapatī; finding fault with Yama once the Sun god discovered Chāyā's identity and after a search found Samjñā doing penance as a mare in the plains of Uttarakuru; 1) Bhā. VIII. 13. 8-9: VI. 6. 40: IX. 1. 11: M. 11. 2 and 24-37; Vā 84. 21; 100. 31. he became a horse in turn and Samjñā as a mare gave birth to three more children; the two Aśvins and Revanta; Viśvakarma filed off the Vaiṣṇava effulgence and out of this he crafted the discus of Viṣṇu, the trident of Śiva, the Puṣpakavimāna of Kubera the lance (Śakti) of Kārtikeya and others. 2) Br. II. 24. 90: III. 59. 22-3; IV. 1. 28: Vi. III. 2. 2-12.

संज्ञा
Saṃjñā  (II)--a Śakti. Br. IV. 44. 87.

संज्ञेय
Saṃjñeya --a son of Kunti and father of Mahiṣmat. Br. III. 69. 5.

सम्पति
Sampati --a son of Aruṇa and Gṛdhri; father of Vijaya and Prasaha. Br. III. 7. 447.

सम्पत्करी
Sampatkarī --managed the elephant corps in the war with Bhaṇḍa. Br. IV. 16. 7-13: 22. 37.

सम्पत्सरस्वती
Sampatsarasvatī --offered fight to Durmada. Br. IV. 22. 36-66.

सम्पदिशा
Sampadiśā --see Sampatkarī. Br. IV. 28. 38. 

सम्पद्वसु
Sampadvasu --one of the seven important rays of the sun. Br. II. 24. 66.

सम्पद्व्रतम्
Sampadvratam --in honour of Lakṣmī. M. 101. 20.

सम्पाति
Sampāti  (I)--a son of Supratīka elephant. Br. III. 7. 341.

सम्पाति
Sampāti  (II)--a son of Aruṇa and Śyeni and father of Babhru and Sighraga; a fabulous bird and brother of Jaṭāyu. M. 6. 35: Vā. 69. 327.

सम्पाति
Sampāti  (III)--a son of Bahuvidha. M. 49. 3.

सम्पार
Sampāra --a son of Samara. M. 49. 54.

सम्बाधि
Sambādhi --a Pravara. M. 196. 30.

सम्बुद्ध
Sambuddhas --the enlightened like Ṛbhu and Sanatkumāra. Vā. 101. 212.

सम्बूत
Sambūta --a son of Yuvanāśva and Narmadā; father of Anaraṇya. Br. III. 63. 73.

सम्बूति
Sambūti --an elephant daughter of dig-nāgas. Br. III. 7. 354. 

सम्बोधनी
Sambodha(i)nī --a daughter of Jāmbavatī and Kṛṣṇa. Br. III. 71. 250; Vā. 96. 241.

सम्भटा
Sambhaṭā --the goddess following Revatī. M. 179. 72.

सम्भव
Sambhava  (I)--a son of Sarva. M. 50. 31.

सम्भव
Sambhava  (II)--at the end of samhāra; impossible to be told in detail; also nisarga. Vā. 61. 136-7.

सम्भवख
Sambhavakhas --a Janapada of the Bhadrā continent. Vā. 43. 21.

सम्भवपीता
Sambhavapītā --Maheśvara, father of creation. Vā. 103. 37.

सम्भाव्य
Sambhāvya --a son of Raivata. Vi. III. 1. 23.

सम्भु
Sambhu --a son of Śuka. Vā. 70. 85.

सम्भूत
Sambhūta --a son of Ṭrasadasyu and father of Anaraya. Vā. 88. 74-75.

सम्भूत
Sambhūtas --sons of Meru Sāvarṇi. Vā. 100. 59.

सम्भूती
Sambhūtī  (I)--a wife of Vairāja. Bhā. VIII. 5. 9. 

सम्भूती
Sambhūtī  (II)--a wife of Jayadratha. Bhā. IX. 23. 12.

सम्भूती
Sambhūtī  (III)--a son of Vasuda. M. 12. 36.

सम्भूती
Sambhūtī  (IV) (Sambhṛtī)--a daughter of Dakṣa and wife of (Pulaha) (Vi. P.) Marīci; mother of Pūrṇamāsa and four daughters. Vi. I. 7. 7, 25; Br. II. 9. 52 and 55; 11. 11; Vā. 10. 27, 30; 28. 9; Vi. I. 10. 6.

सम्भूती
Sambhūtī  (V)--the mother of Hari in the Raivata epoch. Vi. III. 1. 40.

सम्भूती
Sambhūtīs--divya avatārs;  Nārāyaṇa, Narasimha and Vāmana; manuṣya avatārs seven due to Bhṛgu's curse; Dattātreya, Māndhāta, Jamadagni, Rāma, Vedavyāsa, Kṛṣṇa and Kalki. Vā. 98. 88-104.

सम्भ्रम
Sambhrama  (I)--a gaṇa in the service of Kubera. M. 180. 98.

सम्भ्रम
Sambhrama  (II)--a son of Śatarūpā. M. 4. 25.

सम्मति
Sammati --a main stream of Kuśadvīpa. Vi. II. 4. 43. 

सम्मद
Sammada --the King of fish with a number of children and grandchildren, observed by sage Saubhari who turned to the life of a house-holder from that of penance. Vi. IV. 2. 70.

सम्मर्दन
Sammardana --a son of Vasudeva and Devakī. Bhā. IX. 24. 54.

सम्मूह
Sammūha --a Marut of the 6th gaṇa. Br. III. 5. 97.

सम्यद्वसु
Samyadvasu --one of the best seven rays of the sun; the root of Agni. Vā. 53. 45, 48.

सम्यम
Samyama  (I)--the son of Dhūmrākṣasa and father of Kṛśāśva and Devaja. Bhā. IX. 2. 34.

सम्यम
Samyama  (II)--a Yāma deva. Br. II. 13. 92.

सम्यमनी
Samyamanī(ā) --the city of Yama, south of Meru; 1) Bhā. V. 21. 7; VI. 3. 3; Br. II. 21: 31; M. 124. 22; Vā. 50. 88. reached by Kṛṣṇa and Balarāma to recover the dead son of Sāndīpani; 2) Vi. II. 8. 9; Bhā. X. 45. 42-46. visited by Arjuna to recover the dead child of Dvārakā Brāhmaṇa. 3) Ib. X. 89. 43.

