Samrāṭ  (I)--a son of Citraratha and Ūrṇā; had a son Marīci on Utkalā. Bhā. V. 15. 14-15.

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ  (II)--Vairāja Puruṣa; got that name as having assumed the form of Sāma; also Vairāja Manu (see Vairāja). Br. II. 9. 39; Vā. 10. 15; 94. 23.

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ  (III)--the daughter of Kardama, the progenitor. Br. II. 14. 8.

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ  (IV)--the title of a king who conquers all Bhāratavarṣa; 1) Br. II. 16. 16; M. 114. 15. Vā. 45. 86; the title of Hariscandra after his Rājasūya, 2) Ib. 88. 118. of Kārtavīrya. 3) Br. III. 16. 23. 

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ  (V)--a daughter of Priyavrata. Vā. 33. 8; Vi. II. 1. 5.

सम्राट्
Samrāṭ (ḍ) agni --also Kṛśānu--one of the 8 Agnis worshipped by Brahmans. Br. II. 12. 21; Vā. 29. 19.

