Samvatsara  (II)--a part of the five-year yuga; 1) Bhā. III. 11. 14; V. 22. 7; Vi. II. 8. 71-2. a year, the first among years; is Agni; represented by Kāvya pitṛs; 2) Br. II. 21. 131; 24. 57, 141; 28. 15; III. 8. 17; 72. 30. of different kinds--dīvyasamvatsara, Dhruvasamvatsara, Pitṛsamvatsara, and Saptaṛṣisamvatsara. 3) Ib. II. 28. 21; 29. 10, 16 and 18.

सम्वत्सर
Samvatsara  (III)--a Śakti. Br. IV. 32. 15.

सम्वत्सर
Samvatsara  (IV)--is Agni. M. 141. 18.

सम्वत्सर
Samvatsara  (V)--Vārāha Viṣṇu got the form of. Vā. 23. 104.

संवरण
Saṃvaraṇa --a son of Ṛkṣa; and husband of Tapatī, and father of Kuru. Bhā. VI. 6. 41; VIII. 13. 10; IX. 22. 3-4. M. 50. 20; Vā. 99. 214; Vi. IV. 19. 75-6.

