Samvarta  (I)--a son of Angiras, and a yogin; helped Marutta in his yajñas; 1) Bhā. IX. 2. 26; Vā. 65. 101. enabled Prāmśu's son to go to Heaven. 2) Br. III. 61. 5. 

सम्वर्त
Samvarta  (II)--a son of Svarūpa and a gotrakāra; 1) M. 196. 4. attained salvation at Benares. 2) Ib. 180. 63.

सम्वर्त
Samvarta  (III)--a priest of Maruttacakravarti who went bodily to heaven with all his relations and Marutta taking yajña with him; hence Bṛhaspati got angry with him as he anticipated the destruction of the world. Vā. 86. 9, 11.

सम्वर्तक
Samvartaka  (I)--a group of clouds ordered by Indra to inundate Gokula; 1) Bhā. X. 25. 2-7. Pralaya clouds. 2) M. 2. 8; Vā. 77. 7; 100. 156.

सम्वर्तक
Samvartaka  (II)--also Aurva and Vaḍavāmukha; 1) Br. II. 7. 9; 12. 35-6; 22. 43; 25. 45, 55. the fire that consumes waters; the pralaya fire; 2) Ib. IV. 1. 152; 2. 50. Vā. 6. 29; 54. 57 son of Manyumān Agni. 3) Ib. 29. 33.

सम्वर्त्त
Samvartta --a son of Pathya and Atharvāngiras. Br. III. 1. 106.

सम्वर्त्तकस्
Samvarttakas --massive clouds like elephants and of different colours pouring down rain for 100 years during the period of dissolution. Vi. V. 11. 1; VI. 3. 31.

सम्वह
Samvaha --the chief of the fourth Vātaskandha. Br. III. 5. 85; M. 163. 32.

संवेध
Saṃvedhas --with Bṛhaspati in rāśi. Br. II. 23. 87. 

संशय
Saṃśaya --a son of Unmāda and grandson of Nārāyaṇa and Śrī. Br. II. 11. 4.

संश्रुत
Saṃśruta --a Trayārṣeya. M. 198. 4.

संसद्
Saṃsad --an assembly. Vā. 30. 120; 83. 106.

संसार
Saṃsāra --compared to an ocean; the evils of family life as explained by the king of mountains; the necessity of children, the difficulty and anxiety in procuring good husbands for daughters, etc; 1) M. 55. 27; 154. 145-174; Vā. 101. 195-204. the duhham of, explained. 2) Vi. VI. 5. 10-56.

संसारम्
Saṃsāram --(tāmasa) of six kinds--man, animal (paśu), beast (mṛga), bird (pakṣi), snake (sarīsṛpu) and vegetation (sthāvara); sātvikam: Brahmā and others; rājasam--the intervening viṣṭambhaka among the 14 sthānas. Vā. 14. 35-41; 100. 203.

संसारमण्डलम्
Saṃsāramaṇḍalam --of fourteen kinds. Vā. 15. 1.

संसारमोचनम्
Saṃsāramocanam --a tīrtha sacred to Pitṛs. M. 22. 67.

संसिद्धकरण
Saṃsiddhakaraṇa --a son of Yakṣa and Kratusthali. Vā. 69. 142.

संस्कार
Saṃskāras --purificatory rites for house-holders; these do not help without the eight ātmaguṇas (s.v. Kriyā yoga). M. 52. 17, 30. 

सम्हत
Samhata --a son of Kuntī. M. 43. 9.

सम्हताश्व
Samhatāśva --a son of Nikumbha; 1) Br. III. 63. 64. M. 12. 33 well-versed and possessed of prowess in war; had two sons Kṛśāśva and Akṣayāśva. 2) Vā. 88. 63.

सम्हार
Samhāra  (I)--a Bhairava god on the sixth parva of Geyacakra. Br. IV. 19. 79.; 20. 92.

सम्हार
Samhāra  (II)--the pralaya at the end of Kaliyuga; first covering by waters, next by tejas, then by ākāśa, then by bhūtadi, then by mahat, and lastly by avyakta; 1) Vā. 21. 11; 102. 4, 27-31; the period ending all manvantaras, each continuing for several yugas; 2) Vā. 100. 118; impossible to be told in detail. 3) Vā. 61. 126-27.

सम्हारम्
Samhāram pādam --the fourth pāda of the Purāṇa; 1) Br. IV. 1. 2-5, 3. 4. of the Vā. P. of 1,000 ślokas, represents the Kali yuga. 2) Vā. 32. 64; 100. 2 and 5.

सम्हिता
Samhitā --Vedic texts; 1) Br. II. 29. 52; 31. 11-13. M. 264. 23; Vā. 58. 13; 104. 86. three Samhitās composed by eight sages. 2) Ib. 61. 1-2, 4, 121.

सम्हूती
Samhūtī --(Sadvatī)? A wife of Agni and mother of Parjanya. Vā. 28. 16.

सम्हृति
Samhṛti --a Mantrakṛt of the Angirasa branch. Vā. 59. 98. 

सम्ह्राद
Samhrāda --a son of Hiraṇyakaśipu, wife Kṛti, and father of Pañcajana. Bhā. VI. 18. 13-14; Br. III. 5-34; Vā. 67. 70.

सम्ह्लाद
Samhlāda --a son of Hiraṇyakaśipu; his sons were Nivātakavacās; not to be killed by Devas, Gandharvas, Uragas, Rākṣasas; but killed by Arjuna by the grace of Śiva. M. 6. 9, 28-9.

सर
Sara --a Vānara chief. Br. III. 7. 232.

सरघा
Saraghā --the queen of Bindumat and mother of Madhu. Bhā. V. 15. 15.

सरमा
Saramā  (I)--(Sārama); the messenger of Indra, of whom the Dānavas were afraid. Bhā. V. 24. 30.

सरमा
Saramā  (II)--one of Kaśyapa's wives. Her offspring were beasts of prey. Bhā. VI. 6. 26.

सरमाण
Saramāṇa --a nephew of Hiraṇyakaśipu. M. 6. 27.

सरयू
Sarayū --(Mahānadī) R. in Bhāratavarṣa; its source was visited by Balarāma who then travelled to Prayāgā along its bank. The river of Ayodhyā; Asamanjasa used to throw into it the children who were his playmates. 1) Bhā. V. 19. 18; IX. 8. 17; X. 79. 9-10; Br. III. 12. Ib. 15; III. 51. 65; 55. 11; Vā. 108. 79; R. from the Himālayas; 2) Br. II. 16. 25. sacred tīrtha; 3) M. 22. 19. one of the 16 rivers married by Havyavāhana; 4) Ib. 51. 14; Vā. 29. 14. in the Vaidyuta hill and has its source in the Mānasa lake; 5) Br. II. 18. 15 and 70; M. 114. 21; 121. 17. a Rākṣasa named Brahmapāda lived in  the forest here called Vaibhrājyam; 6) Vā. 45. 95; 47. 15. in the chariot of Tripurāri. 7) M. 133. M; 163. 60.

सरव
Sarava --a southern kingdom. Br. II. 16. 57.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (I)--(Vāk Devī); Viśvarūpā, a mind-born daughter of Brahmā who began to love her. Being criticised by his sons for it, he gave up his body in shame. Presented Pṛthu with a wreath, and was offered a wreath of pearls by Viśvakarman. Gave away a string of beads to the Lord. Gave Vīṇa to Kumāra; a Mother goddess. 2) Br. III. 10. 47; 35. 44. IV. 7. 72; 19. 70, 73; 20. 101; 36. 19; 40. 8; The Goddess of Learning; 3) M. 1. 2; enshrined in the faces of Brahmā, 4) Ib. 13. 52; Gāyatrā 5) Ib. 246. 57; in the 23rd Kalpa; constitutes 32 akṣaras; is prakṛti and Gaulī, 6) Vā. 23. 38; source of all worlds; 7) Ib. 23. 54-5; of four feet. 8) Ib. 23. 88; Presented to Skanda a great vīra. 9) Ib. 72. 45. ^1 Bhā. I. 24; III. 12, 28 and 33; IV. 15. 16. VIII. 8. 16; Br. II. 26. 45, M. 3. 32. 171. 33; 260. 44.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (II)--(Mahānadī) R. in Bhāratavarṣa of Brahmāvarta, in Kurukṣetra. Here Ūrvaśī enjoyed water sports with her companions when Purūravas found her a second time. 1) Bhā. I. 4. 15; IV. 19. 1; V. 19. 18; IX. 14. 33. II. 9. 44; Br. II. 12. 16; Vā. 45. 95; 55. 43; 108. 59, 78; 109. 21; The Brahmanadī; on its banks Vyāsa composed the Bhārata, and his hermitage was on the western bank. Here he heard the Bhāgavata from Nārada. 2) Bhā. I. 4. 27; 7. 2. Here Paraśurāma had his avabhṛta bath. 3) Ib. IX. 16. 23. On its banks was the Ambikāvana. 4) Ib. X. 34. 2 and 4. Here sages practised tapas. At its source Pṛthu performed a hundred aśvamedhas. 5) Ib. IV. 14. 36; 16. 24. Lies on the way from Dvārakā to Hāstinapura. Flows west at Prabhāsa; was made to flow back towards a desert where Ambarīṣa performed sacrifices. 6) Ib. X. 71. 22; IX. 30. 6; IX. 4. 22. When the sages per formed yajña on its bank, a question arose as to who was the superior god in the world. Bhṛgu, the son of Brahmā was deputed to find this out. 7) Ib. X. 89. 1-2. Here are eleven places sacred to Trīta, Uśanas, Manu and others. Vidura had his ablutions in all of them. 8) Bhā. III: 1. 21-22. Kṛṣṇa sat under an aśvatta tree on its banks preparing to leave off mortal coil and asked Uddhava to go to Badarī. 9) Ib. III. 4. 3-8. On its banks Kardama performed austerities for 10,000 years. Its banks filled with hermitages, one was Kardama's. In it Devahūtī bathed. 10) Ib. III. 21. 6; 22. 27. 23. 25. 24: 9: Visited by Balarāma. 11) Ib. X. 78. 18-19. Parīkṣit came to hear Dharma at the place where the R. flows East, complaining to Earth on the advent of Kali. 12) Ib. I. 16. 37. Defined. 13) VIII. 4. 23-4. From the Himālayas; fit for śrāddha offerings; 14) Br. II. 16: 24: 27; III. 13. 69; 14. 83; Vi. III. 14. 18. a holy river; 15) M. 7. 3. sacred to pitṛs; flows from the slopes of the Hemakūṭa hill; 16) Ib. 22. 23. flows through Kurukṣetra; 17) Ib. 121: 64-5; 186. 10; 229. 3. scene of talk between Garga and Atri. 18) Ib. 239. 18. sacred to Devamāta; 19) Ib. 13. 44; in the chariot of Tripurāri. 20) Ib. 114. 20; 133. 24.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (III)--a R. in Śālmalidvīpa. Bhā. V. 20. 10.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (IV)--the mother of Sārvabhauma--Hari. Bhā. VIII. 13. 17.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (V)--a wife of Pūrṇamāsa; sons, Viraja and Parvasa. Br. II. 11. 12; Vā. 28. 10. 

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (VI)--a wife of Dadhīci. Br. III. 1. 94; Vā. 65. 91.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (VII)--a Laukikya Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 10.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (VIII)--a Varṇaśakti; worships Kāmākṣī. Br. IV. 39. 14; 44. 57 and 71.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (IX)--the mother of Danu and Diti by Āditya. M. 171. 57.

सरस्वती
Sarasvatī  (X)--a Mt. in the Himālayas. Vā. 23. 168.

सरस्वती
