Sālva --(also Śālva); in Duryodhana's army; was stationed by Jarāsandha at the western gate of Mathurā, during one siege, and at the Eastern gate during the other. Attacked the south when Gomanta was besieged. 1) Bhā. X. 78 [95 (v) 16]; 50. 11 [5], [2]; 52. 11 [8]. Was defeated and killed by Kṛṣṇa in Vaidarbhī svayamvara; arrived at Kuṇḍina. 2) Ib. X. 52; 17 and 19; 42 [1]; 53. 17; Vā. 98. 100.

