Sāvitrī  (IV)--Brahmā contemplated her in his mind when engaged in creation; at that time a being half male and half female broke through his body and it was named Śatarūpā; 1) M. 3. 30. also called Sarasvatī, Gāyatrī and Brahmāṇī; 2) Ib. 4. 10; 187. 45; 260. 44. Viśvarūpā with two feet; came out by cutting through the head of Brahmā. 3) Vā. 23. 78, 91.

