सिनी
Sinī(vālī)  (IV)--left her consort Kardama and loved Soma with 8 other Devis; a devī attending on Soma. M. 23. 34; Br. III. 65, 26; Vā. 90. 25.

सिनीवाली
Sinīvālī (v) --a son of Anuhrada. Vā. 67. 75.

सिन्धव
Sindhavas --The seas which issue from the urethra of Brahmā. Bhā. III. 12. 26.

सिन्धु
Sindhu  (I)--a R. in Bhārata varṣa: The region round about fell into the hands of Vrātyas and others; 1) Bhā. V. 19. 18; XII. 1. 39; Vā. 45. 97. a mahānadī: falls into the western ocean: fit for śrāddha. 2) Ib. 47. 39; 69. 241; 77. 56, 113; 108. 79.

सिन्धु
Sindhu  (II)--(c). Its king was Jayadratha, who was a contemporary of Jarāsandha: was stationed on the east of Gomanta during the siege. Bhā. X. 52. 11 [6]. 

सिन्धु
Sindhu  (III)--a Kṣetram in Prayāgā. M. 110. 1.

सिन्धु
Sindhu  (IV)--one of the three branches of the Gangā from the Pāriyātra hill flowing to the north; 1) M. 114. 20; 121. 40; Br. II. 16. 24, 27. in the chariot of Tripurāri; 2) M. 133. 23; 163. 62. flows through the kingdoms of Darada, Kāśmīra, Gāndhāra and others: falls into the western ocean; 3) Br. II. 18. 41, 46-7; III. 13. 121. noted for Padma elephants; 4) Ib. III. 7. 358. north and south of, unfit for śrāddha; 5) Ib. III. 14. 33 and 81. confluence of, with the sea holy. 6) Ib. III. 13. 57.

सिन्धुक
Sindhuka --an Āndhra: overcame the Kaṇva Suśarman (Śunga) and began the Āndhra line: ruled for 23 years. Br. III. 74. 161; Vā. 99. 348-9.

सिन्धुतट
Sindhutaṭa --the region of the Indus; ruled by Mlecchas. Vi. IV. 24. 69.

सिन्धुदेश
Sindhudeśa --noted for war horses. Br. IV. 16. 16.

