Simhas --born of Hari and Pulaha; as a son of Jāmbavān, a vānara jāti; 1) Br. III. 7. 176, 304, 319; 22. 19; 26. 30; IV. 6. 50. a golden image of, as a gift for vīravratam of women; 2) M. 101. 28. the riding animal of Lalitā; 3) Br. III. 35. 38; 51. 10; IV. 17. 8; 29. 41. born out of the wrath of Śiva and destroyed Dakṣa's sacrifice. 4) Vā. 101. 295.

सिम्हघोष
Simhaghoṣa --a son and commander of Bhaṇḍa. Br. IV. 21. 81; 26. 48.

