Simhala --an Upadvīpa to Jambūdvīpa; 1) Bhā. V. 19. 30. the modern Ceylon: to be conquered by Kalki. 2) Br. II. 31. 82; III. 73. 107; M. 144. 56.

सिम्हल
Simhalas --Ceylonese. Vā. 58. 82; 98. 107.

सिम्हस्थ
Simhastha Bṛhaspati --When Guru is in Simha (this only once in every twelve years) Gayāśrāddham not to be omitted. Vā. 105. 19.

