सिम्हिका
Simhikā  (II)--a daughter of Dakṣa; 1) M. 171. 29. a goddess enshrined at Kṛtaśauca. 2) Ib. 13. 45. 

सिरालक
Sirālaka --a son of Bhaṇḍa. Br. IV. 26. 48.

सिलिन्ध्र
Silindhras--(c)  a western kingdom watered by the Sītā. Br. II. 18. 44.

सीता
Sītā  (I)--a branch of the Gangā issuing from the city of Brahmā: descends Kesara and other hills, falls on the summits of Gandhamādana, and traversing the continent of Bhadrāśva, falls into the Eastern Ocean; 1) Bhā V. 17. 5-6; Br. II. 12. 16; 18. 22, 41-5; 26. 44; III. 56. 52; Vā. 42. 17-35; 47. 39, 43; 55. 42; Vi. II. 2. 34-5; 8. 113. rises out of the Sitānta slopes of the Mukuñja hill, flows through Sumañjasa, Mālyavata, Vaikanka, Maṇiparvatam, Ṛṣabham, Jaṭhara, Devakūṭa, and reaches through the Gandhamādana and takes the name of Alakanandā and enters the Mānasa lake.

सीता
Sītā  (II)--The goddess enshrined at Citrakūṭa. M. 13. 39.

सीता
Sītā  (III)--a R. of Kuśadvīpa. M. 122. 71.

सीता
Sītā  (IV)--wife of Havyavāhana. Vā. 29. 14.

सीता
Sītā  (V)--the supernatural daughter of Janaka; 1) Vi. IV. 4. 92-3; 5. 28; is Lakṣmī; the wife of Rāma; 2) Vā. 106. 58; Vi. I. 9. 144; was discovered by Sīradhvaja when ploughing the earth for a sacrifice. 3) Vā. 88. 195; 89. 15; 108. 19 and 25. In her svayamvara, Rāma broke the dhanus of Śiva. Ravished by her beauty Rāvaṇa took her to Lankā and kept her under a śimśupa tree. Recovered by Rāma. Ever devoted to her lord, enjoyed his company at the capital. In the sacrifices she gave away all her things as gifts except saumāngalya.  Bore the water jar when Bharata carried the Pādukā. 4) Bhā. V. 19. 1-5; IX. 10. 3; 13. 18; XI. 4. 21; Br. III. 63. 196; Bhā. IX. 10. 6-30. 44 & 56; 11. 4 and 35; X. 71. 9: 83. 10; Respect of, to Brahmanas and elders; was sent to Vālmīki's hermitage though pregnant as Rāma heard a citizen speak ill of her stay in Rāvaṇa's palace; gave birth to Kuśa and Lava. After entrusting her sons to the care of the sage, she entered the bowels of the earth. 5) IX. 10. 41 and 47: 11. 10-15.

सीताद्रि
Sītādri --a Mt. in Gayāśilā. Vā. 108. 56.

सीतारामाश्रम
Sītārāmāśrama --sacred to Hari. Bhā VII. 14. 32.

सीतेरजा
Sīterajā --a R. of the Bhāratavarṣa. Vā. 45. 101.

सीतोदम्
