Sugrīva  (I)--a friend of Rāma. Dvivida was one of his ministers. Helped Rāma in his expedition to Lankā. Held the chauri when Bharata carried the Pādukā. Attained salvation by satsanga; 1) Bhā. IX. 10. 16, 19 & 43; X. 67. 2; XI. 12. 6. the son of Viraja and Sūrya: Rumā was his queen: younger brother of Vāli; 2) Br. III. 7. 215, 220 & 70. present at Rāma's abhiṣeka; 3) Vi. IV. 4. 100. to be worshipped before commencing the construction of a palace. 4) M. 268. 15

सुग्रीव
Sugrīva  (II)--the name of a horse of the chariot of Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. 53. 5; 70. 14; 89. 49.

सुग्रीव
Sugrīva  (III)--a son of Śrutadevī and Kṛta. M. 46. 5. 

सुग्रीव
Sugrīva  (IV)--the name of a son of Garuḍa on the Vaikanka hill. Vā. 39. 40.

सुग्रीव
Sugrīva  (V)--a king of Kinnaras; a gaṇa, all of them horse-faced, and going after his name Vā. 41. 30; 69. 32.

सुग्रीवि
Sugrīvi --a daughter of Tāmrā and Kaśyapa; mother of sheep, horses, camels and asses. M. 6. 30, 33; Vi. I. 21. 15, 17.

