Sucandra  (II)--a son of Krodhā and a Devagandharva; father of Dhūmrāśva. Br. III. 6. 39; Vā. 68. 39; 86. 18.

सुचन्द्र
Sucandra  (III)--a son of Devajanī: an Yakṣa. Br. III. 7. 129.

सुचन्द्र
Sucandra  (IV)--of the solar race: an ally of Kārtavīrya: an able soldier: Attacking him, Paraśurāma remembered Bhadrakālī and vanquished him: father of Puṣkarākṣa. Br. III. 39. 18, 50; 40. 1. 

सुचन्द्र
Sucandra  (V)--a son of king Hemacandra. Br. III. 61. 13.

सुचन्द्र
Sucandra  (VI)--a son of Kṛṣṇa given to the sonless Karūṣa in adoption. M. 46. 25.

सुचारु
Sucāru  (I)--a son of Rukmiṇī and Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. 61. 8; M. 47. 16; Vi. V. 28. 2.

सुचारु
Sucāru  (II)--a son of Pratibāhu. Vā. 96. 251; Vi. IV. 15. 42.

सुचिति
Suciti --a Jayādeva. Br. III. 4. 2.

सुचित्ति
Sucitti --a mantrakṛt. M. 145. 104.

सुचित्र
Sucitra --a Śiva god. Br. II. 36. 33.

सुचिन्त
Sucinta --a Ṛṣika. M. 145. 96.

सुचिरथ
Suciratha --a son of Vicitraratha and father of Vṛṣṇimat. Vi. IV. 21. 11-12.

सुचिरा
Sucirā --a Mother Goddess. M. 179. 29. 

