Sucīrā (Sucārā B) --a daughter of Śvaphalka. Bhā. IX. 24. 17.

सुच्छाया
Succhāyā --a daughter of Agni and wife of Śiṣṭa, (ŚiṣṭiVi. P.). M. 4. 38; Vi. I. 13. 1.

सुजंघ
Sujaṃgha --the first of several sons of Dattāli; all known as Paulastyas. Vā. 28. 24.

सुजङ्घी
Sujaṅghī --a wife of Dānāgni: many sons all Paulastyas. Br. II. 11. 29.

सुजन
Sujana --a son of Bhṛgu. M. 195. 12.

सुजय
Sujaya --a Bhavya god. Br. II. 36. 71.

सुजात
Sujāta --a Vānara chief and a son of Śveta. Br. III. 7, 181.

सुजाता
Sujātā --a Brahmavādinī. Br. II. 33. 19.

सुजातेय
Sujāteyas --belonging to Trayārṣeya. M. 198. 7.

सुजारक
Sujārakas --a tribe. Vā. 45. 122. 

सुज्येष्ठ
Sujyeṣṭha --a son of Agnimitra, and father of Vasumitra; 1) Bhā. XII. 16. 17. Vi. IV. 24. 35. ruled for seven years. 2) Br. III. 74. 151.

सुतमि
Sutami --a son of Ugrasena. Br. III. 71. 133. Vā. 96. 132.

सुतनू
Sutanū  (I)--a daughter of Ugrasena, the Kāśi king, and a wife of Vasudeva, mother of Pauṇḍraka. Bhā. X. 66. [5]; Br. III. 71. 134; M. 44. 76; 46. 21; Vi. IV. 14. 21.

सुतनू
Sutanū  (II)--a daughter of Yudhiṣṭhira; married Aśvasuta, son Vajra. Vā. 96. 250.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (I)--the gods of the eighth manvantara: one of the three devagaṇas of the first Sāvarṇi Manu, twenty in number. Bhā. VIII. 13. 12; Br. IV. 1. 12, 14 & 15. Vā. 100. 13-15.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (II)--a son of Antarikṣa and father of Amitrajit. Bhā. IX. 12. 12.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (III)--a son of Hema, and father of Bali. Bhā. IX. 23. 4; Br. III. 74. 25; Vi. IV. 18. 12.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (IV)--the progenitor and husband of Pṛśni of the Svāyambhuva epoch. Bhā. X. 3. 32.

सूतप
Sūtapas  (V)--one of the seven sons of Vasiṣṭha, and Ūrjā; 1) Br. II. 11. 42; Vā. 28. 36; Vi. I. 10. 13. a sage of the Raucya epoch. 2) Br. IV. 1. 103. 

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (VI)--a Śiva god. Br. II. 36. 33.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (VII)--a Marut of the first gaṇa. Br. III. 5-92.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (VIII)--a Vānara chieftain. Br. III. 7. 236.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (IX)--(Paulapa) a sage of the Rohita epoch. Br. IV. 1. 64.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (X)--(Ātreya) a sage of the fourth Sāvarṇa Manu. Br. IV. 1. 91. Vā. 100. 96.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (XI)--a son of Sena. M. 48. 23.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (XII)--a son of Pariṣṇava or Pariplava. M. 50. 83.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (XIII)--Gods of the Sāvarṇi epoch. Vi. III. 2. 15.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (XIV)--a sage of the XII epoch of Manu. Vi. III. 2. 35.

सुतपस्
Sutapas  (XV)--a sage of the XIII epoch of Manu. Vi. III. 2. 40.

सुतप्ता
Sutaptā --a R. of the Plakṣadvīpa. Vā. 49. 17. 

सुतमित्र
Sutamitra --a Marut of the second gaṇa. Br. III. 5. 93.

सुतलम्
Sutalam  (I)--an under world and the residence of Bali: represents the two knees of the Lord; 1) Bhā. II. 1. 27; 5. 40; V. 24. 7 & 18; VIII. 13. 14. Built by Viśvakarman. Bali was sent to this as punishment but was pleased with it: the great cave which Bali and Prahlāda entered; 2) Ib. VIII. 22. 32; 23. 3 & 9, 11-12. reached by Kṛṣṇa and Rāma to recover their brothers killed by Kamsa; Bali then as Indrasena welcomed them; 3) Ib. X. 85. 34-38. Pātālam, assigned to Bali by Vāmana. 4) M. 246, 69, 75-9; Vi. II. 5. 2-3.

सुतलम्
Sutalam  (II)--the second world of white soil: residence of Brahmanas; 1) Br. II. 20. 11, 14, 25; Vā. 50. 11, and 13. here is the town of Mahājambha and other Asuras and Nāgas. 2) Vā. 50. 20-25.

सुतहोत्र
Sutahotra --a son of Svarbhānu; had three sons Kāśa, Śala, and Gṛtsamada. Vā. 92. 2.

सुतापी
Sutāpī  (I)--a daughter of Devakī and one of the seven wives of Vasudeva. M. 44. 73.

सुतापि
Sutāpi  (II)--the avatār of the Lord in the second dvāpara. Vā. 23. 120.

सुतार
Sutāra  (I)--an Yakṣa gaṇa. Vā. 69. 39. 

सुतार
Sutāra  (II) (Sutara)--a gaṇa of the 4th Sāvarṇa Manu of 10 gods. Br. IV. 1. 84, 89.

सुतारा
Sutārā --a daughter of Upamadgu (Cal. Edṇ. and Wilson-sister). Vi. IV. 14. 9.

सुताल
Sutāla --a ṛtvik at the Yāga of Brahmā. Vā. 106. 36.

सुतुष्टिमत्
Sutuṣṭimat --a son of Ugrasena. Vi. IV. 14. 20.

सुतीर्थ
Sutīrtha --a son of Suṣeṇa. Vā. 99. 273.

सुत्या
Sutyā --a special ceremonial of the Soma sacrifice (of Pṛthu); the havis for Bṛhaspati offered to Indra, and hence the Sūta--Bṛhaspati and Indra, master and disciple; the wrong offering led to Sūta's varṇa vaikṛta. Vā. 1. 34; 62. 137.

सुत्राम
Sutrāmas (Sutrāman Bhā. P.) --(Sūtrāmaṇa-Vi. P.) gods of the epoch of the thirteenth Manu, of the Raucya Manu (Sutrāmaṇas). Bhā. VIII. 13. 31; Br. IV. 1. 97-99; Vi. III. 2. 38.

सुत्रामाण
Sutrāmāṇa --one of the three devagaṇas of the 13th Raucya manu; these devas drink ghee given in Prayājya homas. Vā. 100. 101, 104.

सुत्वत्
Sutvat (Sunvān) --the son and pupil of Sumantu: father of Sukarman. Br. II. 35. 31; Vā. 61. 26. 

सुत्वान
Sutvāna  (I)--the name of the daityas. Br. III. 6. 14.

सुत्वान
Sutvāna  (II)--a grandson of Jaimini, taught by him one Samhitā of the Sāma Veda; he taught his son Sukarma. Vi. III. 6. 2-3.

सुदक्ष
Sudakṣa --an Ajita deva. Br. II. 13. 94.

सुदक्षिण
Sudakṣiṇa --the son of Pauṇḍraka: King of Kāmbhojas: attacked with Jarāsandha the western gate of Mathurā, and the eastern gate of Gomanta, performed funeral rites to his father. In order to take vengence on Kṛṣṇa, he worshipped Śiva who directed him to pray to Dakṣiṇāgni out of which would spring up an abhicāra fire which would kill Kṛṣṇa. He did so but the Agni was not able to meet Kṛṣṇa's cakra and returned only to kill Sudakṣiṇa himself. Bhā. X. 66. 27-40; 50 11[5]; 52. 11 [7].

सुदती
Sudatī  (I)--an Apsaras. Br. III. 7. 8.

सुदती
Sudatī  (II)--(Sadvatī) a daughter of Prītī and Pulastya, mother of Parjanya and wife Agni. Vā. 28. 23.

सुदन्ता
Sudantā --an Apsaras. Vā. 69. 7.

सुदंष्ट्र
Sudaṃṣṭra  (I)--a son of Ajāta and an Andhaka. M. 44. 84; Vā. 96. 141.

सुदंष्ट्र
Sudaṃṣṭra  (II)--the adopted son of Asamanjasa. Vā. 96. 141. 

सुदरिद्र
Sudaridra --an old poor Brahman of Pāñcala deśa who had the four cakravākas (in previous birth sons of Kauśika) as his sons, all learned Brahmans. The sons left for yoga giving a verse (on their previous births) to their old father to show it to the king and get money and land. Thus he did and got much wealth including many villages. M. 21. 3-10.

सुदरी
Sudarī --a daughter of Vṛṣaparva. M. 6. 22.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (I)--a weapon of Kṛṣṇa, known as Cakra; 1) Bhā. I. 8. 13; III. 19. 22; VIII. 4. 19. reached Kṛṣṇa when Mathurā was besieged by Jarāsandha, and was used to kill Śatadhanvā; 2) Ib. X. 50 11[2]; 57. 21. sent to the sun and moon to ward off Rāhu's attack; 3) Ib. V. 24. 3. presented to Ambarīṣa; fell upon Durvāsa when he raised a spirit to attack Ambarīṣa who begged to spare the sage and the Cakra did so; 4) Ib. IX. 4. 28 & 48; 52. 11 & 12; XI. 27. 27; XII. 11. 14; Br. III. 5. 28. 40. 66. a weapon of Hari, at Kāśī. 5) M. V. 29. 17; 30. 67; 33. 35; 34. 37.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (II)--a son of Bharata. Bhā. V. 7. 3.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (III)--the husband of Oghavatī and a sage, called on the dying Bhīṣma. Bhā. IX. 2. 18; I. 9. 7.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (IV)--a son of Dhurvasandhi and father of Agni varṇa (of Kuśa vamśa). Bhā. IX. 12. 5; Br. III. 63. 209; Vā. 88. 209; Vi. IV. 4. 108.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (V)--a Vidyādhara who mocked at Angirasa's ugliness and was cursed to become a reptile until  released by Kṛṣṇa; when he seized Nanda, Kṛṣṇa came to his rescue, and at his touch the serpent was transformed into the Vidyādhara. He bowed to the Lord and went to his region. Bhā. X. 34. 12-18; XI. 16. 19.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (VI)--a tīrtha visited by Balarāma. Bhā. X. 78. 19.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (VII)--a son of Puṇyajanī and Maṇibhadra; an Yakṣa. Br. III. 7. 125; Vā. 69. 156.

सुदर्शन
Sudarśana  (VIII)--a Jambū tree (see V. P.). M. 114. 74. Vā. 285. 22.

सुद
Sudas --an Apsara gaṇa from winds. Vā. 69. 57.

सुदान
Sudāna --a Śiva god. Br. II. 36. 32.

सुदान्त
Sudānta --a son of Hṛdīka. Br. III. 71. 141; Vā. 96. 140.

सुदामन्
Sudāman  (I)--the florist of Kamsa: welcomed Kṛṣṇa with Rāma and presented them with choice garlands; was blessed with long life and happiness. Bhā. X. 41. 43-52.

सुदामन्
Sudāman  (II)--defended the northern gate of Mathurā when it was besieged. Bhā. X. 50. 20[3]. 

सुदामिनी
Sudāminī --wife of Śamīka. Bhā. IX. 24. 44.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (I)--a son of Sarvakāma, father of Kalmāṣanemi (Mitrasaha-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 9. 18; Vi. IV. 4. 39-40.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (II)--a son of Cyavana and father of Sahadeva (Sandāsa-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 22. 1; Vā. 99. 208; Vi. IV. 19. 71.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (III)--a son of Bṛhadratha and father of Śatānīka. Bhā. IX. 22. 43.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (V)--a son of Vīrasena and father of Kalmāṣapāda: a friend of Indra. Br. III. 63. 175.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (VI)--a son of Caidyavara. M. 50. 15.

सुदास
Sudāsa  (VII)--a son of Ṛtuparṇa. Vā. 88. 176.

सुदूघमुखी
Sudūghamukhī --a Śakti. Br. IV. 44. 56.

सुदेव
Sudeva  (I)--a son of Dakṣiṇā and Tuṣita god. Bhā. IV. 1. 7-8.

सुदेव
Sudeva  (II)--a son of Campa and father of Vijaya. Bhā. IX. 8. 1. 

सुदेव
Sudeva  (III)--a son of Devaka. Bhā. IX. 24. 22; Br. III. 71. 130; M. 44. 72; Vā. 96. 129.

सुदेव
Sudeva  (IV)--a son of Cancu. Br. III. 63. 118; Vā. 88. 120.

सुदेव
Sudeva  (V)--a son of Rukmiṇī and Kṛṣṇa. Br. III. 71. 245.

सुदेव
Sudeva  (VI)--a son of Madirā. Vā. 96. 170.

सुदेवी
Sudevī  (I)--the mother of Ṛṣabha. Bhā. II. 7. 10.

सुदेवी
Sudevī  (II)--a devī and consort of Kṛṣṇa. Br. III. 71. 251; Vā. 96. 234.

सुदेवी
Sudevī  (III)--wife of Dharma. M. 171. 48.

सुदेश
Sudeśa--(c)  a Kingdom; 1) Br. III. 68. 20. the country of Janamejaya. 2) Vā. 93. 21.

सुदेष्ण
Sudeṣṇa --a son of Kṛṣṇa and Rukmiṇī: went with the sacrificial horse of his father. Bhā. X. 61. 8; 89. 22 [2]; M. 47. 16; Vā. 96. 237: Vi. 28. 1.

सुदेष्णा
Sudeṣṇā --the queen of Bali Vairocana, son of Sutapa; issueless Bali advised her to have intercourse with sage Dirghatamas; finding him old and blind she sent her slave girl (Nurse-Vā. P.) to whom were born Kakṣīvān and Cakṣuṣa; the king found this out and persuaded the queen and sage once again; the sage agreed on condition that she  smeared all his body with curds and salt and licked the whole of it; she did so omitting the bottom portion; the sage cursed that her first son would be without buttocks; on her request he agreed that her first grandson would be born like that and not her son; she got five sons, Anga, Vanga, etc. Br. III. 74. 34-88; M. 48. 61-79; Vā. 99. 34, 68-86.

सुद्यु
Sudyu  (I)--the son of Cārupada and father of Bahugava. Bhā. IX. 20. 3.

सुद्यु
Sudyu  (II)--the son of Abhayada and father of Bahugata. Vi. IV. 19. 1.

सुद्युम्न
Sudyumna  (I)--one of the ten sons of Cākṣuṣa Manu; Ilā converted into a male: (Kimpuruṣa); once when he rode into a forest on a saindhava horse, he came upon Umā's pleasure garden where he with his followers were transformed into females. This was due to a boon granted to Pārvatī by Śiva. In this womanly form Budha saw and embraced her. Aila Purūravas was born of this union. Sudyumna wanted to regain his male form and prayed to Vasiṣṭha. The latter waited on Śiva who allowed Sudyumna to have male form and female form in alternate months. Returning to his kingdom he was not liked by his subjects. His three sons were in charge of Dakṣiṇāpatha. In the fulness of time Purūravas was placed in charge of Pratiṣṭhāna, Sudyumna leaving for forest to perform penance; father of three sons, Utkala, Gaya and Haritāśva (Kiratāśva-Vā. P.); (Vinata-Vi. P.); being once a female had no share of the kingdom; however got Pratiṣṭhāna, through Vasiṣṭha's help; that was given to Purūravas. Bhā. VIII. 5. 7; IX. 1 (whole); Br. II. 36. 79-106; III. 60. 14-27; M. 4. 42; 12. 16-17; Vā. 62. 91; 85. 15-19; 25. 28. Vi. I. 13. 5. IV. 1. 10-16. 

सुद्युम्न
Sudyumna  (II)--a Mantra Brāhmaṇa Kāraka. Vā. 59. 131; 62. 67.

सुधनुस्
Sudhanus  (I)--a son of Kuru, and father of Suhotra. Bhā. IX. 22. 4 & 5; Vi. IV. 19. 78-9.

सुधनुस्
Sudhanus  (II)--a son of the daughter of Yudhiṣṭhira. Br. III. 71. 259.

सुधन्वन्
Sudhanvan  (I)--a son of Virajasa Prajāpati and king of the East (West-Vi. P.). Br. III. 8. 18; Vi. I. 22. 11.

सुधन्वन्
Sudhanvan  (II)--a son of Kuru. M. 50. 23; Vā. 99. 217.

सुधन्वन्
Sudhanvan  (III)--a son of Dhiṣṇu and father of Ṛṣabha; a charioteer of the Devas. Vā. 65. 102.

सुधन्वन्
Sudhanvan  (IV)--a son of Satyahita Vikrānta (Satyahita-Vi. P.) and father of Jatu. Vā. 99. 225; Vi. IV. 19. 82.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (I)--a Pratardana god. Br. II. 36. 31.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (II)--a son of the III Sāvarṇa epoch. Br. IV. 1. 80; Vā. 100. 84.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (III)--the guardian deity of the East. M. 8. 9. 

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (IV)--a sage of the Cākṣuṣa epoch; attained heaven by tapas. M. 9. 22; 143. 38.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (V)--a son of Aśvinī and Akrūra. M. 45. 33.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (VI)--a son of Dṛḍhanemi. M. 49. 71.

सुधर्मन्
Sudharman  (VII)--a son of Dharmasāvarṇi. Vi. III. 2. 32.

सुधर्मा
Sudharmā --the heavenly sabhā sent by Indra and brought to Dvārakā by Kṛṣṇa, taken by Vāyu under orders of Kṛṣṇa; in this Kṛṣṇa seated himself. 1) Bhā. I. 14. 34-38; X. Ib. 64 [1]; Br. IV. 9. 6; 10. 23. It formed the council hall of Dvārakā. Here Kṛṣṇa met the elders. Entered by Kṛṣṇa after the Kurukṣetra war; 2) Ib. X. [67 (v) 42]; 68. 35; 70. 17; 80 [12]; XI. 30. 4. went back to heaven after Kṛṣṇa's departure to it. 3) Vi. V. 35. 24; 38. 7.

सुधर्माण
Sudharmāṇa  (I)--a group of 12 gods of the Raucya epoch; 1) Br. IV. 1. 55, 59-60, 97. partake in upayājya sacrifices. 2) Vā. 100. 101-5.

सुधर्माण
Sudharmāṇa  (II)--a group of gods of the IX Manu. Vi. III. 2. 21.

सुधर्माण
Sudharmāṇa  (III)--a group of Gods of XIII Manu. Vi. III. 2. 38.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (I)--a son of Ghṛtapṛṣṭha. Bhā. V. 20. 21. 

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (II)--(see also Vairāja): a son of Viraja and Gaurī) a lokapāla; father of Vairaja. Br. II. 11. 13; Vā. 28. 11; 50. 206; 62. 66.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (III)--(also Vairāja) a son of Kardama; a lokapāla of Lokāloka hill; attained heaven by tapas. Br. II. 21. 157; 30. 40; M. 124. 95. Vi. II. 8. 83.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (IV)--a Kaśyapa and a sage of the Cākṣuṣa and Raivata epochs. Br. II. 36. 61, 77.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (V)--a disciple of Lokākṣi, an avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 135.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (VI)--a son of Vāli, an avatār of the Lord. Vā. 23. 160.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (VII)--an Ajita deva. Vā. 67. 34.

सुधामन्
Sudhāman  (VIII)--a sage of the Raivata epoch. Vi. III. 1. 22.

सुधामन
Sudhāmanas --a group of 12 gods of the epoch of Uttama Manu and also of the II Sāvarṇa Manu. Br. II. 36. 26, 28; IV. 1. 55, 67; Vi. III. 1. 14.

सुधामान
Sudhāmāna  (I)--a group of gods of the X epoch. Vi. III. 2. 25.

सुधामान
Sudhāmāna  (II)--a son of Prajāpati and lord of the Eastern direction. Vā. 70. 16. 

सुधाम्बुधि
Sudhāmbudhi --is Madirāsindhu. Br. IV. 28. 79.

सुधावन्तौ
Sudhāvantau --months of Iṣa and Ūrja. Vā. 30. 9.

सुधावापि
Sudhāvāpi --see Amṛtavāpikā. Br. IV. 35. 6.

सुधिय
Sudhiya  (I)--a group of gods of the Tāmasa Manu. Br. II. 36. 43; Vā. 62. 37.

सुधिय
Sudhiya  (II)--a group of gods of the Tāmasa epoch. Vi. III. 1. 16.

सुधीर
Sudhīra --the son of Kṣemya, and father of Ripuñjaya. Vi. IV. 19. 55.

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (I)--a son of Rājyavardhana and father of Nara. Bhā. IX. 2. 29; Br. III. 8. 35.

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (II)--a son of Rāṣṭravardhana. Br. III. 61. 9.

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (III)--the son of Dhṛtimat and father of Dhṛṣṭaketu. Br. III. 64. 9; Vā. 89. 9.

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (IV)--a son of Vikrānta and father of Nara. Vā. 86. 13.

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (V)--a son of Kevala and father of Nara. Vi. VI. 1. 39-40. 

सुधृति
Sudhṛti  (VI)--a son of Mahāvīrya and father of Dhṛṣṭaketu. Bhā. IX. 13. 15; Vi. IV. 5. 25-6.

सुनक्षत्र
Sunakṣatra  (I)--a son of Manudeva and father of Puṣkara (Kinnara-Vi. P.). Bhā. IX. 12. 12; M. 271. 8; Vi. IV. 22. 4.

सुनक्षत्र
Sunakṣatra  (II)--a son of Nirāmitra and father of Bṛhatsena. Bhā. IX. 22. 47.

सुनक्षत्र
Sunakṣatra  (III)--a son of Sahadeva. Vā. 99. 284.

सुनन्द
Sunanda  (I)--a chief attendant on Viṣṇu; 1) Bhā. I. 14. 32; II. 9. 14; VII. 8. 39; VIII. 20. 32; 22. 15; X. 39. 53; 89. 57. a celibate and devoted to Hari. Praised Dhruva and followed Hari going to Pṛthu's sacrifice. 2) Ib. IV. 9. 30; 12. 22; 19. 5. Attacked Asura followers of Bali. 3) VIII. 21. 16.

सुनन्द
Sunanda  (II)--a disciple of Brahmā. Vā. 22. 16.

सुनन्दक
Sunandaka --a gopa friend of Nanda. Bhā. X. 34. 4.

सुनन्दन
Sunandana  (I)--a son of Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. X. 90. 34.

सुनन्दन
Sunandana  (II)--a son of Purīṣabhīru and father of Cakora. Bhā. XII. 1. 25-26.

सुनन्दनम्
Sunandanam  (I)--a Janapada of the Bhadrā country. Vā. 43. 19. 

सुनन्दनम्
Sunandanam  (II)--a forest in the Brahmakṣetram. Vā. 59. 129.

