Śūryakānta --a Kulaparvata of the Uttara Kuru country. Vā. 45. 25.

सूर्यकुण्डम्
Sūryakuṇḍam --in Brahmakṣetra. Vā. 59. 122.

सूर्यतेजस्
Sūryatejas --a son of Maṇibhadra and Puṇyajanī; an Yakṣa. Br. III. 7. 122; Vā. 69. 154.

सूर्यपदम्
Sūryapadam --in Gayā. Vā. 111. 54.

सूर्यभक्त
Sūryabhakta --eligible for Pārvaṇa śrāddha. M. 16. 9. 

सूर्यमण्डलम्
Sūryamaṇḍalam --seen after 1000 years in the 27th Kalpa; all yogas and mantras came out of this. Vā. 21. 65.

सूर्यरथ
Sūryaratha --the sun's chariot, made by Brahmā out of the parts of the year with Vedic metres as horses; described; equal to those Varuṇa; his attendant gaṇas in different parts of the year (one gaṇa for every two months) and its motion detailed; has only one wheel. M. 125. 37-47; 126. 1-47; Vā. 51. 54-67. 52. 42-8.

सूर्यलोकम्
Sūryalokam --for a bath in Sangameśvaram. Vā. 111. 3-4, 10-11. M. 191. 78.

सूर्यवंश
Sūryavaṃśa --to be revived by Manu at the end of Kali. Bhā. IX. 12. 6.

सूर्यवर्चस्
Sūryavarcas --the Gandharva presiding over the month of Ūrja; a Mauneya Gandharva; 1) Bhā. XII. 11. 44; Br. III. 7. 2; 23. 21; Vā. 69. 2. with the sun in the months of Māśi and Panguni; 2) Ib. 52. 21. in the sun's chariot during the Phālguna month. 3) Vi. II. 10. 18.

सूर्यव्रतम्
Sūryavratam --in honour of the Sun god. M. 101. 36.

सूर्या
Sūryā --a daughter of Kālindī. Bhā. X. 58. 20.

सूर्यारक
Sūryārakas --a western country. Br. II. 16. 60.

सूर्योपराग
Sūryoparāga --observed by Kṛṣṇa and the other Yadus by bathing in Syamantapañcaka and fasting. Bhā. X. 82. 1-11. 

सृजवान
Sṛjavāna --a son of Dyutiman. Vā. 28. 7.

सृञ्जय
Sṛñjaya  (I)--a son of Uttama Manu. Bhā. VIII. 1. 23.

