Sṛñjaya  (II)--a son of Kālanara(la) and father of Janamejaya; king vanquished by Kṛṣṇa. Bhā. IX. 23. 1-2; II. 7. 35; Vā. 99. 14.

सृञ्जय
Sṛñjaya  (III)--a son of Devamīḍha and Māriṣā; wife Rāṣṭrapālī and father of Vṛṣa and other sons; 1) Bhā. IX. 24. 29 and 42. went to Syamantapañcaka for the solar eclipse. 2) Ib. X. 82. 13 and 24.

सृञ्जय
Sṛñjaya  (IV)--a son of Dhūmrāśva. Br. III. 61. 14.

