Senāni  (I)--a commander-in-chief; 1) Br. II. 29. 76. an epithet of Skanda; 2) Ib. III. 42. 9. a number of them in Bhaṇḍa's army; also Cāmunātha; 3) Ib. IV. 21. 76. of Tāraka; 4) M. 148. 38; see Senāpati.

सेनानि
Senāni  (II)--a name of Vighneśvara. Br. IV. 44. 69.

सेनानि
Senāni  (III)--a Rudra. M. 171. 39.

