Saindhava  (I)--the king of Sindhu country could not defeat Arjuna supported by Kṛṣṇa; 1) Bhā. 1. 15. 16. killed Abhimanyu during the Kurukṣetra war but was slain by Arjuna; see Jayadratha. 2) Ib. X. 78 [95 (v) 30], 35.

सैन्धव
Saindhava  (II)--the horse of the Sind on which Sudyumna rode to the northern forests. Bhā. IX. 1. 23.

