Saindhava  (III)--(c) a kingdom watered by the Sindhu; noted for horses. Br. II. 18. 48; IV. 17. 27; M. 121. 47.

सैन्धव
Saindhava  (IV)--a disciple of Śaunaka; again divided the Samhitā into two parts and gave to Muñjakeśa. Vā. 47. 46; 61. 53; Vi. III. 6. 12.

सैन्धव
Saindhavas --were enlisted by Jarāsandha against the Yadus; 1) Bhā. X. [50 (v) 3]. country of the. 2) Vi. II. 3. 17.

