Saimhikeyas --the fourteen sons of (Asura) Simhikā and Vipracitti; however only 13 names are given; they had their own sons and grandsons forming groups in thousands (hundreds-Vā. P.); vanquished by Bhārgava, son of Jamadagni; 1) Br. III. 6. 18-22; M. 6. 25; 249. 51, 67; Vā. 68. 17-22. city of, in the northern slopes of Maryāda hill. 2) Ib. 40. 11.

सैरन्ध्री
Sairandhrī --a Kaśyapa and a Trayārṣeya. M. 199. 12.

