Sopānapaṃktis --thirty-six of them lead to the cot of Śrīpīṭha (named). Br. IV. 37. 57-61.

सोम
Soma  (I)--a son born of Atri's eyes; honoured at birth by Śiva and Umā; borne for 300 years by diks (directions) and when released became an amśa of Brahmā who took him in his Vedic chariot of 1000 horses to his loka where Brahmaṛṣis adored him as their king and was praised by Mantras; nourished the crying Māriṣā in her babyhood with nectar; presented Pṛthu with undying horses. 1) Bhā. IV. 1. 15 and 33; 14. 26; 30. 14; 15. 17; Br. III. 65. 1-20; M. 4. 49; 23. 4-15; 198. 1; Appealed to Pracetas not to destroy trees and offered their daughter Vārkṣī in marriage to him, married the twenty-seven daughters of Dakṣa; Kṛttikā and other stars as his wives; cursed by Dakṣa he had no issue and was struck with disease propitiated Dakṣa and recovered. 2) Ib. 2. 12; 5. 13; 146. 16. Bhā. VI. 3. 14; 4. 6-16; 6. 2, 23-24; VIII. 4. 21; 5. 34. Appointed by Brahmā as Lord of Plants, Brahmans and stars; worshipped  for a life of enjoyments; also called Rājā; father of Budha; 3) Bhā. VIII. 18. 15; X. 84. 47; XI. 16. 16; II. 3. 9; IX. 1. 35; Br. III. 65. 46. 48; M. 11. 53-4. got rid of his consumption by bathing in the Prabhāsā; worshipped largely in Śālmalidvīpa; 4) Bhā. XI. 6. 36; V. 20. 11-12. conquered three worlds and took Tārā, Bṛhaspati's wife by force. Tārā who was pregnant was given back to Bṛhaspati through the intervention of Brahmā. This was Budha. 5) Ib. IX. 14. 2. 14; Br. III. 65. 28-44.

सोम
Soma  (II) (Candra s.v.)--a Lokapāla with his city Vibhāvarī on the north of Meru; 1) Br. II. 21. 33; 22. 14. 15; M. 266. 26. Lord of stars, and one face of Śiva: served as calf when sages and Pṛthu milked the earth-cow; 2) Br. II. 24. 46; 26. 41; 27. 112 ff.; M. 10. 16. his rays gave rise to certain Apsara clans: Kaśyapa made him king of Brahmans; 3) Br. III. 5. 80; 7. 22; 8. 3. 77. 36. 204. M. 11. 63. a Śrāddhadeva: Lord of Pitṛs: (1/8) amśa of Śiva coming out of the dhāma that issued along with tears of Śiva: Nine women desired and enjoyed his company; 4) Ib. 23-1, 8; 31. 12. one of the nine grahas with white colour; 5) Ib. 93. 10-17. in the Devāsura wars, was vanquished by māyā of Kālanemī, took part in the Tārakāmaya, helped Varuṇa at the suggestion of Indra; 6) Ib. 150. 153; 174. 24; 176. 1-33. the dot in him is the earth's shadow; 7) Ib. 176. 5. propitiated in the installation of an image and in house building; 8) Ib. 265. 39; 253. 27. born from the ocean of milk; 9) Ib. 250. 2; 268. 18. world of; 10) Ib. 91. 1-10. nectar of, drunk by Pitṛs and gods; 11) Br. II. 23. 39, 69-73. feeds rivers by causing rain. 12) Vā. 51. 14-21.

सोम
Soma  (III)--a son of Sāvitrī and Pṛśni. Bhā. VI. 18. 1.

सोम
Soma  (IV)--a madhyamādhvaryu. Br. II. 33. 15. 

सोम
Soma  (V)--a Vasu: a son of Dharma and Sudevī; had five sons Varca, Budha, Dhara, Urmī and Kalila. Br. III. 3. 21; M. 5. 21, 23; 171. 46; 203. 3.

सोम
Soma  (VI)--a Sukhā god. Br. IV. 1, 18.

