Soma  (VII)--the temple of, in the Supakṣa hill. Vā. 39. 63.

सोम
Soma  (VIII)--a mukhya gaṇa. Vā. 100. 18.

सोम
Soma  (IX)--a son of Atri and Anasūyā. Vi. I. 10. 8.

सोम
Soma  (X)--a Vasu; the son of Bhagavān Varca. Vi. I. 15. 110, 112.

सोमक
Somaka  (I)--a son of Sahadeva and father of Janhu and 99 other sons of whom the youngest was Pṛṣarṭa, in previous birth Ajamīḍha. Bhā. IX. 22. 1-2; Vā. 99. 208; Vi. IV. 19. 71-2.

सोमक
Somaka  (II)--a son of Kṛṣṇa and Kālindī. Bhā. X. 61. 14.

सोमक
Somaka  (III)--one of the seven mountains of Plakṣadvīpa (Śākadvīpa-M. P.) which enters the sea; from it Garuḍa took amṛta for his mother. Br. II. 18. 77; 19. 11-12; M. 122. 15; Vā. 47. 74; 49. 10; Vi. II. 4. 7.

सोमक
Somaka  (IV)--a son of Sudāsa; Ajamīḍha was reborn when the line was delayed. M. 50. 15. 

सोमकल्प
Somakalpa --the 19th Kalpa. M. 290. 7.

