Skanda  (I)--a son of Agni and Kṛttikas; father of Niśākha and others; 1) Bhā. VI. 6. 14; Vi. I. 8. 11. the presiding deity for the Angārakagraha; 2) M. 93. 13; Br. II. 74. 48; 26. 33. in the Tripuram battle; 3) M. 138. 24: 181. 32. spoke in praise of Benares; 4) Ib. 182. 1; 184. 74. in praise of; 5) Ib. 185. 2-4; 192. 6. a commander of gods; 6) Ib. 230. 7; 266. 45. ety. 7) Ib. 159. 1-3. also known Kumāra, Kārtikeya; 8) Br. III. 10. 43 and 51; 32. 54, 59, IV. 14. 8; 30. 105. Lord of Naiṛṛtas. 9) Ib. III. 41. 17 and 52; 59. 14. 

